user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Amanda Lott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLRqvqOScSw7ymeAH3B-tIRceiQXtu6EiH_WvlA-OM8tnDP6Rp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They gave us a time limit of an hour and a half abut didn’t take our order until just over 30 minutes after arrival and we didn’t receive or food until an hour after placing our order. If they had tried to enforce the time limit I would have made a big deal at that point. During our time there no one came to see if we wanted more drinks, my Nonna’s coffee never got refilled after making her wait 25 minutes for it in the first place and overall the service was actually pretty bad. I’ve been serving for almost 20 years so I get it, sometimes you’re slammed but there’s steps to take in between taking and order and delivering an order that need to be taken to ensure guest satisfaction. You need to tell people that food will be a longer wait. You tell them that their meal is coming, it will take a little longer than expected but is there anything else you can get them in the meantime while they wait. It’s just common courtesy as a server to practice that behaviour. On top of that, if guests are going to be waiting a longer time for food, the food that they’re served should be hot upon arrival. Making guests wait a hour for food without any notice isn’t great, but it’s absolutely unacceptable for them to receive cold food after an hour long wait.
The food was pretty terrible too. Undercooked vegetables, dry and overcooked meat, dry potatoes, flavourless and soggy Spätzle all served to us lukewarm or cold. The only tasty thing on the Menu was the blaukraut but the rest was not palatable. It kinda just added insult to injury for all of us that we had to wait for such lacklustre food.
My sister planned this birthday dinner for my nonna and I could see how sad she was when food took so long and especially after everyone started to complain because the food was terrible. I don’t think any of us will be returning to this restaurant when there’s the Old Bavaria Haus or even the Italian Restaurant Piva we could have gone to. All of us came over an hour out of our ways to go here and it was not worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQAmeFJCrVxK33I2SpnHQmeyMO3_WzTwuhDLKn&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Naveen Sivasankar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVD85c8-gPz6lah-8hC6Wc52PIW1l9gF6x2wQmy27iEI7TaAflN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was a good introduction to German cuisine, but there are some things that could make the experience better.

The atmosphere was great! The place was well-maintained and had a nice, homely vibe. The service on the other hand was just okay. The food took a while to arrive, and there was some confusion around some of our additional requests.

The food itself was quite tasty, but some items were pricy and some things that we wanted to order were not available. We got the camembert, potato pancakes and spatzle to share, and I got a Worsteiner beer, a regular schnitzel, and a chocolate mousse for myself. I enjoyed all of these items, but I thought that the schnitzel was a little dry and the chocolate mousse was a bit expensive.

Overall, I think this was a good experience but the price, the service, and some of the food items prevent me from giving it a perfect rating.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbqvjZ2gtWk60oSoQYJ8zUrYZneDM9KApP3ngi&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Eugene Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWt86BWkSUXxjxM4Yp4KjTVz_EVidisvYISk3vfLg8W-FEoFQr4Vw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lunch menu at reasonable prices. Most surprising is that desserts are house made. Saw the chef making apple strudels from scratch at the back. Can't wait to try their dinner menu and other desserts.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOVbexW0XvoYY4R1HfyiyGkf_nu0mmYyO1q0TV&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Momo Grey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1yKdTQOoB2LWd9nMFxefdCTf4PGEFfPBITeV_PLh0I2I1xZd80A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stopped by for lunch, got vegetarian schnitzel and Spätzle.  The schnitzel breading was deliciously crunchy.  The potatoes were well seasoned and the cabbage was so darn good.

I loved all the different beers and different glasses for them.

The place was very clean and service was good and friendly.  I'll def be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNf4lQ4p_XEV6UhJDpHiLyP1fIZpDAyopkAGRlm&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"David","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnMeRH6pyTpN_xJHIE9lHdy8QLCVFPVA9aLNJm4mAEDwg3_C1Rkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I like German food, but the rest of my family isn't so keen. Our kids were a little hangry and we found this place and I really enjoyed it!

Gulasch soup (meat and vegetable soup) - Ordered to get something quick for the kids, but it was too spicy for them. I enjoyed it.
Tannenbaum platter with full size schnitzel (Beef rouladen, schnitzel, bratwurst, spatzel) - Split between adult and child and was heartily enjoyed. Next time would ask for gravy on the side.
Schwarzwalder Schnitzel (mushroom gravy) - great!
Kasespätzle (cheesy pasta) - Not a big hit with our picky eater, but I thought it was good. Not enough vegetables in it for me.
Side of sauerkraut.

$110 plus tip.

Next time, I want to try Schupfnudeln!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMKMnPFgmmSJcLQAyenxGpRC4DlzOUAY0yRaSY&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Daniel Stierhof","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTnxC26kuYF9GGcmGnd5PsIIr3J2upRJpAmop0SUGQrXDb68M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tannenbaum, a family-operated establishment with a Bavarian influence, presenting both lunch and dinner options. The service was on point and quite friendly however the food was the star of the show. The Tannenbaum Platter was our go to this time, it serves as an excellent choice for those eager to taste a variety of dishes, featuring Beef rouladen, schnitzel, and bratwurst accompanied by spatzel and vegetables. This was especially delicious when paired with a German beer.

German restaurants are rare around here so we look forward to our next visit which we are looking to include trying the Schweinshaxe, a dish requiring advance ordering to ensure its fresh preparation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBZkidFLkYNZsSv2K90kTLPV-IpIdjfp6Eetlf&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"Marcus L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAm1ka_ESYBlOFfTbfcnGmFcYKuqYakfSxihPN9UkLOeVieLhZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A wonderful German restaurant located in the Columbia Square Plaza with the friendliest staff and really great German food.

Had the TANNENBAUM PLATTER A sampler plate which included: Beef rouladen, schnitzel and bratwurst served with spatzel, and vegetables. It was definitely worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZf_hzmjdaVHNKwk92Zub7W_PUJMm1fhSIUDVb&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Michelle ROQUE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVD5Ft2yZYkozXs1swLhpIu0nnpqHjqQIX3ls8oMAIBKwcM8hbs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"These kind of food doesn’t take an hour of preparation  to be served. The server  old lady was a little bit off of her jokes, my co-worker thought she was being serious. The other servers are looking stressed and unhappy too.
Expensive too","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOx60kQloyAesJNYTLZ604KSFmk7yIeth6z3Uq&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-12-10"}]

My wife and I truly enjoyed this dish. Made to perfection with a plethora of taste in one dish. Definitely will be coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMy95ROxUfleXIDFEGfkChj6hLFPOzb0gPMknf7&fid=0x0:0x68ebc9aff9d9b505"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Gee Ewing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJeZ4OP5M7fsWVAitA-fGvuWB8KuZtq-Dd9VVZ3Ee5TqmP50g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My coworker and I picked the restaurant simply because we had never had East African food before!
I have no experience with this cuisine, so I can't speak to the authenticity of it, but it was FANTASTIC.
I had the veggie combo, and as a big eater, I couldn't eat all of it, so A+ on the portion size.
My coworker had lamb of sorts, and it was quite tasty as well.
The person working, was very friendly, and the food came out quite quickly as well. In and out in 35 minutes made this a great lunch time meal for us.
I'd eat here again!
The only thing I was surprised about though, thought there would be some chicken options. Not a complaint, just an observation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYhWpoIPDY9xkr2aET2Ctau9A23n_8wPyJnME-&fid=0x0:0x68ebc9aff9d9b505"],"When":"2022-10-8"},{"Name":"James Kan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVk_o12iCtyO0gE_QoPCj5qJ7UUQkuic2cEzUnsQvn8LpSf4EV-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have tried African injera 11 years ago in Saskatoon, however, the restaurant closed.
I am great my best friend brought me here, to have delicious African food again.
Very good price for each order you want to pick, and they serve pretty much twice as you need food.
Injera is well known a sour flavour pancake, which looks many holes on the top of the flat bread. Soft pancake with hundreds of hole, put those meat or sauces on, that is maximum those food tasted in mouth.
I would love to come again and again for the injera meals.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9fhz1B0r-K7SpK5Mxvg4O0S-QCTiWI0CnnykC&fid=0x0:0x68ebc9aff9d9b505"],"When":"2023-8-7"},{"Name":"silveryfeather208","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKIV1DAc6oAZcKGUjDYKQfX3Js6BWSD-KkYIFsB6AYpaKFALg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I have no other ethiopian restaurant to compare this too, but portion for price is so wonderful. Although the food wasn't extra special, it tasted fresh and hearty, and price is great, so I give it 5 stars. Service is good! Cute little atmosphere there too.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Azeb A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIfQ9puc9EZxXlJr3oAzuQuWGM9s2aTgc1mtth6hNFiaTTX7A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Massawa restaurant has accommodated  our big family with children for a dinner. The food was really good especially the Tibs. The waitress was amazing, welcoming, and very proportional. According to our group of coffee lovers, the coffee they had had the best taste with a hint of ginger. Our gratitude goes out to the waitress for the amazing service she provided us and for taking care of the other customers in the restaurant even though she was the only one there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andrew Ferguson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVClrrX_-Wt5j3aCHo-S6JYfETzTRqLkHzGlV5LFh0G3R32gm8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Excellent food, very tasty and reasonably priced. Noisy (popular!) which made it a bit hard to hear our server, who missed our son's order. She was very apologetic and they whipped up his order immediately after being informed. Highly tasty and looking forward to going again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIK-DCBsPJNLqz9uCGurtNTgtdmj-8vS4HxnlC&fid=0x0:0x68ebc9aff9d9b505"],"When":"2021-8-10"},{"Name":"Selam Herba","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLgr-rflxntENOwMfWKRJI_DoSn1gfsxzwe9vZkiBk6IrjoNw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely delighted with their new menu. Excellent service and incredibly delicious food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6bhzPzBAEoIHnsPVtskZbXCi2CjYn8nUZRuXr&fid=0x0:0x68ebc9aff9d9b505"],"When":"2024-6-23"}]

[{"Name":"Evelyn Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXInuLivNU3_4_Fb29KcZR5WILPoO9N4aWVZYBZmlRc5aJadHZq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time visited, I was impressed by the services and food. The grilled squid is really nice, I don’t see this dish in every restaurant. Clam pasta and crab cake are standard. 10 oz Steak is very nice for the price, cannot request more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUQ7nsyBFqrtXgNv0HzZXulfLvBnQI2fOqyzDG&fid=0x0:0xefee1f34aa4d5625"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Karlee P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKcogQ6RORYiMmSspqCcqCmyIrc0-pWDzMzKeIGrxpNySqDxSl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Piva is perfection, all day long. Their brunch menu has so many options, and we were so thrilled with everything we ordered. The restaurant is cozy and elegant, and made for a great girls’ day out brunch. Don’t forget to make a reso! Thank you for having us!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDay9lWCZKCw8GroovHQUVnnpWdYSpXdFtDu38&fid=0x0:0xefee1f34aa4d5625"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We just celebrated our anniversary at Piva several this week. We shared dishes including carpiacco, wild boar meatballs, duck & fig pizza, stewed beef rib, and tiramisu sundae. The food is okay, the service is excellent. I like that they gave us a complimentary brownie for our celebration. The wild boar meatballs were my favorite that night, 10 out of 10, juicy & savoury. The stewed beef rib was average, it was tender but the flavor was not special, I'd love if it's served with mashed potatoes instead of polenta.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaUmkMqgu8vd6nr2sYsNCMhb8A4iYXQtDujjQw&fid=0x0:0xefee1f34aa4d5625"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"Mel Watson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW5VTs1jV9mGHt6OL9qkfUDCZGdH17wqi7trSn7ITXDNc6XzIfQGw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My boyfriend took me here for my birthday dinner, and I was honestly amazed the whole time!
The service is absolutely stunning. Our waiter (I believe his name was Darryl but I could be wrong) was so hospitable, kind, and a funny gentleman!
The drinks are SO original and just delicious! I highly recommend the Viola drink. It was so good that when my boyfriend stole a sip of mine...he ordered one for himself!
The food was great. We had the warm olives and the Brussel sprouts to start, the miso carbonara and modern Italian pizza for mains, and the restaurant surprised me with a beautiful birthday dessert!
We will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHQx58gP0fXtUAbWAKE7HFST9iFOwmjJ2MM8ZL&fid=0x0:0xefee1f34aa4d5625"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Manmeet Gill","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMXWGi0PTwBnnJPx-2zRWWQX9viRcadnjBye5zp3cT1qRomGuzzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good customer service, server was nice and polite. She was checking in before, during and post meal. The food options were less as it was brunch menu at 1330 for some reason. I wish there were more options as only three pasta choices were available. For an italian restaurant, we expected a few more dishes in pasta style. The food tasted good. The flavours were good and rich. The service was pretty well timed, with no excessive wait time. The atmosphere was good at the restaurant as well, not too loud, not too quiet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPU26a65QhL0Sk96k43AZHN5yARJkPc7IPH4QF0&fid=0x0:0xefee1f34aa4d5625"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Jamie Coo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMtT8SYH3ODglSdZyhsIz5N_cesns6jNpwE2VJCXq0WPBgF9EA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Highly recommend having a reservation before coming, the place filled up really quickly eventhough we came here for a dinner on a weekday. Service in general was pretty good, most food items were also good. We had the brussel sprouts and fritters to start - brussel sprouts were super crispy and flavourful, while the fritter is also pretty good but nothing too special. For main we ordered the Chef's Best pizza, Duck & Fig pizza, Duck, Halibut, and the Sable Fish to split among the table. Highly recommend the Chef's Best pizza and the Halibut - they were definitely our favourites. Duck was also really enjoyable - the cherry reduction went super well with the meat, but it is a bit pricey as the dish only came with 2 pieces of duck. We were quite disappointed at the Duck & Fig pizza as everything was too dry, feels like there is not enough sauce/fig jam. The Halibut itself was cooked to perfection with amazing texture, but the sauce is waaay too salty. For dessert we ordered the lemon tart and the affogato. The lemon tart was great - perfect balance of sweetness and tartness, and the berry jam on the side went really well with the tart. The affogato was just average.
Overall we had a great experience here, and we are quite interested to try their brunch menu as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvR0ogf3PJ6ES4lIO6J1FXeYlBD4j5CK0wpcpV&fid=0x0:0xefee1f34aa4d5625"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Kristy Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEfZ2rjxNiODjhooQ3vu4wU52UFmMssx1nBEw-QrGtiP3D8nPb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Yummy Italian food, it is on the pricier side. The lamb chops are great. The pasta is amazing half the time, hit or miss depending on the day. I’ve had it when the pasta was super soggy and also had al Dante before. I wouldn’t mind coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvTHVqm5F8jYm47yg6tSVndEM40mSAdxk1UGOM&fid=0x0:0xefee1f34aa4d5625"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Joanna Fahmy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJTznlA_q5Xa6Whv5wHF-yEDXEyOSOXOXBiPU7xtZRDBuF4Yw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Came here for a birthday dinner with my in laws, the food was okay, not as good as I thought it would be. The portions weren’t bad for mains but the appetizers were quite small. Highly recommend the cocktail drinks and creme brûlée.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMljaspSkyyl11UY6MFR88dfsQd0pCcp98rClag&fid=0x0:0xefee1f34aa4d5625"],"When":"2024-11-15"}]

[{"Name":"Armando Camberos Pérez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8FdxDC_OMTFdrn-nLWuCWtgsj8uX-2jp3kPCHgIWa4d0-n3in=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Was excited to discover this speakeasy and was a delightful experience. Bartender Steven was not only friendly and professional but he made delicious cocktails; the charcuterie board has been the most beautifully and vast presented in all Lower Mainland bars I've been to! Very reasonable prices as well so definitely a must stop and soon to come back spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWOc1US9z439_ULXwSoOGweG1768vrPkFYKKHa&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-7-11"},{"Name":"Sara Hamilton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKT_OSgS12G-wrX_ZuffRcwItU4CyUDGy7hcIhiimqbRsagHg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of dining at The Flapper Lounge, and it was an unforgettable experience. The food was absolutely amazing—super fresh and bursting with flavor. Every dish we tried was delicious and beautifully presented.
The service was impeccable. Our server was incredibly friendly and attentive, going above and beyond to ensure we had a wonderful time. She even went out of her way to make us a special tea, which was a lovely touch.
The atmosphere of The Flapper Lounge is cozy and inviting, perfect for a night out with friends or a special occasion. I highly recommend this hidden gem to anyone looking for a fantastic dining experience. We will definitely be back","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eunice L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQkzUZXfdvXjIof6QNpWT0Clt0HQWO6_tic3KMTC1-MnvOY65-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I saw this on social media awhile ago and decided to go for a friend’s birthday.

I was surprised!  It’s a stone’s throw away from New Westminster Station - giving plenty of options to have someone else drive you home after (Skytrain, bus, taxi).  I did make reservations a week in advance and that process was quite smooth.

Our server, Stefan was awesome!  He welcomed us quickly when we stepped in and checked in on us often.  We were 1 of 2 tables occupied on a Thursday evening before a long weekend - service was really great and only slipped a little once the small room filled up with a number of larger groups.

Our table was small so with the combo of drinks and snacks we dropped cutlery a couple of times but Stefan was quick to zip in and provide a replacement right away without asking.  He was also creating drinks at the bar constantly while providing really great customer service.

My friend who “likes to drink in dark places” loved this place, the drinks were strong and the snack food is decent.

The Boulevardier Cocktail - the best one I’ve found since discovering it on a cruise ship several years ago and decently priced.  This sweeter cousin of the Old Fashioned was strong and I like the additional effort with their prep of the maraschino cherry.
Cucumber Collins (non-alcoholic) - a “rest” drink in between drinks, it offered that fizzy light relief I was looking for.  It’s nice that a prohibition style bar still had a handful of non-alcoholic beverages.  The price was a little on the higher side, but OK.
Long Island Teapot - we split it for 4 and it was perfect.  It was strong and the teapot/tea cups were a nice touch.  We ended up staying so long we got this at their Happy Hour price which made it worth it - regular price I’m not so sure other than the fancier presentation.

Food: overall the prices were decent for what we did try - we did mostly snacks and I’ll be back to try more.

Crab stuffed mushroom caps - solid offering - even a crazier price at happy hour - would highly recommend
Nacho basket - they tasted good - size was like a half nacho order.  If you like nachos but don’t want to commit to a large basket this is it.
Toasted Walnuts - so great - even better than the ones you get on a plane - really enjoyable when fresh & warm - price was on a little bit of a higher side but no stale walnuts here… worth it in my opinion
Arancini balls - could’ve been better - not sure what happened but based on what I experienced not sure it was worth the $3.33/ball - more worth it at Happy Hour at close to half price.

I’m really happy with this place and have already started recommending it to my foodie/drinking buddies.  It’s pretty unique and it’s close to transit which is a big selling point.  Drinks are strong and well-priced, food is decently priced for the area.  Small tweaks are needed but overall solid for a fun night out with your friends.

Also the customer service was awesome - thanks Stefan and the Flapper Lounge team!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQn1PCxcM0GbvYo0E3gnIbUqvLj22OxYEACMzx&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-3-30"},{"Name":"Brigitte Danis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ60G9H1oSjnh6iz4UwUMjxsTkrvs-7aTGl6fkY55gbzK3cPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friends reserved a table for happy hour at the Flapper Lounge, a speakeasy we were visiting for the first time. The atmosphere is cozy and has a really cool vibe. The service was outstanding, the food was delicious, and the pan pizza here is just incredible! The cocktails were also absolutely delightful. We highly recommend it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPpSi5oR_AuE7DjQMsKEAmunDyScfI0x96jfG8&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Corrina Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbHCtoxSSqrKvXeeXTFLKQrat9aAUqraU1owbUirkuP2c2WQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for the first time ,for Drag Bingo. What am amazing experience. From the decor,to the food and the Amazing drinks to the very reasonable prices. The owner is a lovely lady and her staff all so friendly. I definitely recommend this amazing lounge. Can hardly wait to come back. Before we even left we made reservations for the next Drag Bingo on.Sept 11. The Waldorf Salad was delicious, the spinach dip is total comfort food and the Nachos scrumptious.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leah Thompson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCXYB9oK-Z06SZU_lzEywuCtZ1xfJTSwFkSkz9M0cjkDO58Ok=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is a fun addition to New West. I came here with some girlfriends for a birthday party and the waitress gave my girlfriend free dessert. Drinks were well priced and strong. The decor was cool and I liked how small and intimate it was. The bartender also came over and wished my friend a happy birthday. I’ve been back again since then and will return.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alejandro Hernandez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEjEKeKGRXpoW4hInQ28WAnbGHbdc_f-hEaoP18NeBZtEtVA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is great! Really made me feel like I was in the 20s/30s. The cocktails were so tasty and the food was great. The mushrooms were so good! I went on a weekday, so there were tables available BUT I can imagine that during the weekend the place could get full very fast","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObjVskSa2Q7lItTGy_K42qZjTjQKdqGpS_qzCA&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Chloe M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXr8JKvX5uvV5LemrDd7roHWUvC8Oej6WDibmPj3O5qOcy5rD9c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Absolutely love the drinks here! Everything I have gotten has been absolutely tasty and fun. I always check their Facebook page to see if they have any seasonal or holiday special drinks. I got one during the Halloween season and it was soooo yummy.

The waiter, whom I think is also the owner is so kind and helpful and just a great guy overall. I can tell he really takes pride in his establishment . We told him we think it would be so awesome if one day they are able to expand and maybe bring in live music. It is a small place but the ambiance is very cool and reminiscent of the roaring 20s and days of prohibition. The last time we went we could tell they had also updated their decor which made for a much more elegant feel.

I will say we have had 50/50 experience with the food. One time we got the Arancini, and although the flavor was good, the rice itself was hard, maybe not cooked all the way. But last time we went we got the Nachos and they were on happy hour so I think it was only $10 and they were a great snack and so worth it.

So definitely give it a try, the drinks are great, fun place to bring a date or small group of friends to start of your night, and totally the place we should be supporting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNaMC-FrGl_NQQebBPZp2PqrMzELpZygriNAJl6&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-3-31"}]

The Chef got it right from the pan to the table.

The staff is amazing and friendly.

The wonderful lady helped us with vegetarian options since I eat only vegetarian she provided prompt suggestions on the size of the meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfE_ZsSHejhI9iLI_GZ2ICuCOVaMVzLyMxEHs2&fid=0x0:0x6be6b5b1e7999279"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"lena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJnjpv3iXOfYAv2h46Q5Ve_MH2ad6Z_t-LQhDjXjQfKFLQawg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first time trying this place ! After 3 years of trying to find real middle eastern food in Vancouver ! I am happy to say I found the best place. Every bite feels like you’re in Lebanon. Very cozy, fresh,flavourful and delicious food. Will definitely be there whenever I crave home food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdKRU0TtCufucesFLWgvgnCVrqub2aU6UcucQy&fid=0x0:0x6be6b5b1e7999279"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"NôMāR Åltïçłöś","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKVyqW_kOlfqb-yGJ_Ks--LFkl55GXHpZ6S3YNX2dqaycCck_x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Definitely a great place to go at New Westminster. Delectable, flavorful menu selection  if you want to try authentic Lebanese food. The place can get packed. I’d recommend reserving ahead. Parking can be a challenge.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmBCJ9tbVG62zYCUQ3EAtELqcEVMwEDOPAgYLz&fid=0x0:0x6be6b5b1e7999279"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Timbo Yuen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHAGMrxbZ5FGQPTt4buk-DBF02oPfWRdAjYIUNtb_J6DcNNUbtrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So good. Everything top notch. Best meal we had from deliveries. Lamb shank. Very good. Arguably could've been cooked slightly 10 degrees Celsius less. But everything else is great. A+++","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0yG2ePykRZVqVp9bv_zhmiISD5RKuQVMvIvZq&fid=0x0:0x6be6b5b1e7999279"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Andrea Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM4pS0EMj65wD2yAVVGQIpVP4NowO8zIGvLgz5WtH9vuZgfj2lUQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For 4 people, we ordered the 1/2 Sujuk & Kashkaval cheese and 1/2 Chicken Taouk flatbread, as well as the Lamb shank. The combos also came with a huge pita with 4 different dips, which were all very flavourful and delicious. The Negroni cocktail was also great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOF6iC59vZ0zj9uGemUc8zokRwEwedaee3CunWa&fid=0x0:0x6be6b5b1e7999279"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Sally Rodriguez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYImJyCsPZ1U003tXN4fpaHQosVQMfmFbKD19gt9ySf-YRWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The flavor of the Manoushe was delicious! We ordered the spicy cheese one and the kofta one, and both were excellent. On the other hand, some Lebanese food staples like the hummus and Fattoush salad were disappointing, tasteless  and far from authentic Lebanese flavor.

The place is very nice and comfortable; however, the service is another weak point. We had a waiter at first who never took our order, we called him but he ignored us. So we asked assistance from another waiter, and he made a huge difference. A very friendly and efficient Chilean young man. He was the only staff member who properly attended to the customers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMlI-C8Higuhtg40r0D-YindgoaxLDDzvvUP2JC&fid=0x0:0x6be6b5b1e7999279"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Denis Santos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXF32K7mKkPkKCpGUSEjmRXhqYloH84bwlSW6sQJ_X-vjOnAtXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"At Wild Thyme, the prices may be a bit higher than average for the area, but the food is undeniably authentic and bursting with flavor. While the service can be slow on occasion, the delicious dishes make it worth the wait. The ambience is very simple. The restaurant's commitment to authentic cuisine shines through in every bite. Overall, Wild Thyme is a great choice for those looking for a flavorful dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNf9EFK7vQvqMKcPi8FRHFxojJHnWj_k2llGZbf&fid=0x0:0x6be6b5b1e7999279"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"Kyna Ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWeAn18U7f9LuHN2nbEK91_Xr_RYuaJ54cNr9CH_ah-OcrfCgjwPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious manuoush’eh flatbread. Had the kafta and kashkaval.was delicious and huge, albeit quite costly.
My friend enjoyed her chicken wrap too.
Great service and ambience! Thanks for a delicious meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-76jk_dfL28BUN8qBoGy4iwWjmQHikLGgrHma&fid=0x0:0x6be6b5b1e7999279"],"When":"2024-10-19"}]

[{"Name":"Leira Zamfirescu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmlNFnl6Uk2r4A70GWrPOK27hW1r6YK4fXnN6ZxoPrXOc05uMj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful little place I just stopped by for a bite to eat and a coffee. Lovely owners and atmosphere, DELICIOUS FOOD!!!

The decor and interior could use a bit of sprucing up, but honestly that doesn't matter too much to me personally.

It's a shame that there are bad reviews from the previous owners that seem to be affecting this place's overall rating, so if you're just checking this out now, I would highly recommend to stop by and give this place a try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJ0s1ohbmfOwJ5XcTS-of_7Gr5hPABzfQBH9qu&fid=0x0:0x7c1f56b59780eb26"],"When":"2023-11-5"},{"Name":"cindyloohoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXWmva7WirSLYgRi2432PpCiiedcHptYBKPxA-k_kH-cnMAB41=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Just stopped by for the all day breakfast...service was excellent breakfast was very good...but the final touch of her bringing me a special slice of her homemade pastry was such a nice and kind gesture and it was amazing...as for her daughter helping out she has a voice to be heard as she sang along to the back ground music! It warranted a higher tip. Not sure about the comment below so maybe a new owner? I would only recommend a makeover on the interior just to make it more appealing inside.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angela Hansen (Artfully Angie)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUJ1k9br0TYHeZ5z_Il0tFMWjRt_aF4Nd072UzMdfQ4P32DyY3Zg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Their site says FREE DELIVERY and I'm not even half the km's away from them and they wanted to charge me 4$ extra for delivery and when I debated the facts he basically cut me off and said he wouldn't deliver at all. I think this is very poor customer service and I don't recommend ordering from here. Tried to claim that because I was over a bridge, directly across from them that they could charge extra, despite what their site says. I'm VERY unimpressed!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Werner Meile","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKpLQS0plmHGASOaFRi1GhSVpjlSeIOXruFTlqCZl1oOcH6Gw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"On Sunday July 21st I walked in as two young black men were arguing with the staff. Apparently they had ordered about 30 minutes earlier yet other customers who ordered only five minutes earlier are already being served. The manager did not say nice things or handle the situation well... at all. He made it clear he didn't like these two young men. (because they were black)

One of the young men left in anger but the 2nd young man patiently spoke to the waitress, calmly saying he was hungry and just wanted to eat and that he had ordered thirty minutes ago.

Incredibly the waitress told him to come back in thirty minutes... because they were busy. I couldn't believe what I was hearing.

She was making it clear to him to never come back. Well, neither will I.

Signed
Disgusted 52-year-old White Guy","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Benoît René Brisson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLpBKFPliGtueqmsUH1oeigQFTvh9DFs_B99jmYdP4JpVkFww=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Apparently the food is very good! user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Michael Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIL9mvbIpNSI1G9EduppoepgcZELLoPKO2kYwxujv6bfrvFLA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food was ok and has reasonable prices.  The gnooki was a bit over cooked but the pici pasta was good. It’s a cozy restaurant, however, their ventilation is not the best and gets very smokey in there. Service was slow and disorganized, as we didn’t know which server was helping us.  Throughout the night we saw the same thing happen where customers were not getting menus, water, or orders taken .  The only this was the manager was good and tried to fix things but he really needs to train the staff properly .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBkSEilfqQdXVWiUqaJO8lB7TxsXHX-37Ov0aW&fid=0x0:0x60775b10bf5d551c"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Esther W.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZ44_CjQ6-wehLPc33Ng17kPOWOSFrXqo3jg5WgP7CtwNUYUeR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Disgusting amount of flies on the wall as circled in my photo. Makes me worry about how clean the food is. The scallops were not as pictured in the photo. There was 5 in the menu that they shown, but in real life, I was only served 4.

The remaining scallops were overcooked and very chewy. The size of the scallops were significantly smaller than pictures as well.

The food was underwhelming and expensive. I would not recommend coming back here, although the server was nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZb06Dgno413mSijdKkL7S4_cvv9wPpU-Kakhl&fid=0x0:0x60775b10bf5d551c"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Julian Hui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXva6nMTps59_gZysueK6_Z4Rf3q6G-hVl-STfHAFEObUz1ODMSqA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Service was great. Very attentive and server was checking in frequently to ensure eveything was going well.
Food was decent.  We ordered the Tartufati gnocchi but the truffle flavor was underwhelming and was disappointed considered it was one of the most expensive dish without any meat. Gnocchi tasted fresh with great fluffy consistency though. We also ordered the Tagliatelle Papalina.  The flavor was great but the pasta was not al dente and it was overly cooked and it was way too soft.  Overall experience was good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5xVbSNezTOc5xT_BASy5pzc8ut3MoCJnUd2t1&fid=0x0:0x60775b10bf5d551c"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"Sandra Bao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCFDxhJJiWfK1A7jrtmOnJj84ihz5DRnzbJb1wpxZG21ZEY8Oo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I’m writing this review because I hope people can stop being fooled by the 4.4 scores on their Google Maps.

Food - Food was horrible, especially the two pasta dishes we got- They are not just flavourless but they simply taste bad. I’m not a good cook but I’m sure I can make better pasta than the food they served us… They have 4 dessert options on the menu, but we were told they only had Tiramisu and Affogato. The so called “Tiramisu” tasted awful and overly sweet.

Environment: The moment we walked into the restaurant, we could smell washroom… There were also so many fruit flies flying around us during our dinner. Though the space was wide and my husband and I could enjoy a quieter space (because there were only 2 other groups in the restaurant who sat in different corners), you can tell this restaurant is aged but not well maintained.

Service: The lady who took our order and served us was the only good thing about this restaurant.

Sometimes if the environment of a restaurant is not clean but the food is tasty, we would probably be okay with it, but this restaurant I really can’t justify the $100 we paid for the poor quality of food we got. Will never be back for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkWcoDpegiWwDZcoeHm2OAcNrJBJUFAZ_LUPPW&fid=0x0:0x60775b10bf5d551c"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Roxsan Bargayo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPXVNuCjS5kalz_g8kM1jbSLRYWdH0q6i7AsZkp_K1h5TcRWis=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their Calamarata Profumo Di Mare pasta is truly a standout among seafood dishes I've experienced. The flavor is simply divine! To top it off, I relished every moment, thanks to the fantastic service and delightful atmosphere. 🤤","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOs77XfuEQJq-rD54L32GrcMXOo3q2rJ_-QVsD3&fid=0x0:0x60775b10bf5d551c"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Vince Q","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIh1Bs882K37cbDDZYd4kfA59hdXMTzPce_oh3-IJYn9tkT8A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Went there for dinner with great expectations.  Sadly, it didn’t turn out that way. Service was good and food came out quick.

The food was nicely presented but everything was extremely salty.  We were drinking water for hours after we got home.

We ordered the meatballs and 3 different pasta dishes. All were very salty to the point that my kids didn’t want to eat anymore.

The bread that was served was also very stale.  This is one of the easiest things to execute during service and they couldn’t even do it right.

I hope they are able to fix their issues as it appears to have been a very good restaurant years ago.

Based on my experience, I would not recommend this restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHn5YtYBuwNI7JzFAGIoJJCrHVQraXFjWLgjrg&fid=0x0:0x60775b10bf5d551c"],"When":"2023-7-3"},{"Name":"ronald janampa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvbrv0ZXAYJiT0S8TXMOVme642A9r6o9j7Nzx8aQxPisk7IA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food was absolutely disgusting! The chicken I paid $5 extra for never even showed up, and the pasta was the most revolting thing I’ve ever tasted. It was so bad I had to cook again the entire meal. This place is a joke, I wouldn’t order from here again if it were the last restaurant on earth. Only buy here if you want to waste your money. This “pesto” doesn’t even taste or look like pesto sauce and the size of the dish is ridiculous. I paid $35 for this and you can see the amount of pasta they served.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMH-wQvHCuRWlV_QcrjOIhxZcAQtK2nhW1xhVD7&fid=0x0:0x60775b10bf5d551c"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Alessandro Salaris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrrAFhZ0DWxEznML-_6_HmJZtHRgzEa3bJxENt2tNnWIMlGRMK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best place visited for dinner so far. Amazing food, amazing service. Couldn't find anything that I didn't love of this place. Highly recommended for an authentic Italian food experience. (Recommended by an Italian) Thank you!!😀","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNttQnpmJm-20vXdaJhMHTIqB9RFTMoS95XD0uw&fid=0x0:0x60775b10bf5d551c"],"When":"2024-6-30"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lydia X.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViT0kOTUfe-14sI-XZzuSAMJ11zLMz2yRFRP-Y15rc4maS4qQo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great experience here! From the moment we arrived, the service was fantastic—super friendly and attentive, making us feel right at home.

We were lucky enough to get a table with a great view of the Fraser River, which added to the whole vibe of the meal. The food was just as impressive as the view. We ordered the family platter, and it was a perfect choice for sampling a bit of everything. The spanakopita and moussaka were the stars of the show—both were so flavorful and cooked to perfection. The chicken breast was also a standout, wonderfully seasoned and grilled just right. Tzatziki was fresh and tangy, and the salad was well-balanced and paired nicely with the heavier dishes.

Overall, Taverna Greka is a gem with delicious food, welcoming service, and a great view. Officially my favorite Greek spot in the city.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOi0dPQuN9Md46DBwHJbFTI7rZUQtPpQqEJt61O&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Emma Adams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVg9rP-qmTc9oJ4NlqoykoNimWvcEUc2ztJW9JN_0qBFJbApiWO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Service and food was divine, the place is beautiful inside and the view out the windows along the wall tops it off 👌 special thank you to Koula and her family for the lovely evening 💖","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIb1rCpa6s9cTEuMjG4lDP6a_0as0h6SGCrP-7&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Angelica Yee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIcQojzbdV9sbLoihEwt6NQe8LJ9Oux6JR_irkYfLyJU1tPYS4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We visited as a large group on a busy night and the experience was mostly good. The lamb wrap turned out to be the best entree out of all our orders, but I also really enjoyed the rice and potato sides. Otherwise, the moussaka was delicious as well; the calamari, lamb, and chicken souvlaki however were really dry (this the lower review). There was a really long wait for service during the whole experience but that’s not a bad comment about the server herself, she had no help and served the whole section by herself. The desserts were great too, if you have room for any! I might try it again if I’m craving Greek food in the neighbourhood, but I also know there’s other options nearby.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMP0aTlgClxR7EgJ8Y_p8bGqSdVdnjeYXkPthAQ&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2023-7-3"},{"Name":"Daphne Langford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYr5ATmEShhiDAW7cc5t3sIZEX_QfM5PFsoVSP-fgIbK_Z0EU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was spectacular. Best spanakopita I’ve ever had!!! Everything is made in house from scratch which I value immensely.
And kosta was like an old European mother, making sure everything was perfect, but with a great sense of humour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2AFpR4pgXcTQ9inzRTeJ9BYWLzWWdEbjj3gU&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Kim Yuen Bali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2P6FKP9R6UvKffaf0DNWn4H1wDeGaQ0l_RxoP8l5lpPOsOiR8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here to celebrate my husband's birthday. We had a wonderful view of the river and sunset. The service was great and the food was very delicious! He had the roast lamb and I had the garlic butter prawns. We will definitely be back and will recommend this restaurant to our friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPN44HYY5E3DyY9moq5GtKS92jqGpzcgjnfHsSH&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2023-10-24"},{"Name":"Vanessa Trotte","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0n44mndB7_WzioFY2rmmLmVlWXISXLoNmc6FAqx187vF1tMFsuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing place with really good food, nice service and a beautiful view. Their souvlaki is the best I ever ate. They also support locals by serving local neighborhood beer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdyIbpu30TMn3lji-RMzY1ubYgMkRFrHcJ1yn_&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Doc Parker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIuKyF7wkNlPzYqNijmgn5Gkom607dWAey_Y6D7nukvJ4ALOg8ZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has been a New West Staple for years...and it just keeps getting better with each renovation! Great food and wonderful service last time I was in...nice views of the river.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP88lxN_R2cP9RGMH2TmJJWgLKRup3QTMF2n12D&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice table to enjoy the view of the water! I enjoyed the roast lamb platter here. Moist lamb, good size, boneless and not very fatty. It came with a nice  fresh bowl of Greek salad, rice, potatoes and bread. I was very full after. We tried the Ek Mek dessert which was delicious, not too sweet and was a good size for two to share. I'd come back to try other dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3A8sddvpSwWzm_JVuYgzNfLzERb9xWVcVqBnB&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2023-4-22"}]

While I personally didn’t enjoy the spring rolls, the overall quality of the food and service was impressive. A solid choice for a satisfying meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxslmRqm8w7mUj06eHhUMH5cZbJq4ynMY2H__x\u0026fid=0x0:0xef6261bd8b77bcd6"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Sky Eyes Video","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2JXXl5yK-thMqk8EUNl3FWmyw5SFqlc_KvzAMt-0MdDn-UuKw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food and friendly service! Had a great time here. The Rare Beef Pho was so heartwarming and tasty. Perfect for a rainy day in the Lower Mainland- or any day, really! The Vermicelli Bowl with Lemongrass Chicken and Spring Roll was awesome and tasted very fresh. The Spring Roll was, by far, one of the best we've tried. Even the tea was on point! Will definitely try again when we're in the area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMt9lYNG38Cx5rjQTV4xjD5teMOEvjb3_NZLDrg\u0026fid=0x0:0xef6261bd8b77bcd6"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"James Ting","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMZPDbe5uOZmXiqOwPtktcTYrZneQs0MxbyLVpytAMRAubDRwm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"1st try:  Clean atmosphere, Good Food, decent portion. Very chill, calming music, have A/C, lots of parking behind building. Decent price vs quantity!  Lots of food choices, Fresh ingredients!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXuuELCkw8ka4NVNqeqKsnvLyiar-YFdsDp5Il\u0026fid=0x0:0xef6261bd8b77bcd6"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"Celina Arenillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPvcNqjpmtihcb5J8miFlC4lw0H-EdaSQUtLM4u3kh0_GMHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"As compared to other neighborhood Vietnamese restaurants in New Westminster and Burnaby, I find their Pho a bit bland.\n\nPho 99 location was convenient because it was close to home. Otherwise, will go to the others.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNR9FSzLhcRquPytsuvT_G1XE8loZSSoCKWC3fM\u0026fid=0x0:0xef6261bd8b77bcd6"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"Yan Jie Pan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWtJgsuhwRId0t1MOzd5ywiIXfrBfIFDTo7UODkLUu9At3EXtegw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the lemongrass pork\u0026 2 sunny side up rice, and it’s surprisingly good!! Wasn’t dry and can know that the pork itself was fresh. My boyfriend ordered pho and it tasted great as well. The environment is spacious and clean too, it opens till 11:00pm so it’s convenient for us.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsOIJMr6BU2RwiInGi9px-EiIjtQuGNCCNAL-1\u0026fid=0x0:0xef6261bd8b77bcd6"],"When":"2024-7-5"},{"Name":"Doris Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFpzwh4AE7_YcIgVh0A81OF-ESwUE6I3Qvm8gTnV5a_DrW6qCK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good local gem! Great service and great food. banh mi was delish, the bun was fresh and crispy, grilled chicken was seasoned well. I ordered without the hot sauce and cilantro. Good filling in the spring roll. Pho noodles were the right thickness and chewiness. Soup was refreshing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMc_5mfvtlb_TGAJ82_34XryuhT-YkCeXzwoJTc\u0026fid=0x0:0xef6261bd8b77bcd6"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Queruben Sarabia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnNb0IsjQweJhkeOwktgxmSQfSfdXJIFG4--oIlJdJdJmINRlY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing place! Definitely a hidden gem. My wife and i stumbled upon this pho restaurant because we were in the area. Have to say, we will definitely be coming back! The food, drinks, price and staff were exceptional. The pho broth and noodle, one of the best my wife and i have ever tasted. The drinks were spectacular, not too sweet! Especially the avocado smoothie; which can be hit or miss depending in where you go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPM9WoJtve4mc4YRD5SngoWgff5ciCIEknPoGA\u0026fid=0x0:0xef6261bd8b77bcd6"],"When":"2024-8-22"},{"Name":"Kingramen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU35K9K-3WDR1LhMOarmobzfUiY3qJQT45Dn4vfHiWAkp32qFPGKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The Bun Bo Hue was good, soup was tasty, not too spicy. [{"Name":"Helen Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKI-mzgGlleZ4ePt7mDYbQ4Gabh9zw-OBKk6bKlySQQQboerA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here, the falafels are amazing. The girl is very friendly. My mom was skeptical about the food because it’s a food truck but she was happy with her chicken wrap.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPej09VM2s4gofk1oc9XeTmBXydpzlE6FDV2cP-&fid=0x0:0xc1f36f889546b7e5"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Cole Davis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAOU6XCX3s_R0vWndse-P-J59JZDVGZbi6kfyG2pJARhX4qsYzZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I wanted to gatekeep this place but... it's time yall know about Marven's Falafel and get addicted. I have not tried better chicken shawarma anywhere else, and believe me there's a reason this place has 5 out of 5 stars.

No, this isn't a paid review. Just a hungry hungry customer.

I still haven't gotten a picture of the food because I finish it every time before remembering.

Quick and friendly service, affordable price.

It's just great. Come try it out for yourself.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKTlxjOl00Nf2fQ4h0XHLMXI_12W6qhBOtVcqK&fid=0x0:0xc1f36f889546b7e5"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Samarah Reed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4N2zHSJ_Xl1GWB4xSgF4eglgDF0QeA3gA-S1lMkAZVANC58Mr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's such a good little food truck. It's always outfront of Columbia skytrain Station, but on Sundays I think they are closed. Best falafel wrap","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYW3ZqwRg4YjYykVTEyA4AwL4byNRSa9ogOQS-&fid=0x0:0xc1f36f889546b7e5"],"When":"2024-7-5"},{"Name":"Anneke Feuermann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUU91ogL8zpaW8vhZgYj1lOCcP6dZXgn8d0AI33U5okEgEtA26-Ew=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Marvin’s Falafel is not just good food - it’s good service, too. Over the course of a year we have lived in New West, and have eaten MF food as much as we can. The family who runs it is so kind, genuine, and caring. They ask about your day, they make small talk with you, and when we told them we were moving away, they teared up. Always working with a smile and eager to provide us with a sample or two, they are the absolute best. If MF opened a brick & mortar we would send all of our friends and family there every single night. Amazing food, amazing value, outstanding service. If you have not gone yet, this is your sign. You will not regret supporting this family business and having one of the best meals of your life.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOer1ZJh9c9s_H0ZM_cY0iXqyUvzSm6ItR0EcH9&fid=0x0:0xc1f36f889546b7e5"],"When":"2023-11-24"},{"Name":"Adele Shiphrah Gorovenko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWl-L9s4B7RbfAOcGiMMsPrGgLbrX5K6RArFMNd8-RXWaWXDmue=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's so refreshing to enjoy authentic food from people who know how to make it! This is totally authentic Mediterranean cuisine! Thank you for a delightful experience. The falafels were definitely made with love.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBJtDH1Mc4hJPjBOZJQb3rv1gB0KChuYIMp4mF&fid=0x0:0xc1f36f889546b7e5"],"When":"2024-3-4"},{"Name":"Patt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUmP4t_e1KDxqzOIGol8UhC9LV0_4HteMTwKPEOl6DT-KB5sDm=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"LOVED the food! Ordered around lunch time with some friends, and since it was our first time being there, the lady offered us a small sample of their falafels, with this very tasty sauce on top. I tried asking what the sauce is, but it seems to be a trade secret, which is understandable.

I got the chicken plate. It was hefty, lots of protein on top. No complaints, it was a really good meal. Plus, the server was very polite and friendly. I noted that they also do Vegan options, which I didn't really order, but felt I should mention, in case anyone wants to know. Feel like this may be a gem outside Columbia Station. I encourage anyone to give it a try if you come by it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Diyar Jamal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURnGZh2tPy3a3Tx2DTPrgsFJAOm7t0TTHUHbd4ZR_93GyZ6dWU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Two beautiful sisters are running this amazing food truck if you see my review you should check them out their meals are delicious and good quality if you take one bite of their sandwich it will take you all the way to Iraq 🇮🇶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6vwlez7Jtl3uWYixaLSH-cXtFURYtq-DDKU_j&fid=0x0:0xc1f36f889546b7e5"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"Kieran Brunetti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWLhSO4LqDlvUeANrbKWOFrkQLksGJ7_zd3a0xg2neG3351XyI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First of all the service is excellent. [{"Name":"MJ W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuwYnh2qtalJZ98h2OFd0NprMyEBNKL_u2CZrqCUnFEcLclG2mlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We’ve been here for several times, and it becomes one of go-to places to eat in the neighborhood. The kitchen and the restaurant are very clean and well managed. Food is always delicious, not only just the main proteins but all the side dishes are very good! We’ve tried  chicken, pork, beef, beef brisket, prawn and etc.. all good!! The staff are always friendly and I’ve got to know some of them already. They are very polite with great attitude! I highly recommend this little neighborhood Gem!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMG6gmxWcAXTXHfHm8EZv0fsG5XCZ1jnKg5oc-p&fid=0x0:0x960f0029ed7dff68"],"When":"2024-6-8"},{"Name":"Fruity Musu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8HZgSg502B-3LLZ7CnQ1lBd1e7yyLLu-MZwEKP_k5w6t9E3U=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Bruh, what happened to DB? Went from great portions to small servings. And the sauce? What sauce?? Looks like they took a paint brush and gave it a few dabs. Drinks are still lit, same with the braised eggs but everything else is just sad. Oh and they gave me no fork, guess I’m raw doggin this with my fingers.(just moved, got no utensils)

Ps. That’s a large… smh","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9FCxwago9w7fS3Y-Iknle-d7k3cqkaz4mV3r3&fid=0x0:0x960f0029ed7dff68"],"When":"2024-6-7"},{"Name":"Ariana Alfred","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-tryINbgooLmoVO9nICqwqNjtvSQmEkmI_vVEllYMWiv1lg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was served warm and the side dishes taste amazing and the bean curd has a little bit of spice to it but is also salty and a bit sweet (my personal favourite) and the egg was good also a bit sweet and salty. The spicy dragon sauce was sweet and salty and a little bit garlicy. Overall I loved the dish and I will definitely be coming back. I tried the honey green tea with pearls it was very refreshing and just the right amount of sweetness, a great pair with the spicy dragon sauce!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgVdn2o96boVV3fJGSM7nY-2ivx9FH2z2URvj3&fid=0x0:0x960f0029ed7dff68"],"When":"2023-11-18"},{"Name":"Josephine Ma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4ctBP8R2rm9S8Aa5NyuULMapTvyTQYakS6AvI9Cd025oSy86H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I'd been itching to try Dragon Bowl and then when Chinese New Year came and we entered the year of the Dragon, I really really wanted to go! Finally made it here.  Chinese food can often be quite greasy but this food was not, and I loved that about it.

This location in New Westminster is the second location of Dragon Bowl. I love how the bowls are customizable. There are options for omnivores, vegetarians and even vegans. You can also get bubble tea drinks here. Dakasi bubble tea was in this space previously but it seems that you can still get their drinks here as all of the cups have the Dakasi name printed on them.

The people working here were friendly and polite; however, I do think they could have been a bit more helpful when it came to food selection. My bowl of food came with a "vegetable" soup and as they knew that I had ordered a Vegan bowl I would have thought that if the soup contained meat in it, they would inform me of it. It was only when I sat down to drink my soup and saw pieces of meat in it that I realized it was not a meat free vegetable soup. I ended up giving the rest of the soup to my daughter. Also, there was a bean curd product that looked like noodles which I selected for my bowl. This item turned out to be quite spicy. I was able to tolerate the spice level but with any food item that's spicy, I think it would be good for a shop to give the customer some warning about it. My daughter was sharing this bowl with me, and she had more troubles than me with handling the spice level.

Aside from the soup and spice blunders, I did enjoy the food here and would most certainly come back again. I chose to go Vegan for this visit but the marinated egg looked very tempting so I may choose to go Vegetarian next time!

Service: Could have been better
Parking: Free parking on the side streets
Location: 406 6th St., New Westminster","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOhv-p8o0JSSCIY7ZJ61K51RtabMNYKQ8qAzPRr&fid=0x0:0x960f0029ed7dff68"],"When":"2024-3-28"},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"谢谢 Xièxiè!!
Wow, phenomenal flavor and super yummy traditional and homemade classic Chinese cuisine at reasonable fare with a plentiful serving. The Woodear mushroom 涼拌木耳 for me was great and my favorite for sure. I was actually pleasantly surprised with the Shrimp 大虾, a tad sweet but great texture throughout. The Eggs are also delicious and great flavor.
To say the spring mix is extra as a base, I'd expect a lot more volume in terms of value for money.
Support local businesses!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMr1Y0vxuI0JTvZZQAVUEwO7mJxkl7_CdVamBew&fid=0x0:0x960f0029ed7dff68"],"When":"2023-10-28"},{"Name":"victoria jiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLe0_YcqhvAl5zKt0oDzj8H3B1pS6pBunoZk02QawKbar8ZrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I tried this incredibly Sinicized dish, a modern twist on Chinese cuisine, located in the heart of New West. Parking is a bit challenging, but it doesn't overshadow the delicious flavors. Ordered super spicy rice noodles, suitable for those who really enjoy spicy food because it is truly very spicy. Also had Earl Grey milk tea. The restaurant's assorted side dishes were amazing, especially the celery.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6OLkwf4Ha3fnS7BpqhXhGAULBwhd7QByQ3lJ6&fid=0x0:0x960f0029ed7dff68"],"When":"2023-11-19"},{"Name":"MING YUE KE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNmLITREu_3uxzjFJ1lbKFjaQeDZdToM5wO2uvjAPMyGc2xQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love that they have very healthy options such as brown rice and vegetable base. The meat is tender and the sauces are so delicious. It’s good for dine in because the restaurant is spacious and bright inside.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnSBLS-sOmkgSKhyaDTjN_zHF2NgADpeZ3YwlG&fid=0x0:0x960f0029ed7dff68"],"When":"2023-11-19"},{"Name":"Joanne Huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJePP8B6w1I9fv3dM1Sk-s6cQGASXo6p31ssgMFcVAHo_pKkA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently dined at Dragon Bowl and I must say it was a fantastic experience. The flavors were authentic, and each dish showcased the skill of the chef. The quality of the food and service exceeded my expectations. I'll definitely be returning soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvu85JBYM56T6H8OffCyvfdLKKBSuFN8LxqJog&fid=0x0:0x960f0029ed7dff68"],"When":"2023-11-19"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Hiep Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMRHHZ7t798igHqhwEObqqiXXBYRe7_vTRRS3-gXG7fOgZlXSH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time at Big Way Hot Pot and so I had high expectations since they have many locations and many ppl talk about it. I've also had hot pot at many different hot pot places so will be comparing based on those experiences.

1. Great selection, however it ended up tasting the same like any other place once everything is in the pot.
2. Lining up to get your own food was long, felt like I'm at a food court.
3. We paid by weighing everything in the pot. Mine was $36 😮.  But we got free tea and ice cream at the end.
4. Many servers always asking how things are, but my friends food came 15 min after mine. I didn't eat til his came. My food wasn't as hot anymore.
5. Great view out their window. This place used to be a pub. Interior decor was nice and spacious, good energy.

Yes, I would come back here again if I was in New West. I know what to do next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3at6-mEjYzjDhA-wX3gN7WPffYL1J2thcIBHG&fid=0x0:0x234a3872f78b5ebc"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"AIZY A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW63HuUeCCv9sgK_rgm18cZfVwLP0r1WfmUCdIu1jqRWz_XpAFKzg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It started getting busy right after we were seated. The service was excellent, and we loved being able to choose exactly what we wanted in our soup and create our own dipping sauce. Plus, the view from our window seat was beautiful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfL8SuU1pDh6NdSe2QjKIDXLAdD0uytmivGTr6&fid=0x0:0x234a3872f78b5ebc"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Soung Son","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHkihcNrKz3Cs19caeCuVOR-Yk29MFxtD_S6stmS9PXtHqts7w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First time here and first time ever at Big Way. Food was good, the broth surprised us. We got the mushroom broth and the savory broth. The mushroom is the way to go.

If it’s your first time. Get here when it’s not rush hour and you gotta get in the waitlist then once ready. They give you a pot and you go ahead and place all the ingredients you want inside your pot and then it gets weighed and you pay.

Then take your table flag and sit anywhere you like. I wish the instruction was explained as nobody really explained it but it wasn’t too hard to figure out

Interior is nice still looks similar to the previous business (bar). Overall a solid 3.5 experience and we would come back for sure","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM40cD640NJi-hC3SeWxNPzxj0nFezbsxu43zcN&fid=0x0:0x234a3872f78b5ebc"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Sherry Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJj8Y2C9f-lxQ3f0Wg6KMNVI7g0Vcpm8w53WH722rbEZ4-8Jnf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Me and my friend visited on one of the busiest night of the week. The staffs are very accommodating and friendly even though we were late to the reservation. Food and drinks are so delicious! For broth, I highly recommend the tomato dry mix and szechuan green pepper. For drink I love the tea, super affordable and yummy. Service is excellent as well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOK3iO6y6hwNnJSaGSj3v3N5uRaHG6JSPovWQy&fid=0x0:0x234a3872f78b5ebc"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"Seinn Moh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3eoiEdZ-Q1IRrKZzncaIBXgDNXSSmr15bmZ4YTKV-pRLAoDZR=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an amazing dining experience at Big Way Hot Pot! A special thanks to Kay Z for her outstanding service! She was incredibly friendly, attentive, and made sure we had everything we needed throughout our meal. Her warm personality truly added to the overall experience. Thank you, Kay Z, for making our visit so enjoyable!
I highly recommend Big Way Hot Pot and will definitely be back soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFKdLtbT0-fgYlzlwJ00-X4G6uP9ALb_a247Pt&fid=0x0:0x234a3872f78b5ebc"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"Paul Rondeau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWud2O79gqkHkgkw8XLlTly4855w4zQuECqNb6Iq_cxHMS3y4p-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great hot pot spot! Worth the wait. As soon as you enter, you’re provided with a huge bowl to fill up with all the ingredients of your choice before it’s weighed and then you pick your broth/soup flavour. Everything was great! Load up on seafood, meat and veggies. Try the collagen bone broth flavour - it was tasty. You will also have a full sauce bar to add spice or other flavours. There are SO many staff/servers which was great. My only complaint is that everyone’s bowl arrived at a very different time. I hope this place can sort this out since it’s a little annoying to wait to eat for others when your soup cools. Can’t wait to return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_OQ5ybaDnNazODPRS2eKoA2RM46smKGwUCQPw&fid=0x0:0x234a3872f78b5ebc"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Hannah Nguon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMhvv9ggaZa8CF9qSvuYmrA6EwdW6vVOlwPPtoTJ-P8n_jyMI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Similar to other Big Way locations. I felt like the food here is saltier? The pots were dented and only the pork shoulder rolls (?) were actually in rolls, everything else was just in shredded pieces and sort of frozen still. The servers were nice but the cashier was mumbling a bit and I felt like I was annoying him by asking him to repeat himself. My food came in approx. 10 minutes but my friend’s took 20. I began eating immediately and noticed everything was overcooked. Also, the customers sitting next to us were speaking to a server who misplaced their orders, when they got new orders, it was still the wrong one. The ice cream here is way smaller than the other locations. Most of the other reviews are also saying these things. It’s closer to Surrey which I appreciate, but I would rather just go to the Metrotown locations.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOM4xn-wJE8ksE7URnvVlX2kVgZs2bs79jpq1-a&fid=0x0:0x234a3872f78b5ebc"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Carmen Aboytes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCCLFKJlS62-34BUpujZzDsaZV9yysTxPBmk8fhCY7OoETeMyS6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First time here and first time ever at Big Way!

If it’s your first time, here’s how it works: try to come during non-peak hours to avoid the rush. You’ll need to join the waitlist, and once it’s your turn, you’ll get a pot. Then, you can pick and add all the ingredients you want into your pot. It’s weighed at the end, and you pay based on the weight. We gor to excited, and we paid $119 with a tip (2 ppl)

Afterward, grab your table flag and sit wherever you like. The process is straightforward, but a tip: the broth can get *really* hot, so be cautious—it can make it hard to fully enjoy your meal for a while.

Also, if you don’t want to wait too long, I highly recommend joining the waitlist online before you arrive. You’ll be able to see how many parties are ahead of you and plan your arrival better. Sometimes there can be over 100 parties ahead, which can mean a wait time of 1-2 hours. Planning ahead is key for a smoother experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPk6l5mUSjGHG0iP8rgD-Ka-XEsFHwUD-kBnZb&fid=0x0:0x234a3872f78b5ebc"],"When":"2024-12-21"}]
