[{"Name":"Conan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKONP9LZ55pWz6eE6at_ESUnF8ur4lTWEh3jE_EzN3U4qQFgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I like the salmon fried rice but the dinner box is underwhelming. The fried chicken is a bit too dry, and the sashimi could be fresher. The price is reasonable, though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEY1Tsf3zu0iw2-EonxfXOZChbaEnOHf4UftbJ&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Rafael Prato","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmw8x9RDf8apa9mg4sXkmCUBL57rpPrrUqVoRoTSqzlDDkuKry=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hyack Sushi in New Westminster is a real gem. The best part? The amazing food at such affordable prices. Their Beef Udon Soup is a must-try—so tasty and filling!

Overall, if you're looking for delicious Japanese food that won't break the bank, Hyack Sushi is the place to go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSDsUNyBJya00iV8zQ14wO_-degtHTOa6KSkTR&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-5-29"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The BC roll and the Mango Avocado roll were quite good here. The mango was real fresh mango and the fish skin in the BC roll was nice and crispy. However, the chopped scallop roll was extremely salty as if the salt shaker was broken and released too much salt as all you tasted was salt and it was almost inedible.

The house roll, filet o fish roll, unagi roll were standard average and the sushi rice was average. The miso soups are in really small containers and about 3 gulps of soup each. Overall, just an okay average place for sushi takeout.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtJkEIA0ad4cGE_qzEKMoNWKdmIxYRJEVDlWr0&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-6-19"},{"Name":"Evan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItqym_b8p4Y-FW9783yYhbbkXgbWq5yo1i3Fyi_bB9_Q1tlIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Solid Japanese restaurant, but menu items are a big hit or a miss. If you want to have a super good meal here you just gotta know what to order. Staff are good and check on you regularly. Prices are cheaper then other places.

Good:
-Tempura , it's served with the sauce heated up and super crispy
-takoyaki, it's crispy enough yet not too oily
-takowasabi
-croquettes
-cold noodles

So-so:
-sushi, the rice did not feel like sushi rice but they do have enough filling
-teriyaki beef , the beef had bad texture
-beef udon, amazing noodles but bad beef","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP85tLfs3zGGBTEt-wLTtJWtlc8A6j5kRf-Xyxn&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-9-15"},{"Name":"Annie Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMh7GPmb-fwTeblPqWA2SYP6eaRbXDOeK0rRGXojq0IfUHF2Je=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved this place for its amazing value.

They give 10% for students, and they offer many cheap donburis/yakiudon/udon dishes. Portions were great, tasted amazing, clean environment, and kind servers.

Check it out if you are in the area and want something cheap and tasty to eat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKUOSgV29CQGRQymnywwtpPi2koMOK0RacGB8l&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-5-24"},{"Name":"PristineVIImages Photography","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGCgLiXlOaLAaKvqMsvgvGbp_5MSFtnUtOpoV6XZkTapQsj6oV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Placed order (Skip the dishes ) from this place.
Firstly, I found a hair in my salmon cone, which was quite off-putting and made me question the overall cleanliness of the establishment. Additionally, the food itself lacked freshness and flavor, which is essential for any sushi restaurant. The salmon felt dull and unappetizing, which was a huge disappointment given my expectations for quality sushi.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anna Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGBFoq-wqDtsu2E9VqMHDA2tmYvRFFvgHrGIpF8C_kgl3YFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"They have good food. I really like their beef udon noodle soup as the udon is chewy and bouncy. Their salads have a nice dressing. The yakisoba is good too but more on the vinegary side, which I like but some may not like this. The sushi was tasty.

Price is decent.

Washrooms are clean.

The service is slow when there are lots of customers. We had to wait a while for our bill.

I would definitely recommend this place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Hyaaa…  so late la!

One of those late nights and options were limited so decided to try out this place for some take out while on the way home.

This place is located right beside Douglas college on 8th Street in New West. There are paid street parkings available (I see roof top parking?)

Here were the food I ordered to go;

1. Soft shell crab. Lack of flavour and a bit too crunchy for a soft shell crab to my liking.
2. Tako wasabi. Pretty good, not slimy.
3. Salmon and tuna sashimi. Decent size and fresh but could use a bit of a presentation even though it’s a take out (all sushi places should STOP putting lemon slices near sashimis, they literally cook the outside of whatever fish it touches).
4. Salmon, hamachi, chopped scallops, tamago, albacore toro nigiris. Fresh but the toros missing that buttery taste.
5. Spider roll and futomaki. The futomaki was pretty good. The spider roll was a bit off, maybe because the softshell crab was a bit off.
6. Deep fried poached egg. Surprisingly pretty good, I actually enjoyed it. I could snack on a couple of these.
7. Asari garlic butter. It was pretty bland even though I do smell the garlics. And what’s with so much broth? It’s like a guppy fish swimming in the ocean.
8. Beef teriyaki with rice. The rice could be softer and the beef could be less dry and slightly thicker so it wouldn’t be like eating beef jerky with rice.

When I went to pick up the order, the restaurant was pretty quiet with one table of customers. A weird little sense of silence especially late at night in New West.

The service from the server who packaged my order was okay, although could be more welcoming . Maybe cause it has been a long day and it was late.

As for the food, I was hoping it to be decently okay because I was counting on it to be my late night take out place but they fell short of that… hyaaaa! Too bad for me la!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxYcpM5X7IxUaTms88ji2rYz7uEWMkQu-Yxa7_&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-3-6"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A fun place to try Brazilian street food. The Pastels are tasty with good melted cheese pull in the middle. The assorted deep fried bites were good with mixtures of ham and cheese, chicken, etc. They sell drinks like matte and guarana. The food is on the heavier and greasy side but unique and tasty and good for an occasional treat. They also sell some Brazilian groceries there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJiOrAcrWq514B2xp-vWKX2q45DVkYSoaJ21Vm&fid=0x0:0xb0170e8318381d0b"],"When":"2024-10-4"},{"Name":"Asif Ali Rahman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNaegjRmNO50bHqqeLJtzO0MH4x4EfVRHgZ8LaeHetSvlquLkr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This has been my favourite restaurant until now when I met a rude young girl today. It’s Sunday and 5:30 pm. She was the one without glasses. She was literally dictating my order. I had a guest tonight from out of town who asked me if I could recommend a good restaurant and I brought him here to have shrimp no. 8. I ordered for both of us when she suddenly asked my friend if he eats shrimp what I had just ordered. My friend doesn’t normally eat shrimp but he wanted to try. The girl insisted that your friend doesn’t want shrimp embarrassing me in the process. Then I was ordering the bigger one no. 8. She insisted that my friend can also get the smaller one because the bigger one is expensive. So my friend who likes to eat more ended up eating half of my order too. My friend hated what he had ordered and his comments were that this is a terrible restaurant.

The shrimp that I ordered had very few shrimps in it. Terrible food.  I’m not coming back to this restaurant again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhyp2Im-TVoOCLWtMUIhYuhZnv_9cFmO5xTcc9&fid=0x0:0xb0170e8318381d0b"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Katia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLoejtYSJ-c7Ynia18FuXvHbd745iN29dWOGkI4LU_5lixNeywE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great pastel de queijo! Felt so good to be able to have a little taste of home again. The bolinha de queijo was a little too bland for me, a little salt would have helped. My friend got coxinha de frango and said it was good.

I’d love to see more vegetarian options of pastel like cheese with oregano and tomatoes (pizza style)

Prices are high considering what I’m used to paying for this meal in Brazil but knowing everything is imported is understandable. Unfortunately it’s not the place I’d be able to go to and have more than one pastel.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-_-5au7vaLvlem5OMcRxf9HYAtdTz4dEK5SK4&fid=0x0:0xb0170e8318381d0b"],"When":"2022-11-19"},{"Name":"Tracy Adina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocICXGY0Ftc1fiXva9t_vLaLmPB0I6d-MMI6HH1tL-B4fIYa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried for the first time yesterday. It was sooo delicious and crispy!

We had the plain cheese puffs, which were soo yummy and goey inside. We also had the beef especial pasteis. The crust was super thin and flaky and the filling was delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUH2W4Jxmujl-34SA6Af5q8awXimWxNBYOIrc&fid=0x0:0xb0170e8318381d0b"],"When":"2023-4-25"},{"Name":"L P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2-s14ft5BiaBgf6wD69hCD-Fd8SrdejFGLneEQD2V5-MuDoLU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This place used to be amazing, especially a couple of years ago. Sadly, it seems like they’ve made some changes. The meat pastel now uses a lower-quality, oily cut of ground beef, and the palmito pastel, which used to be just like the ones in Brazil, hardly has any palmito anymore. It’s disappointing to see the quality isn’t what it used to be.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jossana Haas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9HS1fZakd9ATG0kA5vPRp33X316DVs8TMI4cwGuykQPfD6mqz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious pastel and coxinha! Fresh, tasty and great customer service! A bit pricey, but that’s the price to pay when you miss food from your home country… it not only fills up the belly but also the heart 💛💚💙","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6v8_kYKhYU9R5fCMP3fs9zVsxKhvPMopbo8sN&fid=0x0:0xb0170e8318381d0b"],"When":"2021-7-7"},{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I liked the texture of the crisply fried dough in my beef and cheese pastel, but I found it pricy based on the sparse amount of filling and it was a bit bland tasting. It was also a very long wait (15 mins) despite the fact that we were the only ones in the joint. I had to inquire about my order and the cashier explained that my wife’s chicken pie was still being prepared and it was delayed because their gravy machine was broken. By the time I received my pastel, it was luke warm, but the chicken was hot. The chicken tasted like it was from a can though. I had also wanted to try their fresh pressed sugar cane juice but alas, that juice press was also broken. Not sure I would give this place a second try. Maybe for the fresh sugar cane juice as I miss fresh pressed sugar cane juice!  I would have given 1 star but the cashier seemed very apologetic for the delay, so I moved it up one star.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjTagkmTHmqdJK6fXllB7UcqMt6BfcER31AKQE&fid=0x0:0xb0170e8318381d0b"],"When":"2021-11-8"},{"Name":"Julie N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6EagigylvL8HL0PYbonoE3Mv8ji3wWv7NdsGCZfLbfxhVVvyx=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place always looks empty so I thought the food wasn't good but after passing by for so many years, I finally decided to go inside and the food is delicious! My husband got the carne seca and I got the calabresa and the pastry itself was tasty on its own and the filling so flavourful in a good way! I will go back to try every filling. Please check this place out! Warning: dining in will have you smelling like oil after 15 minutes, haha.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"8T8","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLaHAe29LTwj-kDB4Rxp2LPyCtNn-xUw5U4xwT2905ny-JNkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A new found treasure.  The place is very inviting with a wonderful atmosphere.  It would be advisable to make a reservation this early on as the popularity is through the roof.  Food is exquisite and very reasonably priced.  Filipino food at its best.  Audrey, one of the owners, is a phenomenal host, 👏.   A definite must try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP30PJ2TQaBOJPEE-xsVhXPwvNMEg2hjHm9Lbnu&fid=0x0:0x9b798faa1447547c"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"HIP Whistler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-FecbMeYZlwsMsaWgFdwwPW2nyF8LSVTQke8dwSMurLqoMur1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great new local restaurant, we ended up on weekends which they only do brunch buffet. For the price of 35$/head, not bad for a buffet. Cozy and good size interior. Very local design with lots of street parking around. I will come again to try their ala carte on weekdays. Go check them out","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuhRELuaWI2SCrypexf2rTcAl1cy_ZVgfyRyun&fid=0x0:0x9b798faa1447547c"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Carmen Aboytes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCCLFKJlS62-34BUpujZzDsaZV9yysTxPBmk8fhCY7OoETeMyS6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I recently visited this restaurant with high hopes, but unfortunately, it fell short of expectations. While the presentation of the food was impressive, the flavor was lacking.

The meat was bland and uninspired, and for $80 total ($40 per person) for a salad and two main dishes, I expected much better.
The peanut sauce, which should have elevated the dish, was completely missing, leaving the flavors incomplete. The beef broth was the only highlight, but the beef itself was so rubbery it was hard to enjoy.

This place has potential, but they seriously need to focus on enhancing their flavors. I’m all about supporting local businesses, but with prices like this, the food needs to be delivered. Unfortunately, I won’t be returning unless the quality improves to match the cost.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzYPdMNYDg3hRe4yZtHMRQ44nY3ro8VVaJKouT&fid=0x0:0x9b798faa1447547c"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"FLYWITHMEFPV “FWMFPV”","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZQEK-DcupOyEtNJ8shdXyUltfeIOfDfT4t4h58bzxsTcGy5rG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We visited this restaurant two weeks after it opened and ordered the Angus Beef Kare-Kare, Crispy Pata, Sisig, Ensaladang Gulay, and DK Fried Rice. Here’s our experience:

Angus Beef Kare-Kare: The beef was very tough—almost impossible to chew—and the portion was disappointingly small.

Ensaladang Gulay: A simple dish of steamed or blanched vegetables. Nothing particularly special.

Sisig: We got the appetizer portion, but unfortunately, it was underwhelming compared to authentic sisig from the Philippines. I’d rate it 2/5.

Crispy Pata: This was okay. The skin was crispy, and some parts of the meat were juicy, but nothing standout.

DK Fried Rice: It came in a small serving plate, with yellow-colored rice and extremely tiny "baby shrimps." The flavor was fine, but the portion size and shrimp quality need improvement.

Service also left room for improvement. While the food arrived quickly, no one gave us dinner plates—we had to manage with side plates, which made eating a challenge.

On the positive side, the place is spacious and cozy. However, the food portions, quality, and service need attention. I’ll give them another try in a few months to see if things improve.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkHqNw4hu56Qjodc8FEjDXQOfI5bI0E_gC2yRJ&fid=0x0:0x9b798faa1447547c"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Shivangi Taneja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWbJ6lJW5Zgbc0B62TUwBrLnaRdnLviyJx76UYJx9OcAW-TrEdU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Go Dine Kanadiyan is a true gem! Authentic Filipino flavors, a warm and inviting atmosphere, and a team that’s passionate about what they do. Every dish is full of heart and flavor. Highly recommend for anyone looking to experience the best of Filipino cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8FAkd0r-W6wLEZQRYKwuzd9DOcRYzAffy24qy&fid=0x0:0x9b798faa1447547c"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"robert luchene","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjjaxNMjjElbJIf3rYl-fXCWERoK0kjepSp9EFVgxa44LmfWiniQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything was delicious and everything went well for opening day. The only Filipino food I’ve eaten in the past was the spring rolls and pork skewers so I was looking forward to trying these new dishes and wasn’t disappointed. I got the chance to meet the three lovely ladies that own the restaurant.Can’t wait to go back next weekend.

1: Lechon Belly $24.95
DK tender pork belly roll served with liver sauce and house vinegar
2: Angus Beef Kare-Kare $28.95
Traditional Filipino beef stew in peanut sauce, served with sautéed shrimp paste
3: DK fried rice with baby shrimp and vegetables $10.95
4: Lumpiang Shanghai $14.95 10 pcs
Crispy fried minced pork and vegetable spring rolls served with sweet chilli sauce
5: Sari - Saring Tianapy $9.95
Assorted bread basket","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTcb2zY2aKAlTfyIURCu1FriR8qW9NObuCAK3E&fid=0x0:0x9b798faa1447547c"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Celina Arenillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPvcNqjpmtihcb5J8miFlC4lw0H-EdaSQUtLM4u3kh0_GMHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried this restaurant for dinner. Spacious and clean but they could have played some pipe in music.

Bulalo - it needs more flavor. The beef was tender enough, vegetables should have been cut smaller.

Sisig - served on a hot plate but was not sizzling. Sisig could have been crispier.

Turon - this was good. They can explore more flavors such as ube, macapuno, and langka.

Steamed Rice - was too expensive at $4/order, for one person.

The experience was just okay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAMio1volH84YHLH3--cuqh-xn-ZBatfo1PUbO&fid=0x0:0x9b798faa1447547c"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Ben Chua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCSW5TKJ19PNA5OJkbpbbOOnA0K2QN6aO0WAwwmH4V0bXfi0sR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time in this restaurant and I'm really impressed. The waiter is very attentive and the food is great highly recommended","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxD9iCNOk0WaYM9IQ1XVn4JSwYPsL-sxbbLX9u&fid=0x0:0x9b798faa1447547c"],"When":"2024-12-25"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"C L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFSCt_t74XiqlEdz6jDYOHmtwc4pgb3Fve6nsF3wEBwwz9hl0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Unpretentious neighbourhood favourite in downtown New Westminster. This restaurant is part of the Westminster Centre Shopping Centre so parking is easy. Google Maps leads you right to the lot! We went on a Saturday night and it was already packed with locals at 6:30pm. They got so busy that they missed our orders. However, the server was apologetic and rushed to get our orders out. They serve traditional Greek fare such as souvlaki but there are daily chef specials on a whiteboard too.  Homey and comforting; it is easy to see why this restaurant has loyal patrons.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSOt6nAyeyowRanTZK9s6lPYrJB_Hhfgs48qSo&fid=0x0:0xaa8584956b498880"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"NDS Investments","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVikPs6WOuTzc-E92-sZ1BLaCA6XPNBLrLbmLXnMK-Mmkbrg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered through Uber eats and regretted it as soon as we opened the container...food was not appealing, bland, overall...just stale....waste of $60 plus

With our experience, we would not order from this establishment again.

Cannot rate service or atmosphere as we did not dine in","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEtpMInjQNr6rxpkE75Rku2uL8UqBeWr5a54_U&fid=0x0:0xaa8584956b498880"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Feyona McKenna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZDDipdNdQOlJp1dg4n7g1mc0Smm73l7RifmYSNiXg-VGEyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My first visit to Yiannis Greek Taverna in New Westminster was a pleasant surprise. Located inside a mall, the restaurant offers plenty of free parking and a separate entrance from the outside. Initially, the small door from the mall and the dim lighting made us unsure if it was open. My daughter even asked, “Is it open? Why is it so dark in there?” However, once inside, we were greeted by a warm and inviting ambiance.

Despite it being 6 PM on a bustling Saturday, we managed to snag one of the last tables. Our server was exceptionally friendly and accommodating, although she did forget to place our order and my daughter’s apple juice. After a 40-minute wait, she apologized sincerely, assured us she would expedite our order, and offered us complimentary dessert as a gesture of goodwill.

When our food finally arrived, it was worth the wait. The portions were generous, and I ended up taking some home. I had the roast lamb, which was incredibly tender and fell off the bone. My daughter, a notoriously picky eater, enjoyed her salmon in tomato sauce, possibly because of the long wait. My husband had the lamb souvlaki, and our friend tried the potato-crusted cod—both dishes were delicious.

To top off our meal, our server brought us ek mek, a Greek dessert, on the house. Despite my usual preference for chocolate desserts, I was pleasantly surprised by how much I enjoyed it.

Overall, Yiannis Greek Taverns exceeded our expectations, and I wouldn’t hesitate to return the next time I’m craving Greek cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7PQfPHYYweZZsaIMbYUDpVrWoFnfl9YSzp__W&fid=0x0:0xaa8584956b498880"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Bob Ilapogu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXD-elaNhBNUvlaxka6eecnsUdCevkSM7CivjrbdDP1sf2qzFrO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had a medical appointment nearby, with about 40 minutes to spare. We saw the sign for Yianni's and thought we'd give it a try. We were greeted immediately by Kelsey. After explaining that we were in a bit of a rush, she assured us that it would take less than 15 minutes to receive our food. In fact, it took only 10! The prices were extremely reasonable and the food was quite tasty. Kelsey was perhaps the most friendly and efficient server we've ever had. We will definitely return in the future, as we'd like to try more of the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuQMi8qNOegbOtqemVM55SCqnGB04sm3b_BzY&fid=0x0:0xaa8584956b498880"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Ashraf Elhassan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuLkzBLPu9ua4RE40nOlcxoyN63gwKQwJa-XbekTX0jza_GlQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Lamb shoulder was amazing
Service was very good, thank you Erin, we will definitely come back to try another recipe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipML7ls0RSchsql1GcgNyp0H5ZKha5DtQVScRZgv&fid=0x0:0xaa8584956b498880"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Geetika Hora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKuNXRgll-y86-Lux7G-wc87KBo-i7d7XePhOGrz1Fb2zDBfA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered roast lamb meal for take out. This was my second time getting food from them. First time was dine in last year and I recall it was good back then. Not sure what changed. Meat felt so stale, we couldn't take a second bite. Maybe because it was Monday dinner and they are closed on Tuesday which I didn't know, they were probably clearing out old stuff. Salad was nowhere close to authentic greek salad. Carrots were the frozen baby carrots. Definitely spoiled our dinner, had to throw it all out. Never gonna order here again or I will lose my interest in Greek food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6kFEqbhrn0HzX1VHDlIh66m_RONxO6cfLV2Xs&fid=0x0:0xaa8584956b498880"],"When":"2024-4-10"},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Seem like there dishes have gotten smaller but still very tasty.. Service has gotten slow or she forgot to get it. Had to ask twice for mint sauce for my lamb dish.. then I had to get up and ask the kitchen for it.. don’t get me wrong it’s the first time they did this to me.. service is usually really good..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcSkx-2qFrBfS2I-zcX-VStrkTfGlcxX50c1xp&fid=0x0:0xaa8584956b498880"],"When":"2024-5-29"},{"Name":"KC CLAY FLOWERS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWjHlWzIim_FuzOFm9RWi0CgeKWQj7ySiZICNdORO2eQ9BAXZxWAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food fresh cooked and friendly staff good atmosphere . Love this place and highly recommend for Greek cuisine lover another best place in New Westminster here ..
very convenient you also can park inside of the building behind London drug ..
inside the resturant have the restroom accessible for handicap people..
Yannis Greek Taverna is well known Resturant for this area you will love it !!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOHkvc4oGN2ZyEUtXDp5bhu9X2M1ZcF9lZaNVHA&fid=0x0:0xaa8584956b498880"],"When":"2024-2-10"}]

[{"Name":"Lucy Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuwCjTEBDQem6hcfmmxSA0I0nNlJPkS88N0KyjwlMUZAjI_Jdm8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So so good! We went on a Saturday afternoon (around 1pm) and the wait was ~30 mins. I ordered the half sweet & half savoury brunch meal with the sweet berries, french toasts, scrambled eggs and sausage and it was so yummy. Their portions are so filling and everything I ordered was really good. Their fruits are also really fresh and the sweet strawberry jam sauce is so delicious. Their pannekoek (pancake) is my favourite so I recommend! The service was also amazing despite the store being so busy. Will definitely come back to try other stuff on their menu as they offer a huge variety of brunch items :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxixr8Uc4FBVc7gNi14uuf6Qs4kxmbSuJz-OxI&fid=0x0:0xc258dc25b32ed8e4"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Sky Eyes Video","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2JXXl5yK-thMqk8EUNl3FWmyw5SFqlc_KvzAMt-0MdDn-UuKw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is by far, the best breakfast place we have tried in the Lower Mainland. The food is always delicious, the service is quick and kind and the management is excellent. We never hestitate to recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting the GVRD. Located at the New Westminster Quay, you get to enjoy a wonderful breakfast, brunch or lunch with an historic view of the Fraser River.

We were so happy to share the Big Pannekoeken Breakfast (it was enormous!) and to enjoy their delicious Lattes. Do not miss out on their Fruit Cups/Bowls. They're the best in town. Not sure how, but they always find the best, freshest fruit around for their fruit bowls! Really can't say enough good things about this gem of New Westminster.

Be sure to check them out whether you're a New West Local or just visiting for the day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONWM7nSkoypP2p-LJnDbDE_pLEsSck0rRO_Ic2&fid=0x0:0xc258dc25b32ed8e4"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Ashley Beck","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2go2YhxSI7EswM_VSBvu_ZrkSgFk9Mlc_bhBuN0qSdy7S-csG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am so glad I found this place, it’s so refreshing to have a young staff and all of them are so incredibly on point, polite, friendly, all around gave fantastic service every visit I’ve had. I worked in hospitality for years, am a foodie and they do it RIGHT. I cant say enough good things. The fruit bowl is out of this world! I haven’t had such a great bowl at a restaurant in Canada. It’s like being in Sydney - the kitchen was fully capable of serving my request of “NO melon” and has never had an issue doing so... Highly recommended! I would give 10 stars if I could.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0tVduAYNmIQ5WBiMBLJZo8SXTuJjOjV7-nxYx&fid=0x0:0xc258dc25b32ed8e4"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Wong Mirkit","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjiJ8ex8j1X0oWn9473ThU96BZenBcIeH5TCzgYCkF3KSF10c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It’s a fantastic meal with nice view here. I am very impressed with the fruit dish which contains over 15 species of fruits and all is so fresh and tasty. The medium egg Benedict is awesome too. The service is perfect.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDBEIXQHDxodc_nbrABn3XE77R62wwOOgPNf8P&fid=0x0:0xc258dc25b32ed8e4"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Kristy Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEfZ2rjxNiODjhooQ3vu4wU52UFmMssx1nBEw-QrGtiP3D8nPb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Simple brunch food, but things are cooked well. No complaints, but also nothing super special. Open to coming again for classic brunch food. Their side of fruits are great, quality and quantity wise.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcLAD95E-5bsvErMqbBg_EelX3vRtaVcz0QVp_&fid=0x0:0xc258dc25b32ed8e4"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Melanie E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR0bJcxqNkJt-i1wxCH3EaQXevncA86panZszfT__NAs_0KWRp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My friends and I came here for brunch on the weekend. We all enjoyed our meals.

Atmosphere: 5/5 - if it's a beautiful day, go for the outdoor seating near the water. There's also interior seating too with a nice vibe to the place

Food: 4/5 - Two of us had the breakfast platter of chorizo sausage with fresh fruit, roasted potatoes, toast and choice of 2 eggs and the other ordered the savory Dutch Pannekoeken with two range eggs, and turkey bacon. All servings were of decent portions. There are choices for the gluten-free and the vegetarians. A great place for breakfast.

Server - 4/5 - friendly and helpful. It took a bit of time to get our meal.

Parking - 3/5 - metered parking nearby with insufficient parking spots.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMppjHBLiiYCVf10A0RMOBucmxc7_CYPhu4UFRm&fid=0x0:0xc258dc25b32ed8e4"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Virginia Barazzuol","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLL7wkWLIn3uxnKGJhdMyd6yiile32ZYmw8MVcgdfWI-jdUHA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The whole experience was wonderful, good food beautiful view, nice atmosphere ... BUT The fruit bowl at this restaurant tis the most amazing fresh and exotic fruit you will see! Also if you're hot sauce lover you can get a see election of 8 different hot sauces to choose from... Amazing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6apN0qvMNFOUnWYWwmXnBCk1BMG6gYT1Do_o2&fid=0x0:0xc258dc25b32ed8e4"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Brittany","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHTcuSM-4ly1uIP3q2-jgQ_2Vqi7GhBmGO9JykCcOlnN1NYOmqYg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I know it’s a sin to order lunch/dinner at a breakfast place, but I’m not huge into brekkie. I took a risk and got the fried fish sandwich with salmon and it was amazing! Super fresh fish, not heavy on the breading, and the coleslaw on the sandwich is a great “sauce” addition. Would def go again despite not being a breakfast person!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSbgvCceux2QU4ioSPfC8pkT4H16Oyy_5ot_jv&fid=0x0:0xc258dc25b32ed8e4"],"When":"2024-8-25"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A hidden gem and heartwarming dining experience. The owner or staff, both of them, are very enthusiastic about their food and super kind. They have somehow perfected frying fries. The fries are made fresh to order and they give you a heaping amount with the perfect seasoning. Like, if there was a perfect definition of a French fry, they serve it here; hot, fresh, crispy outside, fluffy inside, bursting with potato flavour! Who would have thought this mall food court place served such good fries????!!!

As for the Philly cheesesteak, it tastes very homemade and hearty with really meaty beef. The beef dip is also hearty with lots of beef. The Philly cheesesteak and beef dip were both good but not gourmet or anything, however, they remind you of granny’s home cooking made with love. That’s what this place gives you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoYxU8KEyQVwS8jXtB6siQTzziTL8azkP82-iK&fid=0x0:0x1ecb9130fdc39fb"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Ian Grimsdick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVNAwbGbAg7iHFZCH2ZcRPNQCqhdrLGjma3MI6N7NMRmpkI8DArQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best food court restaurant in the entire lower mainland.  A combination of guilty pleasure food and grilled options that make you feel good. The staff are friendly and helpful, even when it's really busy which it often is as students will come here for lunch. I just had the Cajun pork which was marinated in a great, just spicy enough marinate and grilled on the spot, served with rice and veggies. You talk to people who go there and they'll rave about pretty much everything on the menu.  This is the kind of place you want to see succeed because they seem like genuinely good guys and they're passionate about the food.  And they have a great system to keep things flowing even when it's busy.  Thanks gentlemen.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely wonderful Philly Cheesesteak. Beefy peppery flavour with just the right amount of melted cheese to bind into the sandwich with sweet grilled onions and peppers. Fries were fresh out of the oil fryer seasoned with the perfect amount of salt and black pepper. Really good value for quality and quantity. The guys behind the counter cooking were really nice to boot and struck up a genuine conversation. Great choice to get something to eat if you’re in this mall food court…scratch that…I’d make this food stall the main destination for my reason to visit this mall!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOr8pa9D0h1Vjj6a0lyxFKJKRFcoXmGEGGubjsA&fid=0x0:0x1ecb9130fdc39fb"],"When":"2024-5-4"},{"Name":"Amanda V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZOLydh5sGAptUXnunY5WEfbl7N6dKLnwlzx-ViawgM6fOfXAmPw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wide variety of food on the menu, literally something for everyone! We tried the beef fries & cajun pork, good taste! Owner is lovely as well, and they have slushies with free refill! Such a great summer option. Highly recommended hidden gem!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO91xmjvez1wI5XUtpco4xy1Co4AsvyEsKR53-w&fid=0x0:0x1ecb9130fdc39fb"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Patrice Ayana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOllg0k09Gc0JobV45f-oVFUTx6IqK6OZGrSkFW1cGk9xCvPTsOg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Joined a food group and I saw a few people mentioning this place so I decided to try it. I ordered the Philly cheesesteak sandwich with fries and it was delicious! I also ordered the loaded Philly cheesesteak fries. I will definitely be back again! Excellent service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGwQ1OYhDO0aRh7bksySOS84lyxlcEZZogzpZ_&fid=0x0:0x1ecb9130fdc39fb"],"When":"2024-6-28"},{"Name":"Daniel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvd6-q0LFLnT6Fjanc2ymc9JLptLuzcaQqNrOdzOGpx9n_bEE6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Owner is incredibly friendly and passionate. Order times are pretty fast and you get to watch him cook.

I ordered the pulled pork sandwich combo. The fries are some of the best I've had, well seasoned and crispy. The sandwich was great. The combination of toasted bread with sauce and juicy pulled pork was soo delicious.

Overall, service and food 10/10. Can't go wrong","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO8otfQ_-A5clRjzTQHXzLusOH0JUN71KGzo7O&fid=0x0:0x1ecb9130fdc39fb"],"When":"2024-4-3"},{"Name":"Bonnie Somers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZUWA-6wmQn1fXY7hj9EJECrGoeopb6z_FXpQjZ_RE3JsAMU8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Grilled chicken is excellent! good portion, fantastic service, recommend !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1MVPnSd8jDssGk8lR2OXzd3sEdX_dDmDQdZRA&fid=0x0:0x1ecb9130fdc39fb"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Sahar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX78XZJ0-0JszsjUnipV__49pbD8R8fMYHiB37wWppP0GEXbB5u=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Grill n More is the BEST fast food restaurant at Royal City Centre. Mr.chef is very friendly and courteous. The food that I ordered ( Philly cheese steak) was so tasty and delicious too. 😋
** huge portion and reasonable price.
I 100% recommend this place and I am ready to try different food from this menu in near future..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeI6vE7GjE-F7zoEPyBGHBDeAp4ol9EzlgD4R4&fid=0x0:0x1ecb9130fdc39fb"],"When":"2023-2-28"}]

[{"Name":"Deb PS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2JrjvxBJWPrjHCwBxV9NiRybb9V5GJpynDBuSW5sd6snYZiMa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food is pretty good here and is like back in Trinidad 🇹🇹. Nice how there is also products you can buy.  Prices are  a bit expensive but I guess everything is going up these days. Prices are higher now than the pics I took earlier.  Service could be better. The owner could remember we are in Canada and not all customers like the blunt talk Caribbean people might be used to.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-SbCoGLynf7t60R47LRPN4ypIxIrdC-H9uhjU&fid=0x0:0xc84624e5ac11c49f"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Tracy Mckay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZ7pUrRrPvOE9Ups9f-1JW2JDDrKyYbDrJG4ixBv__A0__w-gGbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My God the chicken curry Roti here absolutely hands down is the best one I've ever had, and that's saying a lot cuz I lived in Toronto many years. The only place I could ever imagine getting one better would be Jamaica itself. Also was given an amazing recipe for jerk turkey and I'm trying it out this Christmas with everything I needed in this cute little shop! If you haven't been here GOOOOOO","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"A I","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKiE3ix1MGEIh3aUa8hRzWMHn16q0kKIa_rfG-AkI-mQxNKkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For quick and consistent Trinidadian doubles , this is the place. I’m usually satiated after one 😋The take debit now as well which means I don’t have to remember to have cash on hand!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSQ7-gBiOQr2p__Rl53nVJA_XcpwdzElRVR7Vj&fid=0x0:0xc84624e5ac11c49f"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Alexander Trinh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAc3fzU016gOBJqCuTq9i3BxzpNuPlX8O4OvZQ14hKIz8Qu9Vf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is a decent enough place to eat. I ordered the chicken roti and couldn't really tell the difference between roti and a curry wrap. I think if I came back I would just order the curry chicken on rice as the wrap is huge and ordering a rice dish would be easier to take home leftovers. The proprietor was very nice but wasn't very helpful with what to order on the menu. Don't drink the tap water as it tastes like plastic bottles","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqFVFByW3dcAaV8HAe_xksK-93voFXiWYaQEyD&fid=0x0:0xc84624e5ac11c49f"],"When":"2018-9-26"},{"Name":"Robert Miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlAkMc5h58DpsuTOrDV5dMZ_QamLBJDA5p60lG4V6c6STBi6Hg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lots of flavour and good spice.  This is one of our favourite places to get roti.  Friendly staff. Enough variety in the menu. Got sorrel, Peardrax, doubles, and beef roti. So good. Never disappoints. My wife is from Trinidad and loves the food from here. So lucky to have good Trinni food close by. Would recommend this place to anyone. We will be back (again). Hope you enjoy it as much as we do.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWHLpP07fRCg9--_LgqtZVYb-Y2QC7Z8ZOMa-f&fid=0x0:0xc84624e5ac11c49f"],"When":"2021-7-29"},{"Name":"Holly M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnAekHx9iy66WJm94JhcYQf95ezw1lFuYjpqckkrR1z3mVVtqQrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"They do not supply forks or plates. We where on our way somewhere and thought we would stop by and try. The food was fantastic but it's obviously very messy. I would have paid a bit more even for a plate and utensils. Other then that very delicious.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brittany L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuy3Eo3Rjfaw1L-ArDB8VtXv-yTheUORxGqdjgQdmZxxskQlJszA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Family owned restaurant, with delicious authentic food!
The staff were super friendly and were great with helping us with recommendations.

Restaurant style is order at the counter and pay first.

I've been trying to find a restaurant that serves ox tail for quite sometime and finally found one. It definitely did not disappoint.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAWDR-Hn4f1CiLr2RjPGvYOtT2yVE6Kjbhe8mF&fid=0x0:0xc84624e5ac11c49f"],"When":"2020-3-9"},{"Name":"April Meza","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5C4E6m3vD2-Srzp5u-1Xn_C-PV0jQ1TX-Ygz_cuHV2wl0g1pfDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had such a lovely experience at the D ROTI SHAK last Saturday. We tried the Sorrel drink and Mauby which were super tasty! The Doubles were delicious and the Phulouries are a new fav! We were also offered a rice and beans for our toddler which was really thoughtful and well received by our little one. Great place for a full meal or snack. We will definitely be going back to this spot next time we visit New Westminster. Clean and bright space. Thank you for the wonderful experience D ROTI SHAK 🤙","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO__PvpasGOdjOQ9YXWr4pLbow0-YAgB1o07jEB&fid=0x0:0xc84624e5ac11c49f"],"When":"2020-3-10"}]

title: Sixth Street Grill

[{"Name":"Allison Pilgrim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOOiObLEftS4YnyoWTj4IlvDc232PLo39cW_S-RFwrhp_3wCwLYg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Crab cake eggs benny was probably the best eggs benny I’ve ever had. Great environment and very friendly service. Even the coffee was yummy! Will definitely be back here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMA2MkgcM0PZPW93WNc4ohqhYHagrSdzXopvcQX&fid=0x0:0x77295d980dad15d0"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Raquel Stone","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-TsSk8es2mMIaMrY-TeApXLSb9oyC8cTxltIJgYYz_KW2DR50=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Okay place to eat it was alright and I enjoyed my meal, I had the crab cake eggs Benny and it was pretty delicious the hollandaise sauce while having less spices than I'm used to was very buttery more than most places I've been so if you like that you'll really enjoy this place it just wasn't my personal favorite but still good. The crab cakes were very good and I really enjoyed them!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzfD6zCMMyZdCnYH6aAt4WOs9H-JjqASgKkTVO&fid=0x0:0x77295d980dad15d0"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"Jim Pook","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIW7HKxL5MTg-_-q3_KQww2_-v3G-3Swg2N1F-FfTyN5jGToOl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time.  Food & service were great! Had Veal Cutlets, salad, baked potato and broccoli & carrots.  Jello for dessert.  Looking forward to going back to try the meatloaf.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTTLt8Iw0oMhTz83l8SSyawn8Uys6nOunhTaa-&fid=0x0:0x77295d980dad15d0"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Clarke Stanbra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWR0Bc-A4VL6RoU2ST5sfMK7jwFbuXT7nZVkkjSWVQYKzegb2Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m so fortunate to only live a couple blocks away. This is my favourite place to go for good comfort food. Everything just tastes homemade (in a good way) and made fresh. All day breakfast, decent prices, cozy old school diner type atmosphere… everything about this place is just comfortable and calm. I love it. For breakfast I love their crab cake benny, for lunch their beef dip or clubhouse is amazing … honestly though I don’t think anything would disappoint on their menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOn5pc2QqA1lNmg4R5xvn-6iOJ-4hDoQthO7_cS&fid=0x0:0x77295d980dad15d0"],"When":"2023-5-24"},{"Name":"Tina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAKiC5J1ql1LsLTTfBwgvAj6sVGUusHXghumDKVG9ZTQ8QjcD_1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"SO GOOD! ❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥

If you’re looking for a cozy, no-frills, bang-for-your-buck brunch place, this is IT.

We got here at around noon on Sunday, they’re busy, with a queue outside. We waited around 15 min for a table for 2.

Really friendly service right off the bat. We got our coffee with a handful of creamer. Our food came QUICK! And it tasted as delicious as it looked. We got 2 coffees, a grill lite, a sixth street hash, and a side of bacon; came to around $43 after tax

Kathy, our server, was so friendly and attentive. Thank you Kathy for making our experience so wonderful!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNl6Sb_FcbYYSvKTTdWzgWgBnGkoUOXepx9BCQi&fid=0x0:0x77295d980dad15d0"],"When":"2023-11-28"},{"Name":"Gulnur Sultanova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXuYGDYaVeVLlUwM-htQX7w_i6mT3hy5fnLa6BTq7BlM9oujRE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely place, quality food, friendly staff. My appreciation to the chef for very tasty and delicious dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8lj6xFQc1C-pxFS7iq-n4tva632MvsR5XKAJu&fid=0x0:0x77295d980dad15d0"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"BON Barker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL6s4O1HFf2haa-W9xjuPJPsbT_ooYYBv4BFI-p1az4VXJBlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a great old school diner. Simple food that is done right. Friendly efficient staff. Prices are extremely reasonable, especially considering you are in Vancouver. I personally love locations that are true original 70's diners that are what they are with little change. I would definitely recommend stopping by. We ate here twice. The first time, there was ample seating, and the second time, we waited for a while to get a seat. Both times, the food came out quickly with the same quality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPR1UgOV10rQHiPAJ5AkS1EaMSuRkd2vJo69fBy&fid=0x0:0x77295d980dad15d0"],"When":"2023-6-18"},{"Name":"Adam Hatch","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUe7DIzvoENQZ4GjCw_X6rw3ru2I8LVPZqfs82HioYw6dYMZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great little greasy spoon in New Westminster. The breakfast hits the spot. I got the eggs, bacon, potatoes and white toast. If you’re feeling a lighter breakfast, you can get the single waffle and add a side. Real maple syrup is also available upon request. Friendly staff and warm atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDB4eS-AVejb2STpNVk9u-U3BuzaAybtJAVdI-&fid=0x0:0x77295d980dad15d0"],"When":"2024-5-8"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Maty Černý","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJOugUarXg3E3zzEt6pLPUy-qN7wFZlEkZav2IRzy1MMhO9Gi7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very pleasant atmosphere. Great menu selection and the food felt and tasted authentic. Sandy was very kind and helpful during our visit","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwspBfKZ3zUWLHKfVuee8EMPYzMhO3hFA_jDKE&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Philippe Rochon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLW8Uu3ICRp1UpHYlF1cY32QJDuh1D3AjB2e9cuRKX9vU3tlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"A friend recommended this place for the schnitzel and said it had big portions but decided to get the combo plate to try a few different things but unfortunately this was a bit disappointing. It was a more expensive dish but only came with about 1/4 of a schnitzel (a bit misleading) and the beef item was dry with some chewy bits I wasn’t able to eat so a bit of a waste. Service with nice but also slow even though we were one of three tables there that night. Beer was good, came in cold glasses. I had a hot piece of pizza later that night which I enjoyed more for only 3.5 compared to the expensive dinner here.

Atmosphere seemed cool, but I don’t think it was worth the price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nyan Saik Krat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjpmJaQF71Wc9RokZI6crvhpCfkHdwd7PPRXDbqQaGzIKvlA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would say the food average is a solid 4/5 for me. It's better than average, but not quite the best you'll ever have. I would highly recommend coming here if you have a craving for schnitzel. The place also has a homey interior that is very similar to old restaurants you'd visit in southern germany.

I really enjoyed the bratwurst and highly recommend it. It was a plump, flavourful sausage that was perfectly complimented with sauerkraut and mustard.

The baked camenbert was paired nicely with cranberry sauce and seemed to be lightly coated with breading, giving it a nice outer texture.

I enjoyed the goulash, but it was a bit too watery for my taste.

We got the Schnitzel Champignon, which was nicely breaded and flavourful. However, I felt that there were not enough sauteed mushrooms in the dish. The schnitzel came with a very nice cabbage side, potatoes and some vegetables. The portion size is fairly large, and we shared the one order between the two of us.

For dessert, we got the black forest cake, which was absolutely amazing. They really knocked it out of the park, so I highly recommend saving some room for dessert!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOKulCcsDOgkbEeHS6384ajtuKyjUoDjSPaYPs&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2023-9-24"},{"Name":"TS OS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrxJ8Fjd3bGSI8mWbF186RbFWyg_DW73VTS3OIkFaxPfXFBEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We walked into this restaurant casually knowing not much about their menu nor any characteristics.  While the menu were pricey, food were actually good, comparable to Katsu and Kolet Schabowy that I am familiar with.  Restaurant ambience was unique, felt historical.  Server was splendid, named Hardeep.  I would like to return to try their pig hock which needs 2 days prior order placed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPN3k8qt1UGSaqaG-KG5F1BDyGIQI-Nx58zbhf&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2023-8-6"},{"Name":"William Soldat (Will Inspect)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDO6rDUZ6Cgoe5kEavK7LgbjcGmtPD3wQDYxRT1RRpJi-QV0u3Nw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was delicious as always, the atmosphere was great.  Pardeep, our server, was very friendly and helpful. Excellent in every way.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhZhg5mQ4DSzBC_1vHG36H5jBOoSO20f-cIPMF&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Sandra F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJhMeThUlXdv3ue7obqN755TvguHbLlgK_sDr5-q48vcvFMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It was a Saturday night and we were the first table.  We were excited to try the Combination Plate which had Schnitzel , beef roulade,bratwurst sausage , purple cabbage and spatzel.
It came out pretty fast. Food was not very hot or fresh. It tasted ok but the beef roulade fell apart as it was overdone. The bratwurst was tasty.
They put all the meat on top of each other and the schnitzel was on the bottom and became soggy and no longer crisp.  The cabbage was maybe an ounce serving  but abit over cooked. and spatzel was not fresh or hot.
I hope they do a better job with time management as food should be fresher and hot.  Red cabbage should be larger and we didnt get any roasted potatoes .
The dessert chocolate mousse was tasty but not worth ten dollars.
I have bern hear a few times but lobg time ago and Food was much better.
You can tell when its not as fresh as it should be.  Server was pleasant.
If we are paying close to 40.00 for the entree, it has to be much better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNVl2UyqrtXKh28ymuc9SyTgPlclLuUprJoFbl&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"Sy Y.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlvv5Hw7BczrB2EJa0tUi7oVzXQrKcexe_QyluaWJfb22gz7A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I recently dined at a Bavarian restaurant and had a delightful experience. The food was excellent, offering a taste of authentic Bavarian flavors. The atmosphere added to the overall enjoyment, creating a pleasant dining experience. I would recommend it for those seeking a taste of Bavaria in both cuisine and ambiance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPU4D82iEYKANfpkybNrYnr8Tt1rtpaj2Ej8peo&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2023-11-19"},{"Name":"Adrian SJ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLES-BQxUhleHLSjJrlTBTVlln5sw1td2GQifq5exn4uHyYL8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Super disappointed in this place. The food was not well done at all. Came out cold, no taste, spatzel was half soggy/ half crispy and way too greasy overall. Not authentic German food by any means. If you are craving a well done, German dish, head a few minutes further down Royal ave to the Tattenbaum German restaurant. Superb quality, authentic meals.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtmxcHZGwtQ87YTNLg1caCC1M83D4hwz6s7F2G&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2024-2-12"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"james corbett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXORPNpjn99AmypwXC5L8gqaCK1buk43veXhtLSzHUK1ZItjmE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Staff are great and will answer any questions you have and will help you make the right choice as they have so many unique poutines to choose from. We had the The Gaucho “Cowboy” it was so much flavor it almost overwhelmed us. The flavors work with each other and each bit is delicious yet never the same as the last bite. We had the smalls and they were still rather large in size so be mindful when ordering as this is not food to be wasted and enjoyed. My friend now wants to go back when back in town visiting as they want to try more of the offerings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxD-Fv9KwStF16etxHTYAFvMdPR51cvrs4J8iQ\u0026fid=0x0:0xe8e154706ece828a"],"When":"2024-11-26"},{"Name":"Patrick Mathieson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINECmDvDDqotX_gLzijWsJWmEoQhBGS6vcf9OOMM2x3OTExg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today, while I was out shopping. I decided to go and grab a poutine from the spud shack. Every time I go there it great as they have delicious poutines, great service and stuff. I ordered myself the medium size of the night market. Which is fries, curds, and gravy topped with ginger beef, spicy mayo, kimchi, crispy wontons, and green onions. It is always a good treat to have on a cold day, but especially after a nice long walk home. Can't wait to have the other ones there as I have had them before.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAY4T9LbfvSNFmjlfgYtaFm5dTOu_Jb2lkNpyN\u0026fid=0x0:0xe8e154706ece828a"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Angelique Clara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1s2Chb6Y3xW_5s_kxXXs4q_8GystuCIu29D3inyfoSNfBMTUD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"we ordered one large butter chicken poutine for my bf and i. we also got jarritos, very affordable and delicious. service was fast as well - would go back 💯","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJnpjkejfqir29FILKRoBNCxmWRjgLoPcIJSSr\u0026fid=0x0:0xe8e154706ece828a"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Rafael Prato","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmw8x9RDf8apa9mg4sXkmCUBL57rpPrrUqVoRoTSqzlDDkuKry=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Spud Shack Fry in New Westminster is a hidden gem for anyone who loves fries. The menu features a delicious array of loaded fries and poutine, all made with perfectly crispy potatoes. The portions are generous, and the toppings are fresh and flavorful. The casual and cozy atmosphere makes it a great spot for a quick bite or a relaxed meal with friends. If you're in the mood for some seriously good fries, The Spud Shack Fry is the place to go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzw8ivcnt-q6uwfOxm-qLQ1sJnFd0LWTumRrbA\u0026fid=0x0:0xe8e154706ece828a"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Albert Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLu_EXMOFkw3t7ieiosbnUm8U0dDlr8SUxo6E0Nm1EZRYvKeA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the best place to eat poutine and burger. Flavor are well balance. Very accessible to skytrain.  Better try and you will love it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJWIWy4GP2gqB9_8EFj3nuSrXWgx8iNKeN7C5O\u0026fid=0x0:0xe8e154706ece828a"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"Tiger Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLkEFqmN0cNu3GtQMnEWNL_6zBvtzErsM0dAxcmtAudz8ViZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Got the pulled pork poutine. I was quite surprised but this is some of the best tasting and textually best pulled pork I've had. The poutine was tasty the gravy was tasteful and the cheese squeaks! All sign of a good poutine the chips even stayed crispy right till the end. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"JonDesmondFPV","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1_GWf0uM3S7qWLVdXu2l2wWxGsR_qcdghlYmvjkyq3NXcpPX4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Had a sloppy joes with fries and a coconut mango milk tea. Sloppy joes was not sloppy at all. This made the meat dry as there was barely any chili in it. Nothing dripping like a sloppy Joe’s is supposed to be. Bun was nice and soft though. Also, the fries were decent. Seasoning was a nice touch in combination with ketchup. The coconut mango milk tea was just that: coconut, mango bits (small amount), milk and… not sure where the tea part went. Just tasted like a glorified milk drink.
Sorry folks, not a win for me, especially when it’s $18 all in. With some minor improvements, this could be a decent place.

Service was prompt and fast so thanks to the staff for that.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiCFf82LO6cyjH7wnLKxm7yvYG5r6MjfywZN2N&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"b s","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQaUgkam2VdoEVVnEYKPrEoy8mn9UWfTv4Z02-0l7j1yP6jQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I'm very disappointed with these dry ribs. They are so dry they should call them jerky ribs.

Dry, very chewy, the seasoning is alright but not good enough to make this taste good. I had a few of them and I can't stomach anymore.

Looks like dog food but I wouldn't give it my dog.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlcPU0KYuyWPFNflA-772hmNIWwK6eusj7e71g&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Mark George","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnnE264HP_HUH6vlS3LzCqMw0M7F15OpmHo-R2xPUEvjsyjgYV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"very disappointing. such a good opportunity to impress given the location. $17 for 1/3 brisket which isnt too bad. the meat is trash though…

Brisket was just pulled potroast. If youre expecting a nice tender strip look elsewhere. It wasn’t rendered well and was very fatty (I love fat, this was no bueno). No seasoning throughout the meat it just tastes like fatty beef. Bbq sauce squirted atop.

Biscuits and jam were decent though…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQHVuea2CcOBAiOGeNohmwb76IIoLKmh27k2Nc&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Miss Mayette","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhoepfdi2GA4VyP2mG3ugg6DC6lF52RgOcoZVf3bT2nvzCZNqx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went off script and decided to get the brisket sandwich. What a great choice. So flavour and tender. I always choose the pulled pork so I haven't had the brisket since Re-Up was just a food truck at the art gallery. I'll have to alternate my choices now. I did get the combo and the fries are delicious but I didn't need them. The sandwich was filling enough!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjoqvT49umOkbvndWAybsOFQ_SvCF7SFCZGvSD&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2024-2-10"},{"Name":"Cindy M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGKoLguedM393K_wR1xMOVrvE3ThWeh1Ms4feKswKRb-YaoDvm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The pulled pork sandwich was delicious, and I usually don’t even like pulled pork. Fries were well seasoned and the homemade soda (lemony and gingery) was not too sweet. There was plenty of seating during lunch on a weekday. Prices weren’t cheap, but quality was good. I would like to come by again to try their fried chicken sometime.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMtSFZ3_XnyOohvMmjsDHfo2pr2CCx4Q3JGX_5-&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2019-1-5"},{"Name":"Tina Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdBaiZVDYBpLht__4O-UBZTbqid-yvjIPiysoxeNFZ7ASwdw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We had a barnyard. Fries and fried chicken, some parts were super salty, but mostly, I barely taste any seasoning. Beef brisket and back rib were not seasoned enough. They put some sauce on top but didn't taste. That's the reason why they gave us extra sauce. So many people recommened me about this place but I won't comeback. Maybe I can get more delicious and quantity food from KFC with this money I paid.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Avery Sloane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJ0UubQijmu-zbHB4SXflZKnuuPR0wA9R_EbSucR-U4I1WIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"BBQ Ribs were perfect.
Beef Brisket was dry
I got 1/3lb of Beef Brisket & 1/3lb of BBQ Ribs but the Ribs were way heavier than my Brisket so kinda disappointed by that as well.
Pulled Pork Sandwich was good flavour but too much coleslaw in the sandwich

ordered through door dash.

would definitely order just the Ribs again","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Autum S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIczel4RoHrOA56qpcMa4zlMMFCrVwmdVvVnhIASQ5oO9oETg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had the pulled pork and southern sweet tea. Tea tasted no different than regular iced tea. Pulled pork wasn't tender enough, but for around $13 for 1/2 lb, it's a good deal for the amount of meat you get. This is very respectable as more restaurants have increased prices due to greedflation and just inflation. Would not go specifically to the mall it’s in just for their food.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Kenny Poon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCkKTuOESfGudPEm0-BDzQVkIamalgjsSUzE_II9VRplB0iEEX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Visited this boutique Taiwanese restaurant in June 2024. The menu is a highlight of Taiwanese cuisine, with a lot of signature dishes of local Taiwan food.

The dining area is a bit small, with about 10 to 12 seats.

Food was served in a very delicate manner, with a lot of side dishes. The fried chicken we had was nice and beef noodle was very close to what we had in Taipei.

Overall a lovely night and we will go again soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9kNMSyruKabZY7BXI1Oz8GONkdr4bPLezShF7&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Kit Yee Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUy4hyLjXryzPjKJf4N3DUJBAsHtZSSuk76pvxFtVmwfHSV1Gtd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was in the New West neighbourhood this evening and found this restaurant was highly rated. I checked the photos online and the “quality” looked legit, so I decided to give it a try.

When I arrived at the foyer of the restaurant, the cashier or counter was right there. I looked at someone who worked there. He was very familiar to me! I recognized he was the one who worked at an old Taiwanese restaurant on Imperial Street in Burnaby super long time ago that I used to go for Taiwanese food. Then I asked this person at the counter and confirmed he and his team ran the Taiwanese restaurant in Burnaby back in the day. Wow what a small world I finally found their Taiwanese restaurant in New West!

I ordered a few dishes (see attached photos). The chicken nuggets, chicken cutlet bento and oyster pancakes were very delicious and they were traditional Taiwanese food that I used to have.

I would like to go back and try their beef noodles in soup and some other dishes next time. 😋🤗

Their copy on the windows of the restaurant said “the best Taiwanese comfort food”. I totally agreed!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObJjjwBNpM5dBr4ettmvzrNFZ8MMM3-PsRGc5E&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-3-10"},{"Name":"Amy Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvtm7hBqZHDYxXgP_oxkelx2FGhwfW-EuwTv9rdyjxo-_-_8Nq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So authentic and yummy. I could tell by the small menu and cozy decor that the food would be homey. As a Taiwanese, this felt super close to what I’d get in Taiwan. The food is flavourful but not greasy - especially the beef noodle soup. The noodles were chewy and bouncy, the broth was not greasy and there was a good portion of beef. I would have liked more veggie with it but no worries. The other lunch bentos were good too, all three of us Taiwanese enjoyed. The peach oolong tea was good and didn’t taste artificial. They didn’t have toppings today sadly. A small restaurant with artwork that reminded me of Taiwan. Looking forward to coming again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3JEfzMp6FG40hY5-343gtZ150jjwsmnGWMFtH&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-2-27"},{"Name":"Charly Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVW7SDQiPwBHCqABdbNsL_MLu_BT3LcZNa4ETMdBHyxv9riHO5dGQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried it first time and I was in love with it. Authentic Taiwanese bento in New West. Even side dishes were amazing as well. I’ll definitely take skytrain here just for the bentos","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7QCsziAOyCX6HgNV5Dlf3SEKfYu7OhTbpv2bc&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Cheryl Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKRqwGsiyntapcBOAHD9FtzNPiBoZCzUhMf_hjWst1Da_zYAf8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Unpretentious Chinese restaurant with authentic Asian/Taiwanese cuisine... most dishes come in a set. Menu is limited but flavours are very good. Set comes with main dish, rice & 2 slide dishes.

It is a family run restaurant, the guy manning the front & serving the water. The place is clean & with a few tables onsite.

Paid Parking on the street available, there's no parking at the restaurant as it is located in a very small premise opposite Nee Westminster Douglas College.

Food is simple but great, highly recommend!
Check it out","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-tJqAk2Zjplz90jG3CMsW-IdzV-GJHgz9Niw8&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Effie W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwAS7Gj-rv1jRBJdMba7ERQYQ4ZbnqJ1iC2dKspsC01Dbz2GYL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Most authentic Taiwanese beef noodles in the Vancouver area. Worst thing about this restaurant is that I have to drive out from Vancouver to have it! The chicken nuggets are also super delicious. I saw a previous review saying that the beef noodle broth is bland or something, but here's the thing-- the vast majority of "Taiwanese beef noodles" you get in the lower mainland are NOT what you would get in Taiwan. They are way too salty or oily but I suppose it suits the North American taste more? Nothing wrong with liking that, they're still good, just not authentic. But the beef noodles at Rong Rong are most definitely the closest noodles to actual beef noodles you'd have in Taiwan. (Disclaimer: I am not Taiwanese but on my last trip to Taiwan I gathered recommendations from many locals and tried a different beef noodle restaurant every single day of the trip).

That said, personally I think the dining in experience is way better than takeout. The noodles taste much better fresh. There is very limited seating, if I remember correctly there are tables for three groups of 2s, one group of 4, and there's one round table.

There is no free parking (15 min short term parking, only 3 spots) but I have never had too much difficulties finding paid street parking nearby. If dining in, you order and pay at the counter first before you get seated.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjx4Xw4UuIsUpL9wK64urd0pn9l50N6uyBeTnF&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2023-8-10"},{"Name":"Wing Wing Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM-NblQ23wPMIDbEZG4qLeVHUJU9mowQi7hKxpBL0edQSZtY9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love this Taiwanese restaurant. The oyster pancakes are a standout dish, perfectly crispy and flavorful. The prices are very reasonable, making it a great value for the quality of food. Additionally, their other offerings are equally delicious, making it well worth a visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1wRhNkcn4w-Om5dldcBPfQEPMPcjlKUEMrpNn&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"Ivan Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7bK0bappyJ1WIHKFRLINWzON0Yz0Hl7-sgPSDVshCh_Si75XYWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing small and underrated place. The restaurant is run alone by the owner, a kind Taiwanese lady who likes to interact with customers. The food is amazing. Authentic Taiwanese cuisine that isn't too common in the area. It's across from my school so I'll likely come here daily for lunch and/or bubble tea/slush drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTSfmyB_mzdUDTfGshOMEXLdMiPdw5K1K6RMtj&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2019-9-8"}]
