user_reviews:
[{"Name":"wah chi yip","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKKBykHMUbkrtJ4cwRRXsjOnAzAcOzwrpq-XVjovUt6A3trFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you like the vintage ambience, you will not disappointed.   All the decorations, the train, lighting, antique tables and chairs are so attractive.
The food are much better than what we expected.  All the meals are all inclusive.
One dish includes a warm medium bread with garlic butter, soup or salad, tea or coffee and ice-cream in one very reasonable price.
The prices are really reasonable for the food quality.  The streamed one pound mussel is only $10.95 and the quality and portion are good.  All the food come out fresh and hot.
Our server is friendly and helpful.
They also offer happy hour.  The prices are more reasonable too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrI1NaEKk18zPVLWjXeCK07YJnH9IyejK96tzI&fid=0x0:0xe216b5a28ce125ce"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"Alexandra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX11ANDfpnFU7GmCeaVtU5cBwuWRqquWAK3F9_AUyciKpah0H5L=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"High on a hill in New West is a very prominent beige, brick and green building, home to The Old Spaghetti Factory, a family friendly restaurant famous for their "it's all included" slogan.

I've been eating here for years and the food has remained relatively the same throughout. Pasta is their mainstay and they have heaps of it paired with a litany of sauces. Appetizers aplenty and drinks galore round out a very robust menu so there is no way that you will leave hungry.

As if that wasn't enough incentive to visit, I can vouch for the astounding efficiency of the servers. Literally just as soon as you place your order, that's how fast your meal is delivered. A quick succession of drinks, followed by your soup or salad and then very shortly afterwards, your main meal.

And of course, the most important thing: The food is filling and delicious, and the prices are by far some of the cheapest around.

In an age where price gouging has become the norm, it is so refreshing to see that some places aren't out for your money, and instead are more concerned with customer satisfaction. I assure you, the experience at Old Spaghetti Factory will never get "old".","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8K66T6181PkX__5WP8s9IAXwgtF6s9kgrOVJi&fid=0x0:0xe216b5a28ce125ce"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"sara karimi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ1XYkwzloxYSsc1EqxvBP-2Mv59HBF7-8-P7UFahyIx3LfqNI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"‏Old Spaghetti Factory is one of the best restaurants in great Vancouver.
‏The atmosphere is fabulous, you will enjoy all of antique tables and chairs, decorations and the lovely train in the middle of restaurant. When you are walking around, old pictures catch your eyes. All of these brings smile to your mouth and good feeling and happiness to you.
‏The start with bringing fresh bread with garlic butter that is so tasty and if you want more, they bring you. Also, salad or soup at the beginning and coffee, tea or ice cream at the end is included in your food. Food is delicious. We got Fettuccine Alfredo with chicken and lasagna. They were delicious, however the portion of lasagna is so small, I wish it was bigger than that.
‏Also, drink we got was good as well.
‏Price is reasonable.
‏The only complaint is although there were a lot of free tables on the floor and trains, they gave us a table in mezzanine and when we asked to have a table in the train they said you have to wait for 20 minutes! And also other parts of the restaurant is closed!
‏Anyway, I highly recommend Old Spaghetti Factory. You will enjoy the time and food a lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeks5UyNYwMesTqd1OPMBx-5OYcdJnlY2ekXzD&fid=0x0:0xe216b5a28ce125ce"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Champagne Kingdom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT9L6nbhgKeVF6uvC80gh6he8ZgVExYxBb0bRQFJovbeiruBo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The Old Spaghetti Factory consistently delivers, and their new West location is no exception. We adored the warm atmosphere and were impressed by the excellent value offered by their All-Inclusive meal options. However, the real steals were the succulent mussels for under $11 and the half-liter of house wine for under $14 – the perfect finishing touches to an already outstanding dining experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5QzZrrk03TLI0HLb9z2GGf5jqWAJ6evFql9s7&fid=0x0:0xe216b5a28ce125ce"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Yvonne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUj_HNmRFhr0uY3k5KAoKohOmCo83kG-cmVR_BGACYiBkVXvGMN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down our favorite place to eat out when we want a great meal. I have been to other locations but this is definitely my first choice. Great food at a reasonable price. They always treat us well and reserving a table is easy to do.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_RCcKQ-tgRt6Qu2y5p_ZuX6tR2KCRMIFfX8YZ&fid=0x0:0xe216b5a28ce125ce"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Chinmayi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVH4UnNpio-g5tml4wocrS6R0rqjdOLc0uP2LiNmjrAs61LNoo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the food and atmosphere. Food tastes very good and authentic, I love how they serve soup or salad with mains and you get an ice cream at the end. The bread and butter at start tastes very good","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2TTjezrL4hulDStRQxIGgpd23SiqbWaUM1vDu&fid=0x0:0xe216b5a28ce125ce"],"When":"2024-10-30"},{"Name":"carly simon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQF_aGyoPI8H3LYAhNV4wwR-mqrrjL3yRed1ybzkG5ohunzlM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Old Spaghetti Factory in New Westminster has been an integral part of our family’s journey for over 45 years, serving as the backdrop for countless celebrations. So, when my grandmother was asked where she wanted to mark her 101st birthday, there was no hesitation—she chose the New West Old Spaghetti Factory.

Owner Clinton and his incredible team went above and beyond to make this milestone truly unforgettable. From the warm welcome to the thoughtful touches throughout the evening, every detail was perfect. The food, as always, was delicious—comforting, consistent, and just as we remembered from so many special occasions.

What stood out most was the genuine care and attentiveness of Clinton and the staff. They made my grandmother feel celebrated and cherished, which means more to us than words can express.

Thank you, Clinton, and the entire team for creating yet another beautiful memory for our family. We look forward to many more celebrations with you in the years to come.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRkruIYyYsm5LJ6KOxmILJLCHcRtSKtb0rVedB&fid=0x0:0xe216b5a28ce125ce"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Your typical Old Spaghetti Factory here, and it’s quite delicious! They have some nice portion sizes, especially since a soup and bread is included with their pastas. We also got their peach Bellini, which was very well made. I highly recommend 	their shrimps also :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsk5sX7bOYqULK1asqrgtdNWH3FvNHXR7vnOaA&fid=0x0:0xe216b5a28ce125ce"],"When":"2024-9-21"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Susan Ninow - Realtor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLhR2xv519-zmTSY9obAY5M46DsiXjVum-r80rdag4lo3d0rCn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Han Lin noodles, formerly Hon’s, is our ‘go to restaurant’ for Chinese comfort food. I grew up in Vancouver and went to Hon’s on Main Street as a young girl. The food remains me of my family enjoying a meal at Hon’s. The wonton soup and food is the same! Excellent food for the foodies who desire local Chinese cuisine. We ordered the hot pot with scallops, egg tofu and scallops and the beef and rice noodles. We drive to New West from Vancouver every couple of weeks. We buy the frozen dim sum for our lunches. The food is classic local Vancouver Chinese chains.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIxyakGM6JCJ6hy_I3L-1vaTNSMfn5jKPZq8Kh&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Sandy Y. (CameraGourmet)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQ9J8ig1HwUQBJbXRdKDIwR0OrTw3YtQtyHDEaRuCN8XnUDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We finally tried Han Lin Noodle House (formerly Hon’s Wun-Tun House) after hearing so much buzz, and let me tell you – it did not disappoint! 🍜✨

This is the spot if you’re looking for cheap eats and comforting Chinese food.  The vibe?  Simple, casual, and welcoming – perfect for locals.  Whether dining in through the front door or grabbing takeout from the side, the servers here treat you like family.  👨‍👩‍👦‍👦

Han Lin brings back all our nostalgic feelings — it’s like stepping back to when we first arrived in Canada.  Han Lin's got you covered if you love supporting local gems and want authentic, no-frills food.

📝📝

Food:  🍜🍜🍜🍜 Should Try!
Service:  👩‍🍳👩‍🍳👩‍🍳
Kids:  👶👶👶👶 Yay!  Like most Chinese-American restaurants, they give out fortune cookies.
Price: 💲$10-$20 per person
Presentation:  📷
Parking:  🚗 parking at the back of the building is limited, but there is free street parking in the neighbourhood.  The parking entrance is on 6th Street.
Tips:
📝 Prepare to wait - always line up for tables.
📝 Can feel claustrophobia with limited spacing between tables.
Would I Return:  Yes 🙋‍♀️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMr89PhazVTUBCWVkhciHQfmuiAHLXa5sXjkMk3&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Julie Soriano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJN2Kfv8XrjdGgvYA9G1yG3kdW0V7hMAPTw3q7h1y1pWaH98A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Flavorful food, impeccable service, and reasonable prices. Highly recommended for foodies and those seeking great service! 👌😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEnTILqlquQtFroghP8O4mkX170Jj-kKSn5nIs&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"B W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJp85P5JohieEKJOfTMzyjH1aTNit_eIhBL3dFVyxf0xS2BxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Han Lin Noodle House used to be the old Hon's in New Westminster. This is our "go to" for beef brisket dishes in soup or with rice. Their cut of beef is very flavourfully stewed and tender. They have also kept their potstickers which comes in chicken, beef, pork or vegetable.

The restaurant is not overly large and seating can be tight. Service is very fast and the food arrives relatively quick. Nice place to stop, eat and go.

Updated:
The Missus and I stopped by for a Saturday night dinner of Hot & Sour Soup, Sweet & Sour Boneless Pork and Beef & Broccoli. The long time staff kept all the diners happy with their excellent service. Highly recommend for a quick bite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2ljKj1hWhsO5tUO33TI8ItD9aMA6YBacvNqtu&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-2-15"},{"Name":"Ryan Cheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQl1j9sZTOT0V9bUqpH9in_0GIVVfG0l3j5RhhcMAIo39qi9zA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very kind and active waitress and delicious foods. What I tried were good, but I think can make it better…

As an Asian, I think those food quality are on average. But if you’re the one not always having Asian food, you will feel satisfied with that.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOX3gmUepyF_rGk-ult35p90qyLswV3ntn6wEk&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"Rafael Prato","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmw8x9RDf8apa9mg4sXkmCUBL57rpPrrUqVoRoTSqzlDDkuKry=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Han Lin Noodle House in New Westminster is a cozy spot perfect for a comforting meal. Their Wonton Noodle Soup is a standout—packed with flavorful broth, tender wontons, and perfectly cooked noodles, it’s the ideal dish for a chilly day. The Beef Gyozas are another must-try, with a crispy exterior and juicy, flavorful filling that makes them the perfect side.

The friendly service and relaxed atmosphere make it a great place to enjoy a casual, delicious meal. If you're in the area and craving authentic wonton soup and tasty gyozas, Han Lin Noodle House is a top pick!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtJmSf_P0ncLp_iUBjOVsmnrRr0ZUprp0Rzon7&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Ray Chow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnHoKzUHN2laU2bSp7bGdZulx8wlTrl7fcyIV2n_GmA8fi001AHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly staff and the food was pretty good here definitely authentic Cantonese food I will come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMREF-XjQjjVM-5ornqWC-o8QZ5bkNGHVVZGR3S&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Andre Xado","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4pF2kcxQctE24BGb5mTVOt8Vw7IK0bjuvwABeQ4ZahtlItYM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I have been coming here since it was Hons over 20 years ago or more.  There has been almost no change in the sense that same staff are working and they have become even more friendly. They kept a similar Menu so you can still enjoy Hons like food.  Food is great and the place is quite tight for space.  But its one of our favourite spots","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dhyris Cajes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWskpm_OO-giIgqAc5jWYooTUEYE673RiDJ0L-9DErINh7Fz6M=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited their newly opened place in Burnaby, and it's incredibly Instagram-worthy. I love the fresh color palette they've chosen for the place. And let's not forget about their food. Though we didn't have time to try many dishes, the pancit guisado and scramble are absolute must-tries. They bring back childhood memories from birthday parties and afternoon snacks. It's the perfect combination! I highly recommend this food haven as a must-visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOl5TBjg8hgPobMnhe1hgZVPit2ZVQtwjbLNb6o&fid=0x0:0x8ad16c1a88c7963b"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Star Lord","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXe8up1pfq5QyFHn2RPK5fUHNc6GvdzvGD0ChUElvkdvzAbgm2W=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First time trying this filipino restaurant, location is alright, lots of available parking around the area.
The food selection is decent and taste awesome, they also have the street food type of snacks that most filipinos crave for like kwek kwek, halo-halo and iscramble, one of my favorite is the bbq isaw. The restaurant is not that big, it might be a bit crowded for  20 people inside.I think its a must try food, I will be back to try the other dishes and post my second review.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBVcOZx31is9rbBEZpv8QszVhvcJBJzJBDL2JP&fid=0x0:0x8ad16c1a88c7963b"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Edgar Ignacio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7oexz4qXoBKr6ujKuYxwMvlf16ckv-ovFMKFmC4nzUqeMSoelFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their bopis is highly recommended and was very tasty that is why I bought another one for takeout. Prices are competitive and affordable for smaller orders like budget meals for under $10. They also offer Filipino street foods are also present and are freshly cooked when you order. I highly recommend them if you have cravings for pinoy foods. Cone check them out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBdtqx50isPfE-INvYuBJQC6gFv43nTaGN8N7X&fid=0x0:0x8ad16c1a88c7963b"],"When":"2023-8-13"},{"Name":"Patty Lawa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyJ57zaddManS-BKaF-6lD-R2YkZkW8O9B-vtES-NEKTLDRgU-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I was excited when I saw this Filipino Food Court Stall in New Westminster. They have ready to serve food options they also have Silog meals. I ordered tapsilog and I won’t say it’s bad but it could definitely be better. The rice that they are using has a bit of an after taste like it’s not the good kind :( the beef serving is pretty small for the price of $14 i think… they can make it worth the price somehow by adding a bit more to it. It took a little while for them to also serve the one order of Tapsilog my husband already finished his food before I could even start. But still happy to see a Filipino place I hope they can improve better so we can support them again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGPsDUanGBGdya11HA2wayZ6S95iUCBuWAkRjU&fid=0x0:0x8ad16c1a88c7963b"],"When":"2023-10-23"},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Considering that this is just food court food, this is phenomenal! Their garlic rice is top notch, and their meat has just the right amount of seasoning. Their beef jerky is a little bit dry, but overall tastes great! This is some very solid Filipino food that I highly recommend :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjJTMwlW22fxGmj4VKUg4ShYZubI13lU3VvX-p&fid=0x0:0x8ad16c1a88c7963b"],"When":"2023-5-9"},{"Name":"Jsh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvEGVU-NT42eeWcLNvzuM8t1sDRYlUZOwxuqB1E92xc27QT0zyeA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The service is really nice and the food is really delicious!
(I had the crispy kare-kare)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvD188ikg4eJb_d5RcbWSc2rvvmaQmh-Sapa0b&fid=0x0:0x8ad16c1a88c7963b"],"When":"2024-11-27"},{"Name":"Bob Celles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIj1-nWzxKx7nCSQg8YjTThODESj_RZuF8OZxxLJGkGXHqzvsd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"There were days, the foods were good but lately there were some inconsistency in tastes. I ordered laing and fried galunggong with rice, which they categorized as combo 2. The rice texture was a mix of soft and hard grains. It tasted  like they mixed the left over ones with the newly cooked. The laing was blant in taste and a disappointment, the galunggong was served with vinegar but even the sauce was somewhat plain for the taste. If the management wants to hold of their regular customers, and wants them coming back,  the taste of the food shouldn’t be compromised . Their prices are a bit high and the diners should get their money’s worth with good food tastes. Also, they should refrain from upselling other food products since the customers can view them anyway. If they want to buy desserts or other snacks, they will do so even without the hard sell. As a Filipino we wanted to patronize the businesses of our co- Filipinos but when we feel shortchanged with the service we will be avoiding coming back again buying their goods. Hopefully, I was able to air my constructive criticisms with regards on how they can improve their service to their paying customers. I am just stating a fact based on my experience.

This is in response to your statement that nobody is perfect which I found very unwelcoming of customers complaints. If you feel slighted on an honest opinion from your regular customer then no one will dare point out a constructive feedback. It looks like you’re just open to good criticism even in reality not every paying customer is satisfied by the foods they eat. Sorry if you feel the negative side of a positive feedback. Good luck!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Evangeline Perez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHsk7XmNVDj_WGLb_K-QU6GomYcUCna3BBUZrVzvQWYV0iBy4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"we ordered and overpaid for fish balls, kikiam, siomai, and isaw. The isaw stinks and has the unsavoury after taste - it was obviously not cleaned and cooked properly. They tried masking the stench with their sugary sauce. The siomai tasted like it just came out of a box. The food were all lukewarm - quite unsanitary. Spend your hard earned money elsewhere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9M288FDWN2HsYcmukxI7i8l9NG-FgmoFGFr7r&fid=0x0:0x8ad16c1a88c7963b"],"When":"2023-5-28"}]

[{"Name":"Ryan Cheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQl1j9sZTOT0V9bUqpH9in_0GIVVfG0l3j5RhhcMAIo39qi9zA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I am so curious why there are so difficult to find a good Katsu don in Vancouver right now… as I remember 10-15yrs ago there are so many Japanese restaurants selling delicious Katsu don…

Anyway the Katsu don from Ki sushi is pretty awful. It’s dry and those pork cutlets is hard like stack of paper. I know this is hash but I am telling the truth… please don’t try. I am pretty disappointed.

The Alaska roll tastes okay. Wish they can put little more mayonnaise in it. Now just taste like a California roll.

Overall the price is the best part ($22), just need to make a right choice… hope I have more luck next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCJPiSCryR3qKP41HYTnwPgunDaUvDwfxodE1c&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Sushi is ok.. Don’t hate it.. not a high end restaurant.. need a good cleaning. Very musty, Like there was a water link. Service is ok.. it’s seems to me like a fast food restaurant.. get you in get you out..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3NUC42UqZloaI3kHW262rtfGrr02DtG7BTH7t&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Jason P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwQ6VrAafrL568UtVUXBwRugwDfBdgtXm5PLgDAxdMUbNAFin6DA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The restaurant had good value bento lunch specials. But I decided to order from the regular menu since I was craving ramen. I ordered a spicy ramen. The order took more than 30 mins to arrive. I wasn’t too happy since I had to go back to work and was tight for time. I had to check a couple of times and each time the server said the order was coming. When I finished my meal, it was the manager that came and apologized. They gave me a 20% discount for the delay. Informed me that the server should’ve mentioned that the ramen will take longer compared to the other items served for lunch.

The ramen was good and I would come back here to try the lunch specials. The manager made up for the initial lousy server communication but I will come back here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPB-aVejcHwrAcLjii0fzVB0Tke_Cnxqui1Y8hk&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Tina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAKiC5J1ql1LsLTTfBwgvAj6sVGUusHXghumDKVG9ZTQ8QjcD_1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I want to love this place for the pricing (because you hardly see prices like this anymore in greater Vancouver), but unfortunately the sushi ingredients are just not fresh enough to justify a perfect score.

I got the combo A and the dynamite roll was soggy, the cali rolls tasted off.

That being said I will probably go back:
The ladies working there are very nice and friendly, and I wonder if trying a different menu item would change my mind.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUyrerlnxJVFQTp11onhHn6FeM3zoT0L37Owbq&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-3-5"},{"Name":"ana paula Khaddour","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJy2bnzWtsAkraPu7zbqcbnCHBpNiC67r33GIm0VobWn64-ODk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrified.
Terrible service, rude waitresses  and worst of all...disgusting food.
Ordered a beef yaki udon that was just noodles on a very salty sauce with FAT, not meat (see picture of all the meat i had to throw out, wont even give to the dogs).
Many other better jap estaurants in new west.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-UMfbKGk5wRQkTL-O8v-W_I5Sd2Smu38KxJ0f&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Manizha A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC2amaTPsYhEEr9awVR6ZxKWDqTPxYLLvu7b9SO5vvAOcniJoJSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We called before and made a reservation for a group of seven before we came, and the staff was very friendly and helpful. The waiter was not overbearing and only came over when needed.
The Ingredients were very fresh, and the everything was delicious, we all had different dishes and everyone loved their food. I would definitely recommend the veggie spring rolls and their pink rolls. We also had the peach growers, the drinks menu isn't very big, there's only 5-6 drink options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuF4K4SKWRPX2cGJsmfRw9jxGnB5EmRG5lC73t&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2023-7-16"},{"Name":"Jason Karman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEeWYgeWBPccpmH96g24c0GxKxN_YHOGKvLq55UVRy7jibnTY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Among the many dishes we had, the salmon fried rice stood out. The food here was satisfying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbl2YlIkpJLHzqf8u8QCwyxIANI4cPPb60CJo&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ki-nda dry…

During my youngling years, used to come here with friends when it was a Chinese restaurant. Then came a couple of times when the Neptune group took over and turned it into this Japanese restaurant.

It’s located right across the street from the New West skytrain station. There are a handful of free parking spaces available on its private parking lot, otherwise it’s paid street parking or the parkade.

Inside is a pretty basic layout with booth seats by the window, tables to the middle and the sushi bar to the inner corner. Very casual setting.

Here were the food I ordered;

1. Miso soup (Complimentary). Nice and hot the way I like it, thank you!
2. Tako wasabi. Fresh and pretty good, probably one of the best price so far for this dish compared to other places.
3. Kani sunomono. First, it was too sweet (added too much sugar), secondly the amount of crab meat was almost a joke (come on guys, the prepackaged low quality crab meat is cheap), lastly  the crab meat was dry! (Hint: There’s a new supplier has better and whole crab meat chunks, better and same price!)
4. Soft shell crab. Decent size, lightly battered and seasoned just the way it should!
5. Oyster motoyaki. It was okay but I would like it more if they were made from fresh oysters on a shell.
6. Sakura roll. Looked very promising like a blossom in the menu but in reality just another basic roll with no hint of Sakura whatsoever. (It’s called a Sakura roll, add some pink or red to it!!!)
7. Red tuna, albacore toro, salmon, chopped scallops, tamago, ikura nigiris. The toro was missing that butteriness, the chopped scallops and tamago were okay, ikura was so so, the salmon and red tuna were dry.
8. Assorted sashimi. I honestly am shocked on how every piece of the sashimis could be so dry and tasteless. It literally seems like the chef dab dry every single piece of sashimi with bounty paper towels.

The services here were quite accommodating and friendly, at least during my visit here.

As for the food, I remember it used to be decently okay, maybe different chefs?! It was somewhat disappointing during this visit; some of the ingredients were off, the sashimis and nigiris were quite dry. This is a prime location for any restaurant in New West and offers great potentials if it offers their customers quality food and service, unfortunately it fell quite short this time around.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6WO-HJmQ5Qfmhe-gCmZvyKSA1O_y9fMDvWGgj&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-3-29"}]

Had a meeting in the area and went in for a quick bite.  Tried the lamb, it was cooked pretty well.  Upgraded to a combo for $4.50 more rather than buying steamed rice for $1.50.  They obviously know what they are doing as the dishes look amazing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAp30aw9SudUB0V6T0ThO-uQzVCw0OCdefaM5Y&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Luke Weng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn1tdfwXfRnZVszKV8bZBNwooyRqfHv0VT8T0EAQWyUrqTrrO6aQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am very impressed with the staff at bubble world. Especially the lady with the short hair (I think her named started with an A)

We came as a group of 20 on Sept 21, near closing hour after Gospel Night, an event at anvil center. Personally, I was just going to get a drink and leave since I wasn't feeling well. But the group was too big and the orders took a long time.

All the while, this staff was extremely patient with us, and wasn't angry at all, eveb though some people in our group weren't being the most respectful. It took 30 minutes to get everyone's order, and it was already last call.

By the time they were closing up, we were paying our bill. Some people in our group were taking a group photo, and our waitress offered to take one for us.

Bubble World is always my favorite Taiwanese restaurant because it was one of the first ones in greater Vancouver. I'm glad that the quality of both food and service has not changed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcxyFQ1w2izaz0eVZkQmEz4FUNvW_WGngLKCfi&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Jeff Feng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWD04N7yAqK5bQW4CKDPzu-YbWI12ot70TbAi4lhM4-9KR2NVFH-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food here has no right to be this good. It’s a bubble tea place that delivers better food than restaurants dedicated to Taiwanese cuisine. It’s worth a sit down and dine. Highly recommend the Taiwanese Chicken here, the personal hot pot is also well presented and flavourful. Bubble tea is up to standard with gourmet places without the price tag. Suitable for dining with non Asian friends too! 😇","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfh6AvR9MRQCQMVc0O80yKe9W1al7N0_zyqpoo&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-5-24"},{"Name":"Eryne Donahue","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVP5EtXFYuZkNIyjSvTY2rCMnbXCoJa2XoQkt0Ilhovj4ony8ts=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was so pleasantly surprised by this place. Not a lot of vegetarian options, but what they do have is definitely worth a try. We had the deep fried tofu which comes with a siracha-type sauce and kimchi, the fried king oyster mushrooms- very high value as a big flavourful crispy bowlful, and the vegetarian noodles which had so great little nuggets of flavour and texture. Their bubble tea menu is extensive with many more options than other local shops- high quality and far less expensive. Make the trip there with a group: it is spacious and accessible!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOptsGPkkbvXzDUYkNFNQoFAGo36hKbvp5fLLV&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"Jay R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKagpkay_tyMiZJ290grAjrZOpOEgY41rzeVSw6eYBfxe4VIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a positive experience at this location, the beef soup was a nice comfort food, simple and tasty broth. Overall a good experience, the one waitress was super friendly, attentive and went above and beyond with her service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPStwfCYlYfiJMRMDuez5aJ3qf7Jj9wDqz_TOnn&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Danny Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eoyUE6az-FmQo7i2mVq5z64Ow48sgKu1EmLZc0zWWN6DMy5asw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"3.5 stars for the food. The food feels like a touch above food court quality and lacks something. The fried chicken lacks a freshness and plumpness, and the broth of the beef noodle soup lacks a bit of richness.

This particular location always seems empty.

The servers seem friendly and manage large groups well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwgdqAaVJYxbMZBwZvzLULDzrMLrrGuY7RS63c&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-2-27"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The seating and restaurant environment itself is very clean and comfy. The food is good but my baked pork chop over fried rice with red sauce barely had tomato sauce on it such that the ratio was off and you are mainly eating the dry fried rice (which had good flavour but could have used a lot more tomato sauce). The milk seafood hot pot was good as well. Would be even better if you could cook your own raw lamb at the table yourself like real hotpot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcjsm4DmT7a--qkWDiT048V5Eu8rfGpskwD3Tq&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2023-6-19"},{"Name":"Hangout CAN (出走加拿大)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLsataZBHdbXdf5fvvtSixzA7_P_SmPgA4k4U2s2VVx5uk12E8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tried Bubble World last weekend. It is Brown Sugar Pearl Milk.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMac1dVa4NNXWLOtJRZZwZ-bdTSeANLHOzXsNbY&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2023-5-10"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Chloe P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIOd_k819TESfS_1UYIzyA7DvAbrwpJ3dshJgc2zLqPvpO9BA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Unlike any pizza I’ve ever tried, and I’m not sure if that’s good or not.

There’s very little sauce and the crust is bizarre. It’s almost like styrofoam - very airy without much substance to it and just kind of evaporates on your tongue.

The fusion slices were far superior to the classic slices. I found the tomato sauce much too sweet on the pepperoni or ham & pineapple. The slices with a garlic sauce base were much preferable.

They’re on 2G2G as well and you can snag 6 slices for ~$6, so if you’re on a budget the price can’t be beat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOat9t_lVjbxli5PED1CAlLSCat7nC24OAHyG0X&fid=0x0:0xbdad31142392064e"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Salina Tamang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKWZn4hN2MZE09XMYTMkhdlkJngWOWbm88VF-9BGXG0r27FXw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I Must say
Best pizza ever at BC .
I recently visited this amazing place and really enjoyed the cozy atmosphere. Their yummy meat pizza was a highlight, with fresh ingredients and a perfectly crispy base. I also recommend trying the BBQ chicken pizza—it has a delicious smoky flavor. Overall, it’s a great spot for a casual meal or takeout!
Highly recommended !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8eGbVf_0V3ZQhLlUN6CYLWT__JwnuhbFLCvNA&fid=0x0:0xbdad31142392064e"],"When":"2024-10-30"},{"Name":"Akashtan Thayalan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFIjc2JXsNgwhJCUJvqX8KupOSfHqcZLREF7owIC7-FHERfqU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Yummy Slice is hands down the best pizza spot in town! The crust is perfectly crispy, the toppings are always fresh, and the flavour combinations are amazing. Whether you’re in the mood for a classic margherita or something more adventurous, they’ve got it all. The staff is friendly and the service is fast, even during peak hours. Plus, their prices are super reasonable for the quality you get. If you’re a pizza lover, Yummy Slice is a must-try. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Celine Aubin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLT1S6Oz-6K4DYad4aDna9Btmg7664lyQqhzWyvE9b19E7lSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pizza is tasty when they get the order right. We order the gluten free crust every time and they only make it on the gluten free crust about half the time. We’ve had to go back to the store after delivery on multiple occasions to get the gluten free crust with no compensation.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsEN8LESXHdVUHALQ4S3DxVR2gfd5knlpOhRGZTjLzMJeMHtuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve ordered from this place twice now and both times the service and the quality of food was amazing. Manpreet went above and beyond to make sure my order was allergy friendly. Their gluten free crust is delicious. Highly recommend trying : Shahi paneer pizza","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoaBv1MIELfQHEgns3kPWWYvkgCzABPQb4zKkS&fid=0x0:0xbdad31142392064e"],"When":"2024-3-25"},{"Name":"Pawandeep kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKyFTkYA5Gn1e8feBrIImUz7BFCF55VoQ6I96hNgkxgpQ1XMg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visited the store yesterday around 11 pm girl working there was so nice and cute. we were four friends we all ordered different pizzas she served us so well. Great communication skills.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Harmandeep kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJfqltxoAw13wW_gQi2R3lSc2xQRY7keQqXGUHfjLEfcP1QRlc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":""I had such a great experience ordering pizza  on the night of October 8th , around  8 PM .I have to give special thanks to the wonderful female employee working during that time. She was so kind and welcoming, even though it was a late shift. Her smile and warm attitude made me feel valued as a customer. Not only was my pizza perfect—hot, fresh, and exactly as I ordered—but the service truly stood out because of her. It’s not often you come across someone so dedicated, especially during those late hours. Thank you for making my night better!"","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Munroop Maan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLifpQRFEIh0Yt9cm8cdukLuxsCpodOg799LagL90gyQTDqfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I hate this location so much. The Commercial location of Yummy Slice gave me such a good impression that I decided to give this place a few shots but new west keeps failing me. Maybe it’s because I order on Uber eats? The chicken and macaroni bites are disrespectfully bad, the pizza is only decent if you order a whole one fresh. Customer service is no good either. This place is not at the standard of their other locations at all.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Andrew Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK13LuhtbcQQQ1wDmBa9J0Vwn9ABCTfxSFuyxqkVS3IT67IVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amelia restaurant on 12th Street in New Westminster offers an exceptional breakfast experience that combines great value with friendly service. The menu features a variety of hearty options, from fluffy pancakes to savory omelets, all made with fresh ingredients that elevate the meal. The portions are generous, ensuring that diners leave satisfied without breaking the bank. The staff is attentive and welcoming, creating a warm atmosphere that makes you feel right at home. Whether you're a local or just passing through, Amelia is a must-visit for anyone seeking a delightful start to their day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNKEjRXEuOKsGVqiSXdN-aPrRaezPFRonRpRrC&fid=0x0:0x96f31292f36a860a"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Honest Reviews","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8H803fKx1YqmW2UYOqm_SSmbFPJq9HKHS8Q8uYcbaiump3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here with a friend for breakfast and the food was good.  Portion size was okay and the price was reasonable.

Service was very good as the staff refilled my grinds coffee 3 times!!!

Other breakfast places slowly increase their price and decrease their portion size and forget what their business is suppose to be (example Jimmy”s Place Restaurant on North Road Coquitlam)

Will come back again 100%","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C Pérez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWILDNLHQbwQ4WYh0f_XaV2u7QTtA8bZ0QNemPRYV6F4iiNEtYnbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We visited this local restaurant this morning for the very first time.  The place is quaint and the ladies working there were nice.  I expected better food quality based on the price. The coffee and bread were below average.  My eggs were so, so.  The hashbrowns weren't good.  The building is old but it's to be expected as this area in New Westminster is like an old town.

Overall, the prices are high for the area and food quality.  Many locals do visit the restaurant and some are regulars.  The service is good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3TAgMTT3F7taGXC3MDtS7QQi5bwBNNkzpIriY&fid=0x0:0x96f31292f36a860a"],"When":"2023-10-14"},{"Name":"Trevor Jansen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8u7FBG6Utcjx4cKkz3RqodOcVGDgPNMzet5a4YlDeZVZGGbP8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A cozy Mom & Pop diner with lovely service and big windows for people-watching. Can’t go wrong with the eggs, bacon, and potatoes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRTZ3LtHtY53yQX2bHlz8_39pVYlfDokwucCVv&fid=0x0:0x96f31292f36a860a"],"When":"2024-11-26"},{"Name":"Ms. Fancy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBQaNfblq64oqWShq2FuM-_BC-1ScwkOJu_eYkfqvQy0DjNuPb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I thought I would give this restaurant a try as it is rated fairly well.
It is a good neighborhood place and the prices are adequate given what it is.
In regards to the food, the breakfast potatoes were bland tasting. Do you salt the water when cooking?
Scrambled eggs cooked through which is good, the toast was overcooked, dry and too much butter on top of dry so it just kind of pooled on the toast. The bacon was good and cooked well and I enjoyed my black coffee.
The atmosphere could use some cleaning, the entrance glass door and walls and sockets for eg. Other than that, everything else seemed clean.
The service was excellent and the owner seems lovely.

Ms Fancy

Super rich curry! So glad I came!!! The Butterica sample sauce to live for!!! Very bold well rounded flavors. Potato pea and chicken spinach begged to be savored. ... and I did! 👏👏👍👍💜 Dont miss out thinking food court cant be off the charts yummy!!! 💯🔥😜❤️🫶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSi_7AzhhQYdHqRVBnjd37mAGI1qqPQkGPn7Mt&fid=0x0:0xf5fc27bdb257303b"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Hugo Laci","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVh2bsCCLXWzhYcHv8w-UnkctyZRKXIL_T2cdWDgPQU9RfV95_jSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious Indian food at a reasonable / affordable price!
We had the Butterica chicken rice bowl and was great. About $30 all in for two. Highly recommended.

Returned to this small restaurant inside the River Market on 2024 and the quality is still as I remembered it. Delicious Indian food , cooked in well-balanced Indian spices","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUS09LqTurWIncGajYVx4uZbgZtVkUFo5EeR70&fid=0x0:0xf5fc27bdb257303b"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"JP Hernandez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqDSabFJQPH8ehPvxcKcRIyOrxnMxwg8bqFl10E7Zhv5zTsaDMow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ok folks, this is probably the best bang for your buck. I ordered Butterica Chicken - comes with Rice.

Good for two meals (or more). Really love the amount of rice that goes with the order! Would definitely come back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rachna Joshi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLMSFFXh4WG3ofUm4zYX0SIJx_nf45oQ_7d2nKNILETcWyLA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wasn't expecting too much from a food court restaurant, but wow, my punjabi socks were blown off! Ordered every type of parantha, salted lassi, mango lassi, chai and raita and could have wept tears of joy at the authentic flavours and exact right choice of achaar (pickles) and seasoning for everything. Paranthas were FULLY stuffed, I could have been India. I ordered nine more for take out, for a road trip to Calgary, and everything including dishes and utensils were packed to make that roadside pullout snack a breeze. Just go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODJ5-e2cDioy4qVIq2VBXeWbC-eZPCAR8qHdtt&fid=0x0:0xf5fc27bdb257303b"],"When":"2024-4-17"},{"Name":"Hillbillytc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV833YeKMKJfxtYeKhRHVRSrikZoFOcCapKBwyEFBOnxiCMeXAZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The restaurant is in a mall so not much atmosphere. The server was very friendly. The food was hot and tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOoPByffUTAIyTb2F3mtTq4_grTtVECpPHBh1Am&fid=0x0:0xf5fc27bdb257303b"],"When":"2024-11-1"},{"Name":"Hiroko Yanagimura","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1ErVT0xDb0oZqAI-75hYcVnk7s9u23JuKLz3ZbqcNlwwj3BL-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The rice bowl had lots of veggies and the garlic naan bread was freshly baked and so flavourful. What a great value for only $13.95!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNAMvVqmJIiBnTARkGx1nzSbldtnTgej5CZ_qWQ&fid=0x0:0xf5fc27bdb257303b"],"When":"2023-12-3"},{"Name":"Anastasiia Zarusskaia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrx31gqopgxkED-a0ipWozlatV20DUOFoCtzzOJvQO1dVGmtjW=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very delicious butter chicken curry + mango lassi! Paid about $14 for a turkey cranberry sandwich, a delicious ham soup and a cold can if cream soda. Every bite was scrumptious. Will be back next time I'm in the area. A fantastic spot for food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbZtnQg01rMeTzio6bwWOy2oAysacdhJ9-xZOs&fid=0x0:0x91f78abf96cd4075"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Erica Evans","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-LioakTfgmZaxuGVgvelBVTuI24TSHJ7lLBCeaGfQOoizFRB6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a staff event and had Columbia Street Sandwich cater. They delivered to our event and set up for us. The food was delicious! Lots of variety and so well put together. The amazing food was the highlight of the party ! So fresh and tasty!! 10/10 recommend !!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipML0u_eQ7lb_By5KDf2I5VVDgaWq-bDWnUucUx4&fid=0x0:0x91f78abf96cd4075"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Marley Mckenzie cook","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5n4XAwgV26WrtDQFOwKexjEHrP8ok0rq2RztGWysEOnM29r4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time checking out Columbia street sandwich  shop. I've literally passed by this place for years and thought it was a fish and chips shop and was very happy to see it was a sandwich shop! I definitely recommend this shop to anyone looking for good eats!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1AKYYcu9LCnKjxrkbc1yl-JToHS7wcoxm6rc&fid=0x0:0x91f78abf96cd4075"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Josho Kamoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ4n3iaFjoQyR1zucz1_1m7k51NtiBqRfCJcIPe2noft0FdsQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good sandwich shop right off Columbia !

We will definitely be using them again for our next event! Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rebecca Harvey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7bAaL9XJKXSMHKbWbjlFNwMaIzZxf0fS7FEtOfQX6gIFmbSpvng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best breakfast/lunch sandwiches. This small business is a treasure that I've enjoyed for the past 9 years ❤️","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ashraf Elhassan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuLkzBLPu9ua4RE40nOlcxoyN63gwKQwJa-XbekTX0jza_GlQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It started to rain while we are ordering
A very nice staff started to install a tent to cover their valued customers.
Thank you for your care and thank you for the amazing breakfast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIjByoq6RBAsrcIlRkzI8ltVydLAccN5zG2nuI&fid=0x0:0x91f78abf96cd4075"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Barb H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocITq1DWvJoN4Ge4RUxmHr_xI9FqqtuqrZfRAG967oKKGTEA8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have had Columbia Street Sandwich Company cater a wedding shower & baby shower for me and the food has been excellent both times. [{"Name":"Allen Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXuVE_WE8vewNrNDTzO1x5qptZqWw9u99U1EDdTLUCUHh7t0ohoQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good Malaysian food with nice service. Price is standard. It's fairly good Malaysian food in the New Westminster area.
We arrived at about 5:30pm and it wasn't busy but as the dinner hour approached, the restaurant filled up for a Tuesday evening. My favourite pick of the night was the Nasi Goreng. The rice was perfect! I could've eaten it all night! The taste kept me returning for more. There wasn't a lot of ingredients (shrimp or other meats). That's my only 'complaint' about the dish.
Regarding the Papaya salad, I've had tastier ones but this isn't bad. There's spicy sauce at the bottom - so good!
I wasn't a huge fan of the laksa but that's because I have authentic laksa at my god-parent's home.
I'm not sure where the best parking is located but there's paid parking on the streets. I parked in the mall (it wasn't a good idea). The mall closes at 5:30pm so you might have challenges getting back to the car after dinner. We walked through the parking lot because we parked at the other side. If you park in the lot closer to the restaurant, that would be easier getting back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuMjbe2CP7fpqSjuYxGaX-hM5JFPQD6VNdEQHm&fid=0x0:0xe55d562737a0834f"],"When":"2017-11-25"},{"Name":"Cheryl Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKRqwGsiyntapcBOAHD9FtzNPiBoZCzUhMf_hjWst1Da_zYAf8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This restaurant is one of my favourite for lunch. We have been going there for years. The owner Louis is a very attentive & awesome person. The lunch menu is extensive which has almost everything of a typical favourite Singapore & Malaysia dishes. They are good for dinner too. We usually have Roti Canai, it is spot on when served with their curry. One of our favourite is Hainanese Chicken Rice, Singapore style Laksa, Singapore style Hokkien Mee ( they serve it with chicken instead of pork), it is slightly wet & not too dry. They have other item such as Char Kuay Teow etc.
No disappointments in any dishes. They also have one in North Vancouver alone Lonsdale. This one is close to us, hence our favourite go to place. Decor is lovely with a subtle lighting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQ9CreBkyl-NTVz0dhQqSdRgddVydL_JcBOYC5&fid=0x0:0xe55d562737a0834f"],"When":"2018-11-23"},{"Name":"April C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqRH6DdBq3fgsPaN7Q6lty536z44SYXfEjq_wW5vBJRHpR4c8Suw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Eggplant dish was the best. Would highly recommend that dish. However the Hainan chicken didn't have much of the "Hainan flavor" it is still good but not the best I've tasted.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyH48nMysL-eBbuShdf9dwBJWeAWvV1EE5iUnM&fid=0x0:0xe55d562737a0834f"],"When":"2020-8-23"},{"Name":"Francesca Flores","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqFaunME8eO-WTATDIi7j8aUrmEsiM36P0yCe7j-y7U1Adiq3KVg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So delicious! Happy they are back and open for business. A good variety of Malaysian, Singaporean and Indonesian dishes! Their special clams in sambal sauce was amazing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaAy4o27QTwIsBQ8Jt3Grv6g8sBeAwA6-SrVbD&fid=0x0:0xe55d562737a0834f"],"When":"2022-4-9"},{"Name":"Ember N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAOVVSRZSBJ6e5O5jUUtiBAq23q-FcEx-8tVq1hmthlfDRNYcfgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food was ok but service was really really bad. We had a party reserved and they served the people around us first when we ordered 1st. =(
I will try to come here again and try it 1 more time. for now it's a -3stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDInebhKbzRTKmQTDxIQr-Jyt2t4JpLWLz4MBP&fid=0x0:0xe55d562737a0834f"],"When":"2020-1-31"},{"Name":"Sampson Low - eXp Realty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5-nAJ3Hfrda7C10R7DZFzGI9EIQe40LQVumTj4ikshD9ogtV4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Beautifully decorated restaurant with a nice and quiet ambience during off peak hours. Food is pretty much SG and Msia style. The Murtabak come as a surprise in the form as a wrap.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvncs9RumA7tUeGbZ2tGEtipbW_8o4cTflQFm8&fid=0x0:0xe55d562737a0834f"],"When":"2018-6-10"},{"Name":"Thisis monmon (Thisismonmon)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_hEAe1OlnYVjnjIXXU-MVPyInDlTOUwo4rXRuhgV4LENc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good service. Really enjoyed my meal.

I've been back 4 more times and changed my rating to 5 stars. The food and service is great everytime. If you like Malaysian food this place is perfect. I have a feeling its family run and they are delightful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8rD4DIKKFnJwSrC-Glkl1X9t3_mhrDPQ3AV8&fid=0x0:0xe55d562737a0834f"],"When":"2017-12-4"},{"Name":"gilbert villanueva","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6JNP6K4IJgsX4Zn9nNt1yPHqaCKSuviBZdJ8Wyd86x1RdO985=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best Malaysian food in town. We tried almost everything, but i definitely recommend the grilled snapper wrapped in banana leaf. Great service too.  Definitely would come back soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqu7clng3kNNbDABS49W37q7Wcc_HKoxGs1ugF&fid=0x0:0xe55d562737a0834f"],"When":"2018-4-11"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A reliable place for good casual eats. The burger I had was flavourful and done right and there was lots of fresh cheese shavings on my Caesar salad. They have an option with entrees for ayce fries and a side of coleslaw which is fun to nibble on while having drinks. Happy hour is after 8pm and the Bellini I had for $6.50 was nice and refreshing. The zucchini fries are also crispy and fun to eat but a little greasy and the oil could maybe be drained off after frying a bit longer. Standard good beef dip and club sandwiches too. Not gourmet, but casual food done well with good service in a cozy dining area suitable for families.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJ_8OdwRvT766Ly_UdDubLJq1NC-FjnUo2UilR&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-3-2"},{"Name":"Amit Patel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQ4BWWOt-MFNnYLuIrS2NwWeJ6KyjNkjkl1nXIyIhTmr_T7w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I enjoy my visits to White Spot weekly.  The entire staff is very professional and outgoing.  Big shout out to Jai, Max & V, always going that extra mile to take care of customers.  😊😊

After visiting yesterday, I would NEVER go back.  My complaint has been forwarded to head office.  This is Canada, Don't use dirty words in other languages or you will get the same treatment.  Owner needs to wipe that grin of his face.  I have spent roughly 800.00 including tips in past six weeks.

Issue is with cleanliness and not having ANY coasters for beverages which cause water to drip everywhere, even on your clothes, food and table.  This makes bacteria multiple at a fast pace.  When I asked the Owner, his reply was very arrogant and told me to keep wiping using the one tissue supplied.  Manager decided to use foul language in Punjabi.  The entire issue escalated because the Owner started to bully me and I won't stand for that BS.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhDTLXuTUfELwU2k2VHnp92RlTz6sS4lEeSK6R&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Bonnie Robbins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIB9HUSWvOCF6XxK9oUaKKvSi1myInWDR_8c48I-FNInV8HGg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a great spot! My husband and I are from out of town and wanted a place to have lunch while in New West for the day.
We chose White Spot as we have always found them a good choice. I have food allergies and they are very good about making sure my meal meets my needs. It is nice to find a place when traveling that allows me to feel comfortable ordering.
The atmosphere is great and all the staff were friendly and helpful. When the meal came my husband and I were both very pleased with our meal. I am almost sorry our travels don’t take us to New West to enjoy this restaurant experience more often.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gerald Knott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXz1E7AZgefW8YShOxZvEa82KyKhmBd-cihkjnTEdZmj69vuY_v=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I’ve tried avoiding writing this review; because the staff seem nice enough, but EVERY time we order from here there is some mistake.

One of my kids likes pasta but hates pasta sauce and we use to order online but they would mess up the modifications 60% of the time. After leaving a phone message the manager (I think it was the manager) asked me to call orders in b/c the online system wasn’t clear. So I did going forward. The error rate went down to maybe 40% on that dish.

The problem is when you order take out and find mistakes when you are home, you can’t be bothered turning back.  I’ve gotten better at checking but they are finding new ways to mess up.

Last week they called me to tell me they were out of mashed potatoes, so I needed to pick a different side for the steak meal. Then they proceeded not to bother packing it.

Today again they messed up the pasta order, but caught it. So they re-made it.. cool,  but then the rest of the food was cold. Then they gave me steamed veggies is a plastic bag?? And the cherry on top..  one of the two kids ice creams I received was essentially empty.. it may not have ever been ice cream?  it may have been ice cream mixed with whipped cream?  honestly idk what it was but it was basically empty. The top and sides had stuff on them so it wasn’t obvious till it was opened.

So while it’s further for me..  I’ll just start going to the kingsway location b/c this one..  they just don’t seem to want my business.

The food generally is good, when it’s packed right or not cold b/c I had to have them remake something. The staff is always really nice, but that means very little when my take out order is wrong.. over and over.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6OCtva7z2Fg2y1q2HcabH1BKcHTAIdocdYEbD&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Esther W.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZ44_CjQ6-wehLPc33Ng17kPOWOSFrXqo3jg5WgP7CtwNUYUeR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Restaurant was really quiet. Price of the food seems high for the value. Fries soaked in oil and soggy. Food otherwise ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPq9xjQ1cAJ3TyKevqQRCA1ETEg57vcRuWYPVIb&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"When you go to White Spot, you know you’re going to get decent casual food. We split the farro salad and shrimp sandwich and both meals were good. My husband enjoyed the blueberry milkshake, and as always, I got the iced tea. The washrooms were humid and dark, two words I’ve never used for a washroom. There was no hook in my stall to hang my purse or jacket, but I could see the drill holes where it used to be.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPeJXcToAS5yFbdhRbnN0EIPe5UaUlSYw1-1iX0&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"Louiza Valderama","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX45vT1nMCSVypsdgSruQCt3dbZF3_b_NVMsVJBCsFAyWcoPypT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered the chicken strips and salad via UberEats in this location. Found a finger nail in one of the chicken strips🤢 This is really disgusting. Happy to hand this nail over to its rightful owner.

Someone claim your lost finger nail 🤮🤮","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYuzU42LlVe8IVltb3Dgxva4o4XZVF0O2_pYtu&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Astha Ray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_VHp9yBas6tZ1mKdg_70eaJ5sdLRxyHvPSoXUZhJopvEGV6fv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Food was too bland, though service was good!

Might be something to do with the location, because whitespot Kitsilano’s food definitely taste better than what we had here!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPmrkrlkakCEmWeU5XXSDBvJqwDqYkKinRIPPY&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-9-10"}]

[{"Name":"lyla won","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdqECsZHiDTrplL2HX0YPo8YA6hf4tYpourdVXWs7awJzWv6kb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I treat myself to this place once a month! Atmosphere is clean, staff are VERY welcoming and friendly, and food is AMAZING! My love for Filipino food has completely grown because of this restaurant.
Tip: ask them for the hot dish of the day and they will recommend some dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM43oCfkd8t_EpjWIVe6WaOgpAmJH6I-b5_XgBc&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Celina Arenillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPvcNqjpmtihcb5J8miFlC4lw0H-EdaSQUtLM4u3kh0_GMHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"How I wish Plato Filipino can elevate the presentation. I ordered lomi, paid $10, and it was placed in a plastic take away. They could have used a simple, ceramic bowl for this. Quite sad to see how they serve Filipino food - cheap.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsO6tBGxXmq4r5VMHqGgG1LriRYK5w8iFbda-v&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Jessica Aranas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUG8N5f3Wd4GKt8zT_qaGsKHP4OREkobtyE2Xefb2cmdEv-KSHu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We’re so excited because we aren’t usually buying food from Filipino restaurants. We ordered crispy pata, ginataang kalabasa, monggo, and leche flan. I liked the crispy pata and ginataang kalabasa, the leche flan is so-so ( I can make leche flan so much better than what they’re selling), and unfortunately the servers are not honest about the monggo, me and my husband know they don’t have enough, I even asked if they still have some for us and she said yes, but they just added like sinigang soup on it to fill our order (the monggo is so sour), you can see on the picture that the monggo looks like a soup. We’re never coming back to this restaurant, this is really disappointing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOD6_BZby1LWBSy35BJdAYnBQHPBdh-hKXtvVsf&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Jordana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJvxqFr8nGL8vok-SCRwxhp2_EJmOiFDFc3qAUH70xw1rrHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good Filipino food with a good variety of options. We came on Sunday at 10am and the viands were freshly cooked and ready.  The BBQ in the BBQ silog was lean, the Turon was crispy and not greasy despite being fried, and the lechon kawali was very tender. The place was clean compared to other Filipino restos in the area and theres quite a bit of space. Highly recommended if you are looking for home cooked Filipino food at a decent price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNU6wDqBDyLMxGeY2u2S0CTKNVZpIJFbQNQHGxj&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cafeteria style ordering wherein you can see all the dishes from you. Very authentic Filipino food with lots of Filipinos customers dropping by and working behind the counter. Price was a bit high for the small portion of food we got. We ordered the adobo, crispy pata, laing and extra rice. The crispy pata came with the lean meat and the fatty part. Total came out to be around $30 but portions were relatively small.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVtTM2GlyX9FNUdpGYHVi8eLTpj8kEuL8yOjpZ&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2023-5-7"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The ladies were nice to explain some of the dishes but I wish there were labels on them. Each dish seem to be scooped differently with the pork sisig being the most abundant, to mediocre sized beef caldereta and very stingy on the sinigang. Not sure why.

The rice was very generous but it was also overcooked and soggy. The sisig isnt fresh and they have to microwave it for you so the crispy pork rinds are no longer crispy. The beef caldereta was delicious though. In my opinion, sinigang is quite easy and cheap to make and it would be nice to have it as a side soup that comes with every combo.

The parking lot nearby is paid so you'll have to park further away.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvRqw2sDYBIUHGze-pd2mD3Tl1zg23g8_ILKge&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-3-26"},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A very nice spot to get some fantastic food right before watching  a movie at Landmark! They've got some great portion sizes, and a very decent variety of Fillipino dishes. I highly recommend all of their sisig dishes, I especially liked their garlic rice :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6vtfrLmaa2D4v9P-88cM4nvG7t5ZZiB_MBIRb&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-5-1"},{"Name":"Krissa guevarra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUibiGsetoxfVc6X9kI_bjXVaRHGBVtnySbE2ZkNsK1RJ22uugu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Me and my family went here twice already. My husband loves the food here. He rarely craves for filipino food and this place satisfied his cravings. It’s so nice that you can get dinuguan, bopis, sisig and crispy pata for a smaller amount and can upsize for a bigger one. Place is nice and clean. Would definitely recommend this place to anyone.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOu6fzs7jj6zsTZk63U7-vIadbbezTetXwNXhqp&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2022-11-7"}]

[{"Name":"Cat King","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs0w4Gi6wbbwHozHIMXCxGOYXWgHMRV7NGZtPTmRmCUIubsOlj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I've gotten catering done by Big Star Sandwich twice now and I've gotten compliments on the sandwiches. Sandwiches are on the pricey side for sure. However, the quality is there. We've always gotten bunch of turkey, roast beef, and pulled pork sandwiches. (#21, 25, 27) We think roast beef and pulled pork sandwiches are better than the turkey ones. Forgot what number is what.  Somehow, the turkey ones taste good enough, but they were drier than other ones. The sandwiches actually taste pretty good even the next day after you put them in their air fryer for like three minutes. I think their bread is really awesome. Even if you are a big eater, two of these sandwiches will probably get you full. They're professional and the sandwiches are always made and prepared to be picked up on time. Probably will get more sandwiches done by these guys if I have another party.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_DLjmzbxLGAV2Bejcm58EFWR16vW_TMEYUZ3L&fid=0x0:0xaa52eb13fd2c04be"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Alli L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK7M-K_wMLVOHyWDXpjXXk3pyMIn-Cv8yGLpMXYPKQoyxLDNQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered a sandwich from Big Star on Doordash today. I paid a total of $23.00 for 1 small sandwich & the delivery fee. When I grabbed it to take a bite, the bottom of the bread was soaking wet, and the whole sandwich was a soggy mess. The bread wasn’t wet from the sauce, it actually felt as though somebody must have accidentally spilled water on it. The vegetables on the sandwich were mushy and not crisp or fresh at all. And lastly, I asked for the store to please add extra cheese to my sandwich, and I did not receive extra cheese.

If you’re going to charge people a ridiculously high price for 1 sandwich, the least you could do is make sure it is actually of quality…. Very poor experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUTIXEz2WloPJHKsY-lBYCoP8lSfLgih2RyGuV&fid=0x0:0xaa52eb13fd2c04be"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Laine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMUfuiKNWfIVTADojs-9fWgIpssQGI4GKv83Vg4wwNeLBsXQSk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Number 17 Beef Dip sandwich was SO delicious! It came with gravy on the side for dipping. Service was quick and friendly! Perfect place to grab a sandwich to go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkRpW-I0gtEKzGz9deJelPZ6izmahsjHBlYLqw&fid=0x0:0xaa52eb13fd2c04be"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Nick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGjptqH3FdoeLfdSjPWQygL5KEsM_ui4pClg77BekGUD0E-Q_8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I'm not going to be cruel while writing this because these guys did the best they could, but I really don't get what the hype is all about. Feels like people in New Westminster groups have never traveled outside of this city ever and tried anything else. I keep falling for the hype over and over again thinking maybe this time they might just be right and maybe this time it would be different.
I'll give you the only positive experience of eating here first - the young lady at the counter taking the order was very jolly and helpful. I own a business so I know how hard it is to find a good employee.
Moving on to the food - It's no secret that the bread is the foundation of any great sandwich, and in this case, it felt somewhat stale and lacked any sort of flavour. The beef was rather unseasoned and didn't have any savory flavor, a more seasoned and marinated meat option could significantly improve the taste. Even the sauces lacked flavor.

Do not fall for the hype, this is a really expensive sandwich shop which is not even close to being good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuWkbPzUq4SbOrefiRmOINWlARpVEbxtLOiLs0&fid=0x0:0xaa52eb13fd2c04be"],"When":"2023-10-16"},{"Name":"Madison G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtZsEld-Yz5a2Swm5LesjF83lo03ZXPGgujeQvQiLn6WLaIuGx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for lunch with my dad and it was so delicious. I’m a pretty picky eater but I managed to find something I liked. I had #21 and I believe my dad had #20? Both were soooo delicious. They were pretty efficient in making them and the prices are a bit more expensive then subway. The sauce and portion is perfect on the sandwich. Is it presentable. No. But the overall taste is amazing and the hickory sticks really made it! Would definitely come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXzUScyyw8hKh3blWBsVgALsvcBN6UE1YvRFvc&fid=0x0:0xaa52eb13fd2c04be"],"When":"2022-11-24"},{"Name":"Zineb Abou el falah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHyg-obkzj0DGMieCL8rSWDieZldd--V1N8yaCu3AKJcdktlQqSg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The sandwiches from Bigstar were far from fresh; in fact, they were stale. After consuming half of them, we experienced immediate diarrhea. This is highly irresponsible, particularly when we rely on Uber to deliver fresh food. My husband and I were already unwell, and now we're dealing with additional side effects from the food we ordered. In the picture, the sandwiches look great, but I wished they tasted as great and fresh as they appeared. Shame on you, Bigstar, for the price you charge for the sandwiches and the disappointing quality we received.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9aerZq0NMcEKq9hbpb9d29C4D2S-E3FwyK8TK&fid=0x0:0xaa52eb13fd2c04be"],"When":"2023-9-4"},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A dope lil sub shop joint! This place is awesome for vegans and vegetarians, plenty of legitimate protein options, packed in a hearty sub served with great flavor. I hauled the Veggie Turkey and Cranberry Sub which was pretty yummy and good value for money.
Awesome, would return again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbHTjo9Gxq3vFfjpe234xosjZeYL1uxNF_P4nx&fid=0x0:0xaa52eb13fd2c04be"],"When":"2024-3-9"},{"Name":"Samantha Nash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT_3WhwP0zFqqSmA1bQauQLqH79OWNW9HQvH3UH-Zrb5R9UimFRA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have used Big Star's catering service a couple of times now for my team at work, and it is always a hit! Sometimes with larger orders places will skimp on fillings but not with Big Star. We love the sandwiches and variety offered, and the customer service that comes along with it is amazing! Frida and the team are great! Definitely recommend!","Images":null,"When":""}]
