I tried so many pizzas in vancouver and surrey but Papa dave’s pizza is number One .I could  taste all the flavours out of it ….it was so fresh and the best thing was the customer service that we received we never felt we came for first time . The owner was so kind and sweet….gonna keep visiting this place .loved it .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSlQlduOw6eaW-Ve1on_QuN2G2IoY44m9lH9OT&fid=0x0:0xa01716310f064a0"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Mridul Mehta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmm0IQmbS5H7Jg1wEqSruPUZhb2VZVS0eSmjZZ7qAo3MIaTKM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5 stars! Absolutely amazing experience at Papa Dave’s ! From the moment we walked in, we were greeted with a warm and welcoming atmosphere. The pizza was hands down some of the best I’ve ever had - perfectly crispy crust, flavorful sauce, and high-quality toppings. It’s clear they use fresh ingredients. The staff were super friendly and went above and beyond to ensure we had a great dining experience. I also appreciated the quick service, despite how busy they were. This place is a gem, and I can’t wait to come back for more delicious pizza. Highly recommend to anyone looking for top-notch pizza in a cozy setting!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlrlFH4VpTKO9jlVbJnP0ZE1OpayIabbRwhfcQ&fid=0x0:0xa01716310f064a0"],"When":"2024-3-30"},{"Name":"Marissa Mar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3R1PjY9e2Xy92U5PIoq9X_hF8ImauaEEe8_6ewp2hX56YAw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's the second year in a row that we've used Papa Dave's for a large gathering. Each year they have gone above and beyond for us - even going to the extent of adjusting their service hours, accommodating gluten-free/vegan cheese needs, and thoughtfully labelling each individual pizza. The pizzas speak for themselves - our friends liked the pizza so much they took the brochures! Papa Dave's is a real family-owned, community institution that delivers true value. An enormous thank you to the amazing and gracious Papa Dave's daughter and the whole team. We are so grateful for you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPw1OyaX_1GIf0-XwvdTuE1nLYDjCnnFq98qhXo&fid=0x0:0xa01716310f064a0"],"When":"2024-6-24"},{"Name":"Steffi C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8COqw00bMCOoCithIbf6q0z0D0HQEN-W3WyguF94VjEwh6UA_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Papa Daves makes amazing pizza! They have deals throughout the week and I was able to pick up their Monday special. The pizza tastes so fresh and is packed with flavour because they use high-quality ingredients. Their service was very attentive and you can tell that a lot of heart is put into the business. I had the pleasure of talking to the late owner’s daughter and she was really nice! The pizzas smelled so good on the drive back and they did not disappoint. Even though I live in Richmond, I’ll definitely be back to have their pizza again 😋🍕","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBewePM7lpBb59dyfmBywnnKbHo5V-R84uA6Jr&fid=0x0:0xa01716310f064a0"],"When":"2024-1-9"},{"Name":"Farid Baradaran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHZFxXs8sujUAsgNNrAf6-ZW1pPPs34QK8jDoet5Rtg6wWNj4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down, the best pizza I've had in a long time! I ordered the Beef Lovers Pizza and it was absolute perfection. Crust, sauce, cheese, and generous toppings - everything was just right. 5 stars isn't enough!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dave Munday","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXaNS1DZd97spwQGogwfE06SDoDiGtYHmZ-fIsxivv-iLxnAtq3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In this local market, there are a couple places that charge about double the actual value of what you receive without any hint of being better than ANY of the competitors.
(looking at you...[45-70 minute wait times] Mr.Ed)

PLUS TAKE NOTE OF THIS....
Papa D's HAS A FAST PREP TIME!!

Yes guys make a CONSISTENTLY dependable pizza-- nice crust, not burnt, and good flavour.. for a fair price (especially by comparison to that old 'Ed' son of a gun).

Also... if you request a double portion of cheese (or anything else for that matter,) they aren't at all skimpy when they fulfill your request.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great presentation of food and good portion for the price. We ordered several different dishes including chicken souvlaki,  beef souvlaki, roast lamb, Greek salad, and calamari. Each main dish came with Greek salad, a potato, and pita bread. Everything was very flavourful. One disappointing aspect with the roast lamb. The piece was very small and it had some sort of sauce poured over it. Another complaint was that there was too much raw red onion in the Greek salad. Overall, it was a good meal with plenty of table space on a Friday evening at 7 pm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPg6S_uJMOdoTa23Y-oIwtTty8eEnq2rTdxyBTE&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Carmen Aboytes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCCLFKJlS62-34BUpujZzDsaZV9yysTxPBmk8fhCY7OoETeMyS6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It’s a decent Greek restaurant, but nothing stands out as exceptional. The service was fine, and the flavors were average, nothing memorable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWMH-wkXxvz2Up20rQmHhNvp-vKgXFKkPhgTAd&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"NDS Investments","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVikPs6WOuTzc-E92-sZ1BLaCA6XPNBLrLbmLXnMK-Mmkbrg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Rating is for Pizza delivered  only, did not dine in/pickup

Ordered a large Gino's Special.
all ingredients appeared to be fresh, the pizza tastes great

Reduced 1 star based on:
When the pizza arrived, the box did not have a sticker seal on it...ensuring that no one open and tampers with the food...something to consider

Pizza also arrived very soggy, we put it in the toast oven for a few minutes before enjoying","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVuu3TeUW4EPKWNaqMSXsydJ-pyB3C2qy1P918&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"B W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJp85P5JohieEKJOfTMzyjH1aTNit_eIhBL3dFVyxf0xS2BxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The Missus and I had passed Gino's many times over the years and now have visited 3 times.

We have found the food to be above average for the price paid. The Missus really enjoyed her roast lamb on the Thursday night special while I liked the baked lasagne. However, we found the service to be very inconsistent. On the third visit, we had the best service. On the first visit, we felt rushed and the server never asked us for drinks or dessert. Then on the second visit, the server neglected our pizza order (even though the restaurant was not busy) while we had finished our other dishes. We had the pizza as a take away.

As with other reviewers, we also did have a few pesky fruit flies as our dinner guests.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvbpt8jKp8GmSg_wnr05II8EYgKKb8p3LWh7hJ&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2023-12-10"},{"Name":"Joseph Denunzio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXx9p6AEcNVuDztxesE59-KiwxsfDC3721FfKjwJrbNsmUuaphs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I heard good things from a friend but wasn't expecting dawn of the dead. I wasn't impressed, no love in the food despite the expedited service.. Staff weren't really fun or friendly which is Vancouver standard (chatting at the bar the whole time). Its a great place if you're a boomer and just waiting to pass the time until you venture on into the afterlife. I would recommend the bar just down the street instead. Much more lively.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I tried the roast lamb and calamari here. The roast lamb was very tender and had great flavor. The calamari had a nice texture and was plenty seasoned. Both plates were a good portion size. Prices were very reasonable and service was good. The restaurant had a nice local community vibe. I would definitely come back to try out other menu options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXA0O7J-Gex3oD_PW8CjyY324YoWyrZ_JV1j59&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2023-3-4"},{"Name":"Adrian Torino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI9dSAfw-7UTYYunGGifd3UMcpQDU3BkyOZ5dXVAmXbL6fxVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice time here last night. Enjoyed the food very much and the servers were really friendly.

We had the kalamari as well as the scallops and bacon appetizer. Both were great. Kalamari had a nice crunchy batter and soft squid. Scallop was very tender.

Had the roast lamb dinner and can't really go wrong with this item. Fall-off-the-bone lamb that's also still very juicy and packed with flavor. Their tzatziki sauce is great too along with the pita bread.

Nice time here overall and would come back in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvJCQNsvvKlem9bfwa9VyAj8ax1BFvMLZddQnp&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2022-5-19"},{"Name":"Lisa EmBee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDNJ3jcRSoM-kPGXAPwTDqF66ZFDdapFUABmX6L3GoRCiLnw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I always look forward to a meal at Gino's and anyone I recommend it to  has been happy they went. They have dine in and drink specials almost every day of the week and makes it easier on the wallet!  The food is consistently good. Always fresh, good quality and tasty. My favorite is the baked lasagna but if you like thicker crust pizza with lots of toppings you won't go wrong. Atmosphere is low key and on the plain side but clean and comfortable and always room available. Service is fast and always super friendly.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJu7qs7wWZ8h14oY158Bcan-2zVcMlG9fgSmqP_Wf5wVO4c10Evg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We both had the smoked salmon eggs Benny and they were perfect! The service is super helpful and friendly too. I definitely will come back as it’s on the way to my physiotherapist and I love brunch. If you enjoy good food and brunch food (I’m sure the rest of the menu is as good), definitely come here!
As a treat we also had peppermint hot chocolate. So good!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5aqiw0eB-Z2CjPiDbHcVFU5f1nDUC1SoEDCPb&fid=0x0:0x3a588f79e270b662"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"Kathryn Roberts","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwUCQew_OZoHuagjXFIOHaArFg1ZLQmSWyNQVQJxwytQ7fWimr=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food beautiful plating!
The pancakes are light and fluffy,
the small potatoes (hash browns)
are a nice change. The brioche French toast topped with mascarpone delightful.
The eggs benny, gets a thumbs up.
It is a bit pricey for the New Westminster crowd  but definitely worth every penny.Once you have tried it you’ll want to go back again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTL9gm3iQBeeEKAYeYdV-EV8GO3u4TXMiyDHBt&fid=0x0:0x3a588f79e270b662"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Chelsea Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXfGclplc9AHR_eqqhWoYd-014DKC0E1v16d-38NOYjI6FbBLQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The staff was incredibly friendly - our waitress was friendly and frequently checked up on us. We were slightly disappointed in the food. The chicken and waffles was not as expected - it was served with thin chicken tenders coated in the sauce of your choice. The pork benedict could use more hollandaise sauce on it. The kids pasta was done with macaroni.. Might have been better with spaghetti. However, I can see this place being a good place for friends to catch up at with a couple of drinks. Maybe their burgers are better? The vibes were nice and cozy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkUJ_n2XuqKPUV7g8d1VsjgkkINKlwKZuPQOGq&fid=0x0:0x3a588f79e270b662"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"CLY","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKrxaj6z3gWVbRX-86hRrQED63tUStZHe5T7RlvjDSQSijE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here - great food and services! I brought my dog so we sat at the patio. It was cold and raining but the restaurant manager and staff constantly checked if we were doing okay. Will come again when the weather is warmer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZoAcnH-ad1g0NaCLUQ6fHmn-nmnYm2kZph2I&fid=0x0:0x3a588f79e270b662"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"Jessa Turner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVT4JG0AWsbk6dMMlx-eBDbDOEaG8t6vAGvyndKupteLf8DS3q6Ww=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We’ve been here a couple of times and have enjoyed it. Today we visited and noticed a different menu with higher prices, fair, considering the cost of everything nowadays in the industry.

My food came with cold sunnyside up eggs and I asked for new hot ones, which were brought. About 1/2 way through I noticed this red piece under lettuce and initially assumed it was a pepper. Upon quick investigation realized it was a piece of silicone and the waitress confirmed it was indeed a piece of their tongs.

Never will visit again especially after also reading the health inspector reports from earlier this year.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOP-Afy6xwJu3Le7pszghY3sx4uS8L3guDa_VYB&fid=0x0:0x3a588f79e270b662"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"dan james lapera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGhriroFFwmYTbM38ylhk7T3Z-GZT-r-rgqucROQ3J4j5NEw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went here with my girl and with our friends, got entertained and got seated right away. Service was excellent, took our orders in and got our food quickly and the vibe was really awesome.

Will definitely comeback here again, would recommend the tater tots(bussin). Friendly staff, food prices were great, food tastes way on top of the roof, and food quality is 1000%.

Credits to the Chef(Jude), the kitchen staff, and servers for making our day ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrWMsBRFjQuoAiXQgsVxkejMWqqrhr6b6H09O9&fid=0x0:0x3a588f79e270b662"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"PARAM SINGH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJTCskfoTZffCwVuI2yICPYAST3KP4yL9ONCnLrjKtoZTGt83I=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved it! Good food, Amazing service and staff was super friendly. It was nice meeting with the new manager HINA. Thank You for accommodating our dog on your patio.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4xEYZLcmgRzoFFeTvedYauXmgXZwbY8w4Kg2O&fid=0x0:0x3a588f79e270b662"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"Toni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGjLo4s5ggV7jm1MJkKLe78L3gWsd5EvXMWiC_B-1D73uvO24=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Had the breakfast wrap but I got it with vegetarian sausage instead of regular (as they didn’t have nearly as many vegetarian options as I saw online). Pretty sure they gave me vegan egg even though I explicitly asked not for vegan egg. The only decent thing on plate was the potatoes. The ratio of egg to sausage was so off. (See picture). The salad tasted rotten. The menu stated that the dish comes with “fruits” both my boyfriend and I received a singular piece of pineapple as our “fruits”. Waiter didn’t check on us once so I didn’t have an opportunity to complain. They brought the bill out without us asking which made us feel a bit rushed. Not coming back this is the most disappointing brunch I have ever had…

Also saw a review mentioning to read their fraser health inspection. Went ahead and did that, shocked to say the least…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkJhkB51Ic9HFf95hKJbi-HB8Y1ov8xrbb5kKz&fid=0x0:0x3a588f79e270b662"],"When":"2024-11-16"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! Everything tasted absolutely delicious! Super satisfying North American Chinese Takeout. In fact, this is one of the best stereotypical Chinese foods I have ever had. Imagine a cartoon where they order Chinese takeout and you imagine how perfect it could taste and look and this is exactly it! That’s the best way I can describe it. Each dish tasted exactly like how I imagined it should taste.

The deep fried chicken wings with garlic were crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside with a hint of Chinese wine marinade which tasted fantastic. The deep fried tofu had the perfect soft chewy texture amongst lots of stir fried veggies including cauliflower, broccoli, zucchini, mushrooms, cabbage, carrots, and onions. The honey garlic spareribs were the perfect blend of sweet and savoury. The chow mein had lots of chicken and veggie bits and embodied everything chow mein should be. Totally hits the spot for North American Chinese food and would definitely order it again. The portions were generous too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPC7_gdZfR1Hx8DMyI20YwjE5MzohSP0vJgYkZj&fid=0x0:0x5c433c48d412ce49"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"J J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUP-GnClnyFGKZIC-e5xuUz_tNBB5fGAJbOBNCdRcYO2l_ndwV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The eggplant and kungpow chicken are horrible, the worst I’ve ever had. Eggplant is tasteless literally just oil flavor. Kungpow chicken is not even kungpow chicken, who puts celery and mushrooms in it? And why is there no flavor at all? Both are suppose to be spicy but none are. So disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCzOnmDQma-tAuephfoXfNI0YuWYgxGe0NNwfK&fid=0x0:0x5c433c48d412ce49"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"The JOKER","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQuiHl5446ZqSIBmhoQY8q4NuTHDo0F4Qr2KVa1APrDHGiVv22=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food here is very good. I didn't particularly like the ginger beef dish though as it doesn't taste like ginger beef. The small pieces of beef (???) were covered in batter and tastes more like  sweet n sour meat which I dislike. I think they gave me honey garlic pork instead.  If this was ginger beef then every restaurant has their own version of ginger beef but this one was not the traditional type.
The chow mein and beef pan fried rice noodle were really good. The squid had a spicy taste to it too which was a good touch. Overall, 4 outta 5.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4gY1lX1MFc8TGQ4-tcvUjUn80S0zmgnn4UI_7&fid=0x0:0x5c433c48d412ce49"],"When":"2022-5-21"},{"Name":"Darcy Miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI71fcxxUfiUCwlsILyc4nAAOKfsbLZBJvWflDMP7qqXkWeYg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"DO NOT EAT HERE unless you like to have food poisoning.
I ordered last night.. wonton soup, bbq rice, lemon chicken and wontons. $70 worth of food literally down the toilet 5 hours later.
Place should be shut down","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ryan Greenlees","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVH0j0zHsuy6S8tiKyo5qdYoZ-cmLI7-TqJyAD5PyDuUvxveWWx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A calm, affordable place to get great chinese food! We will definitely be back again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlLSeETPbfKatkPdgJ2m0zHgOc5chwP0WB8FM8&fid=0x0:0x5c433c48d412ce49"],"When":"2023-4-24"},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"谢谢 Xièxiè!

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Tai C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxzHUmtVbeOMH22fzU9hQouYcREwNZ603mUbLvjMqsYVkzOVqX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Decent fish and chips chain. Prices are fair. Portions are decent. Definitely a go to place if you want a quick bite for this simple pub dish.

For those non-native to BC, I definitely recommend trying the salmon fish for a new unique flavour and taste!

Lastly, parking is a bit difficult to find, especially during weekends. Washroom is also a single stall so be prepared to wait for your turn during peak hours.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgh6NaJzVXvSFdyGlPmjgbWlpAXtUav29mwlXK&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"M L'Esperance","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZqUBTP-65WyvMXDylpShFuRceNg0tDp5M3yyClpT9KjBeCmg4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious melt in your mouth halibut with perfect batter, the chips were still hot on the plate when served, and the kitchen split our 2 piece halibut and chips order for us at no extra charge. Service was really excellent, our server was friendly and our food didn’t take long to get to our table. The coleslaw tasted fresh and creamy and lacked the sour aftertaste that sometimes accompanies that dish.
Good drink specials and food specials throughout the week as you can see. Sleeve of lager for $5 was perfect with my food. For the quality of the food, all in all very reasonable prices.
Plenty of free parking in the shopping centre. Street parking around the corner is not free during the day.
We went here on the recommendation of some friends and it definitely made up for a lacklustre fish and chips dinner we recently had elsewhere. My only small quibble was the pieces of halibut could have maybe been slightly bigger.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMF5JSNvTXWVqZzdctpbXJhjIqanzppUwbsTWO7&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Angel Armamento","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFUTSsVNLgcbZDJ1ia4JVguSAjmcTqulnR0CbJwaLy1YjbMvo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For the value, I'd say we got our money's worth. The fish were cooked right and was well seasoned. The batter was light and fluffy. Halibut was a little overcooked, but still tender. Tartar sauce is served bottomless on the table, not too fancy. Calamari was a hit with the Greek like seasoning, and tender.
Fish tacos were good too, but can use more seasoning or sauce.

The kids meals were generous in their fish portions. Mine seemed to pick it over the chicken tenders, which only came with two pieces compared to the 5 or so smaller fish.

Overall, it was a good experience for the family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBjwJUJc7i_0qVe7fclNmyvel8uid_oIywVFg-&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Chris Mesman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ08hw55SeJHYsXvdPVfCXPxGNK_Xy_jIb2hnDUnOfnCvrcNw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We've eaten at a lot of fish & chip places over the years, and by far Cockney Kings has the most tastiest seafood.  The halibut we ordered for our most recent take out order was tender & delicious.  We were also impressed with the portion size for the fish & chips.  Prices are reasonable as well.  Wait time was also reasonable considering that the place was very busy.  Staff are very friendly and efficient.  We definitely recommend this place for both take out and dine-in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Pua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQE67YcmODoXcmMTFKf4Q3qoazClSzG0lMsbeDc-pzuop1N5k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The service and the atmosphere is amazing! I honestly can’t believe it. We went there for the All you can eat fish and chips and thought the service wouldn’t be great and the place would loud but it felt like a family restaurant; The best part was the service. They were very friendly and nice, despite them being busy they try their best to attend to you as soon as they can. Lastly, the food was okay I find their fish to have quite a bit of batter instead of fish; I wonder if this is only for the All you can eat option but either way it is also quite oily mostly because of the thick batter; fries were great though and I love their condiments they have an amazing tar tar sauce and vinegar.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZuNzs7z5aJGkx_Wr5cHoQC4u3RaACW61-qdgn&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Penny Rusty Sophie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkGfXMIDqwS_yD1axTk6tkHoLsnybE2ErvKrHMoMIElMJWekI_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Cockney Kings has been a staple of Columbia Square mall for many years. My last visit here was all the way back in 2012. Had a quick look at my old food blog and, sure enough, the menu hasn't changed much since then (aside from the prices).

We ordered the combo platter where you can choose 2 different types of fish. We got the cod and snapper ($21.95) combo which came with chips, coleslaw, a dinner roll and butter. Then we added the 3pc prawns and 2 pc oysters (+$10.75). We also got their signature soup ($6.95).

I forgotten how thick the batter was on their shrimp. A bit too much for my liking.  The oyster batter was thinner. The soup has halibut, bacon, tiny clams, and veggies in a thickish chicken broth. The dinner roll is quite dry and cold but ok when dipped in the soup.

The fish and chips here is serviceable but mid-level at best. The fish was either cooked a bit too long or wasn't the freshest as parts were a bit dry. Fries were lightly crispy but some also seemed quite limp. I ordered a ginger ale and it came out super flat. I mentioned this to the waitress and she poured another glass which was pretty much the same. Must have been something wrong with their machine so they just gave me a can instead.

The place was actually fairly busy when we visited. Also noticed a strange odor inside. Not sure what it was (or if it was one of the other patrons).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEESlILNkbH-YM-uiKN2mbaSWqKmmhMjm8OKvq&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Christine Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInYD77OKR3wU6wHPNxepryYvr_lPkpT3c-4RO5yMIe-yR1iA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Go there to have a brunch with hubby on Tuesday.
There is AYCE from Monday to Wednesday, so we tried it.
Almost full house on that day. The service is good although they are very busy.
The fish is good. $17.95 AYCE with pop is a good deal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAZNBWi3OZzM0aIvInZDcNVL1b9ZEGcaCwMGjJ&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Their haddock fish & chips was excellent. I love the thin batter & fresh, chunky, firm pieces of fish inside. Fish & shrimp tacos were great too. Calamari was quite plain while their soup was kinda off for me, that combination of fish, clam, bacon, carrot, celery in 1 bowl. The volume of food was a nice surprise for the price. Our waitress was fantastic. Recommend this restaurant for those who want a somewhat simple, family-friendly dinner, you can't go wrong with their fish & chips.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEzjnJSQBkq8LmNy4lFDTdB_dLQoLshgWRqyq-&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2023-8-5"}]

[{"Name":"Sumire Ninomiya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUm-M5CCbH8omzg2hl1Ei1Uk1T7pnlAYQ5yqgkYgA6w3LfHZlT8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing spot for your new go-to brunch place in New West! Everything we tried at this restaurant did not disappoint, not only with its gorgeous presentation but also with the quality of its taste. The owner told us that the meat and salmon are slow-cooked for 4 hours, preserving their juiciness and tenderness. All the breads are freshly baked in the house every morning too! The store is not big, but it enhances a cozy and warm vibe of their overall atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDYRLoFn7AMscBsAcKRMKJF24sooGgfFf8vW0m&fid=0x0:0x230c373358ec5343"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Camille Estrada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU47AuX_xbBITEK1xwE4RKQXxGw7oOUhbF53grHoYbTK3vNt_I=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the pleasure of dining at Banette recently, and I can confidently say this gem is a must-visit in New Westminster!

Food:
The dishes were beautifully plated, and the portion sizes were generous. I ordered the Pulled Pork Bliss Brunch, and it was absolutely divine. The pulled pork was tender, well-seasoned, and perfectly balanced by a touch of sweetness from the pineapple. I enjoyed making an open sandwich with it, which was delicious, and the fresh berries on the side were a thoughtful and tasty touch—both visually appealing and a lovely contrast to the savory pork.
My friends ordered the Salmon Sunrise Benedict and the Atlantic Delight. Both dishes were outstanding. The salmon was perfectly moist and flaky, and the eggs were cooked just right, with that runny yolk that made for a rich, natural sauce. The Atlantic Delight, similar to the benedict, had a delightful combination of flavors, and the addition of bacon provided the perfect contrast to the salmon’s delicate texture.
All dishes came with soft brioche buns, which I would recommend toasting a little more for a crunchy texture—this would elevate the meal further, especially when paired with the tender meats and rich eggs.

Atmosphere:
The vibe at Banette is bright, warm, and inviting—perfect for a relaxing brunch. The bakery section by the window is a clever touch that draws you in and lets you gaze at the freshly baked goods. The space is cozy, which means it’s ideal for smaller groups (6 people or fewer), but it can get a bit tight with larger parties. Nonetheless, they’ve made excellent use of the space available. It’s a great spot for brunch with friends, family, or kids, and the perfect place to grab a coffee and pastry if you're looking for some peaceful alone time or a cute date spot.

Service:
Jenny, the owner, was incredibly sweet and welcoming. She went out of her way to make sure we had a wonderful experience. When one of my friends was waiting a little longer for his order, Jenny kindly offered a croissant on the house. It’s clear she values feedback and customer connection—especially since they just opened this month—and we really appreciated her warm, friendly service. Her smile truly added to the overall experience.

Overall:
We will definitely be returning to Banette! It's a fantastic spot to support local and enjoy great food, wonderful service, and a cozy atmosphere. Highly recommend this place to anyone in the area!

Let’s support local businesses! 😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPObAI-_09H2HqDU-neWby_KZA2Iojq8rCKktO&fid=0x0:0x230c373358ec5343"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"Jason York","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2KL5JJiTZL1QVt_3AcqILQXXBIuqDWdYOdj3lYENvavlAma6S8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"What a beautiful grand opening on Dec 14, 2024.

The pulled pork bliss brunch had a scrumptious mound of delicious pulled pork on a piece of ciabatta bread baked in house. The roasted pear was sweet and satisfying.  For $22.50 I only wish the portion size was a smidge larger.

Yes, the presentation is absolutely beautiful.

I look forward to trying the Supreme Stack, but at $32.99 for one burger, I'd have to be high (this will probably happen sooner than later).

I'm told the owner used to own Sushi Well next door and focuses on quality, quality, quality.   I wonder if there will be additional menu items or specials here and there 🤔

Overall, I'll be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOyE-76EMs0V9hACA4Jb6QTi2eyGfdNTrNTzci&fid=0x0:0x230c373358ec5343"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Susan Mihalic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL2N8sKlMs8zfjzRoPH_UIhyO3pwAMJ0QRFhAr8FlHvOt4etw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Visited Banette Brunch with my sister yesterday - and I am so glad we did! Brunch was delicious and looked so beautiful, like a work of art. The service from staff was terrific! It was wonderful to see Jenny - she is an amazingly kind person and we are fortunate to have her in our community. I was lucky enough to also pick up an array of delicious baked goods from Banette. I shared them with my coworkers at the office today and everyone agreed, so tasty and fresh!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMExC31sHcXwy7KhsDIovzZscMCm5s-KGKIkICc&fid=0x0:0x230c373358ec5343"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"louise henry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXWx7s6Ob-Www_YEe9E8D5ok_8T9OPzpa1Mr0qwxM1qxZJFg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best brunch spots I have ever tried. Super fresh ingredients, so tasty and a well thought out and balanced plate of food. Really generous portions and amazing staff. My new favorite spot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsDfBHa1MvXvRk-nC7FUuVDgVfxW9iydPJTy7g&fid=0x0:0x230c373358ec5343"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Sue L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWK1Xs45MxTbBAkDexDdc8tM6u5P21ibhQQKSUFoghgoR8a2bOV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So happy to see a new brunch place in New West. We had the golden roost benedict and beef royal burger. Both were delicious and very fresh tasting. I can tell a lot of care went into making the food. They only opened a week ago and are in soft opening phase so service was a little slow but they were fully seated and busy during weekend brunch. The vibe is cozy so we did not mind the wait. The owner came by to check on all the tables and she seemed very kind. They also have a small to-go bakery section. We bought a couple buns but did not try them yet as we were too full. Hope to visit again soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZGyUiSN-oSR-odIHM8LeZKHMAmThQwLH1JMAT&fid=0x0:0x230c373358ec5343"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"José Andrés Castañeda Bernot","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVicxFjuO-TQ_IxUXxZGqtH_zhpS4TSj1GD2u_8OTWYVVmpgYEX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place is new and I came in with my wife. The pastry was delicious and so was the French toast. It had avocado which was something new for me but it gave it a good twist. We loved it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCTzLK--CDGeD8faTB1M8RQNXZ30XgPBMCDjqv&fid=0x0:0x230c373358ec5343"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Carmen Aboytes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCCLFKJlS62-34BUpujZzDsaZV9yysTxPBmk8fhCY7OoETeMyS6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A delightful and cozy spot for breakfast or brunch! Highly recommend stopping by for a great start to your day!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNixC3kq8Vt-s3i7IjENQX-mkdmxzAK9F3HbZwO&fid=0x0:0x230c373358ec5343"],"When":"2024-12-19"}]

Thanks Tommy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxehPeVGCAt9nbZqBQAHUbExLbaYsW5HIchuRx&fid=0x0:0x741657c0c784f6b6"],"When":"2024-9-11"},{"Name":"Carmen Lo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTR-ikIBCe6evZ04WLR2qLmnyKRPcxeXUVrFAXND3VVi4va6bl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered a takeout vermicelli and some spring rolls. It was delicious. The owner is so friendly and had a great hospitality manner, he saw that I was dousing my spring rolls in sauces and offered me to try his fish sauce in the mix. Recommend getting a takeout here if you’re in the area!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kennard D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVybnWKFp-741ZDKCATwXv6Mb9FlyxlSFxKzyKVo6jTdm_H4DUa=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Simply an Authetic and Best Hidden Gem of Vietnamese Food. Was shocked when coming in, seeing how small but cozy and intimate it is.
The owner is such a kind and genuine guy who did all the cooking and serving by himself.
Even I did take-out. But the sping roll still crunchy. The packing is really eco-friendly and minimum of plastic. Food tatstes EXTREMELY HOMEADE, DELICOUS and ORGANIC ( ALL MADE FROM SCATCH).
First time and already impressed. Will come back for more since I am living in the neighbourhood. So glad I found a Vietnamese cuisine place near my house. Love it !!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmnpFUTlDymr1tMWmHsERXsrUs2y69USIQnK-F&fid=0x0:0x741657c0c784f6b6"],"When":"2022-5-17"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"WOW!!! HIDDEN GEM ALERT! Highly reccomend the Vietnamese food here! All made fresh to order and from scratch! You wait a bit but the food is amazing and not generic! The scoop:

Wonton Soup: they use Pho broth for the soup and the wontons are not generic and filled with baby shrimp and Chinese mushroom, very tasty

Lemongrass Chicken: Generous portion of flavorful chicken

Spring roll: meaty and well spiced. Unique tasting.

Noodles, fried egg, and salad: FRESH

Plus, it comes on a cute frog tray!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQPP_Oj313elbcd774zMfB6rCPLh54XCMsHz_v&fid=0x0:0x741657c0c784f6b6"],"When":"2021-6-9"},{"Name":"Henry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5IdIO2L2su5qRvfL88YEx69qYxNengft50bruqaE6VPGwv-I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is a hidden gem you have to try. I visited today and wow, the food was tasty, fresh and cheap! I ordered the Beef Pho, the beef was tender, the soup was rich and the noodles were nice and chewy.  It's kind of in a strange spot, you might miss it at first. It was bright and clean inside and you can really tell they put a lot of effort into opening this business. Just overall a friendly, tasty spot to eat good food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM96io1bSTNeeUQKFobIugxhzakEQ4fnXHTLeu2&fid=0x0:0x741657c0c784f6b6"],"When":"2020-8-18"},{"Name":"DA KTH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHktSST1wYzUPO9giZrzWDFkWebV4ep6nSFoBLTj4MhQJhGEfUyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Terrible place, definitely not homemade, and not authentic Vietnamese cuisine. I have bought the same mini spring rolls at Save-On-Foods nearby. The ancestors must cry every time the owner tells customers he makes everything from scratch.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVcqSv23wMKM_DWJZLRmPEUtwUrK1Ud0nDHDqRtYwGi2K6MQev2RA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the lemongrass chicken pho here a couple weeks ago and it was amazing!! The owner Tommy was super nice. Even the tea was flavourful. It's a quiet spot to eat. Will definitely be coming back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Danny C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIq1V3ELCQR8swrfHo6pQxjRvGbX3HPRr5R6K7UBKZwbvT3Vw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A true hole-in-the-wall spot that is special. Corner Cafe is a sanctuary escaping the frenzy of delivery services and disappointing franchises. The chicken is so unique and has the thinnest crispiest skin, but the juiciest meat underneath. It is funny that it is located in a medical building because the pho will heal you!...(or at least your hunger). You can taste the quality and difference in the broth compared to any other pho restaurant. The owner takes a lot of pride in what he does, and you're lucky if you get to experience this place.","Images":null,"When":""}]

I highly recommend this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOegX2krSph9osCE0dTYDN_yXfLH2Z8mdUXFXKt&fid=0x0:0x78411a88a9e10c56"],"When":"2024-3-8"},{"Name":"Hunter Moe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiOxfcmHg3ov1U7SsZnJbwcN8uqOUZu0sw1tzEQkrX1isKmw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good pizza with quality ingredients. No street parking, all permit parking based on what I saw.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRhU5Mgzz5ImtLxhC7Nait-zB6RwKZgD7Sy0Yt&fid=0x0:0x78411a88a9e10c56"],"When":"2024-6-28"},{"Name":"M Blades","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDpKQ5mJcitw8kCfImDZeBLX__thXm3-LVhxIKibbfOMEBfBI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I was so excited when I saw that Sapperton will be getting a Neapolitan style pizza restaurant and boy they didn’t disappoint! They opened pretty quickly and the atmosphere and staff are definitely welcoming. The pizza itself tastes really good! My 4 year old ate two slices! Can’t wait to have pizza evenings with my little ones there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgMkJUJIXZguvV9GVC_j3kcfmfJB27yTh85Itx&fid=0x0:0x78411a88a9e10c56"],"When":"2024-3-9"},{"Name":"Shannon Skilton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUItoNPbuaq80qYyQTKeH54aep5aXoERL-4chn5doIcHaWOF5OT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Walking by yesterday and decided to order a medium vegetarian pesto garlic pizza - #22 on menu. Pizza was DELICIOUS, FRESH and I loved the crust too. I will definitely order from them again! They cook in a brick fire roasted oven, and deliver direct too; so don't need to order through a third party and pay all the extra fees for delivery! Yes!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin Gordon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVr-ZJgY15PKPyqXvkmFiRQmvzfwvaxz4dzHtZxUjVctqvY1psXQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ordered a medium 2 meat pizza. The sauce and cheese are spot on but this pizza needed another few minutes in the oven!!! If this is the norm for this pizzeria, it will be my first and last purchase ever.
2 more minutes in the oven to crisp this pie
Sauce is tangy and delicious. Toppings are very good.
This pie needed more time in the oven.
It was delivered at 4pm so no excuse for undercooked pizza.
I was very hopeful this would be my “go to” pizza stop …
Good enough for another order?
I’m leaning towards maybe","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Alina Emery","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFFXXc2y2gjjUEfjvZr7gv44kQb-MPmzWUcV4nZl5nDLrvQSAXAQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Split the sushi boat with some sake and it was really delicious! We had to stop and grab something to eat quickly as we had a 5month old needing to eat too. The servers were super lovely and food came to us very quickly! Felt very homey and food was great. Only feedback is having a space to change diapers would be a 10/10 but loved everything else! Will be back soon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Makoto Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTTV198NAfai_RKRHly1LIX-gqZYSb8Sv-UnCFgLBSyAxhsz0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ikoi Sushi used to be our favorite sushi place, but unfortunately today is our last day here.

There is a new policy that is $15 minimum order per person. We completely get it.
After ordering food, we let the server knows we will order more later. But when the other server (older lady) brought us food she told us to pay for the complementary tea.
The way she told us was rude and unprofessional.
(She said "You only spent $12" "You have to pay for the tea!")

Also, we felt the food portion became smaller than before.

I'm not going to write everything down here but after all the miscommunication and server's behavior, we decided not to tip them this time.

When server saw we gave no tips, she said "NO TIPS?????"
"Was anything wrong??"

When we were going to speak about the bad experience, she interrupted and said "it's ok" and WALKED AWAY🤣
I wonder why she asked us if she is not going to listen to us.

We stood up and went outside of the restaurant, and she never says thank you.

We couldn't enjoy our meal at all because of the bad experience. WON'T be back again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMj1pXTISptBEWEn3NYWdCWanHbL4oXqnTHYBqo&fid=0x0:0xebc91fe3fe1ee168"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Uros Nikolic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqZKUGj61BfmTYu8vecdYC7cNoaJsQnfWJB3zipm50mUOPG3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This Japanese’s restaurant has a good variety of sushi choices on their menu. I ordered sushi rolls , and other things from menu and everything was very tasty and fresh.
Pricing is fair ,not too expensive and waitress was very polite so I’ll definitely come back.
All recommendations for this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMK5F8RgXraZhkqG9TOfycuu11buc0B-IPkBPnQ&fid=0x0:0xebc91fe3fe1ee168"],"When":"2024-4-4"},{"Name":"Djordje Kojic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBL6vcGYM0P3feyhqJkWM8uZeZP_Q7F0JmFh9MDsvKIRzJtg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small little place in a strip mall. Just went in for a quick meal. It doesn’t look like much, but the quality of the food was amazing. I was very pleasantly surprised. Way better quality then I expected going into the place. The nigiri was amazing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3IlHYlAdGeHSjUXE-4Lk7E1GAxsEcKpFJ1Oct&fid=0x0:0xebc91fe3fe1ee168"],"When":"2024-4-4"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"They have a good variety of sushi choices on their menu but I found their sushi rice lacked the usual plumpness, sweetness, and vinegar flavor other places have. The sushi was not bad, but overall, quite average. For the price you pay, I have had nicer and tastier sushi at the same price or cheaper. It still does the job of satisfying a sushi craving though. Like a standard neighborhood sushi place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeHpD8Qrbh2ezSqIV-f9pTI-p9eEIOTrM9pHxE&fid=0x0:0xebc91fe3fe1ee168"],"When":"2022-10-7"},{"Name":"Leona Zheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmB6XMzxTi6G9GEmyD0MJjB6nkqYOP7GVBTMUakDrRUolumXkH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Perhaps one of the best authentic Japanese meals we have had recently. You will find some unique and traditional Japanese dishes here that many Japanese restaurants will not carry nowadays: real tobiko, ikura, masago, anago, aji, etc. They were fresh and sweet. We ordered these in the form of temaki sushi. I couldn't believe that how generous that they put the tobiko, ikura on top! It was a real deal for me. The wasabi is made of the real one, not the mimic horseradish. The staffs were really friendly.
I understand the frustration that some of the other reviewers expressed - e.g. minimum charge of $15 per person. When you have kiddos it seems unreasonable. However, for two of us, we easy ate over $80 there (ate too much, now groaning), the $15/p seems not a difficult thing.
My favourite: tori karaage (fried Juicy boneless chicken), Tobiko nigiri sushi (flying fish roes), masago nigiri sushi (smelt fish roes), aji butterly fries, dragon rolls.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO50I8hjv88AxZ0A7I3a6Io1fcEeUCHlCM4aDAI&fid=0x0:0xebc91fe3fe1ee168"],"When":"2023-9-8"},{"Name":"Rebecca P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOtv1z9oQXsu_j8G9uE8jVQGZlbdGZfOgnrsP8gOev0iFfifM3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very delicious and fresh sushi! You can definitely taste the quality. The servers are very friendly. Overall great experience.

A very small place, recommend to book a reservation! I would definitely keep coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQWRLRvQuM5UOpudvP7FoQNFiUeBHB_C_5UEen&fid=0x0:0xebc91fe3fe1ee168"],"When":"2022-3-16"},{"Name":"Nathan Gock","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHkNE3wp0BHPmjWdgFbhh1J2W__TRTD91hRVxAd_Wa5elpxg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Japanese owned and operated sushi spot on New West. We really like the Uni Ikura Don, and the Aji Tataki was also delicious. All the nigiri we ordered were great as well. Service was also very nice!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6_YkXHdk-ZPsGzGLNfNZHYcId1y49nc3M0JBl&fid=0x0:0xebc91fe3fe1ee168"],"When":"2021-9-4"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Patrick Mathieson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINECmDvDDqotX_gLzijWsJWmEoQhBGS6vcf9OOMM2x3OTExg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went today after a doctor's appointment for some sushi here. The place was quite which is okay as it gives you a chance to look things over and not feel too rushed. I ordered two of the bacon avocado roll and they had a spicy California roll on two for 9.99 which is a awesome price. I also got some nigri as I got saba, squid and some eel. I also had a bc roll. Everything was very delicious and fresh tasting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmdfKlzLfEGAAD8lUR9tQMEEMjY45QTYuJce9k&fid=0x0:0xa4655268ea0d3909"],"When":"2024-6-11"},{"Name":"Tasha H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOEvGpfqoRWg4TT1Q7uFhaaKtDgixG75Hzd7qsRbbEaXcZ-fkohA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Good value, fast and welcoming service. The food looked nice, but the taste was not as balanced as expected. The spicy sauce used tastes more like ketchup than spice. It was applied so liberally, it overpowered all other flavours. If you want spicy, get tbe sauce on the side.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUt1ZudjV6LV9EFg7m1Xc1IXO-bsq6s_XrE7EaGSJdu-pH4ZgEFgQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Average food, great prices. Tempura was thickly breaded, rolls had a thicker layer of rice on the outside, and the spicy sauce is rather standard. I would come back but only when I want a cheaper bento option. Service was great and the waiter was very kind and attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNh5c3koDCmfM1qTNHSsoNssCXCtmrixRQpXMym&fid=0x0:0xa4655268ea0d3909"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Miles P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-Hpfcsh-5YUkphb7Gj8zjmyb-3jxrzSmAcEonVaY-w5hkDIdV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I enjoyed the chicken yakisoba. I'll give it a 5 star if there's more veges on it. Unfortunately I forgot my wallet when I'm about to pay and the waiter was flexible enough to accommodate transferring money via e transfer. Thank you so much, that saved me time and effort.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cyndy González","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUITBu2jPQwGoVtdpsgtFVx2DmbgGXb4-wGAQ-xtysuxbkH_mXy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Prawn tempura, miso soup and avocado roll were fine. I ordered a spicy tuna don buri as my main but did not like it. The spicy sauce to me tasted like that fake spice you find in instant noodle soups, but the consistency was lumpy, and the tuna itself did not taste fresh (threading texture). Took two bites and asked the server to please take it away. I order the avocado roll instead.

They still charged me for a dish I did not eat. I asked the waitress why that was and she just nervously laughed and started apologizing stating there was nothing she could do for me.

I am very disappointed.
It certainly feels like they just robbed me $18.50 dollars. Would not recommend and will not return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJgnCWwJPE2ZC2_mr3S4uvyEotmPehL20Vd-mk&fid=0x0:0xa4655268ea0d3909"],"When":"2023-1-26"},{"Name":"Minh Lu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-Ky9fV1KWLmdSBFYBS9eqC1jvAprMJD9aTS3IuRtQck4oZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Nice little place, unfortunately the sushi was average. [{"Name":"wooseok jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLho2ZGCxfXzD8GiWQxcNSfFQKjOnI4LxY-BNnmT00UxYr4mA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I often order from this place because my cat only eats the salmon from here, it must be that fresh!

I love sushi, and I would be happy if my cat asked for more salmon even more often.
The rolls and nigiri are incredibly delicious, and the owner and staff are always friendly, making it a place I visit regularly.

Highly recommended for both sushi lovers and their pets!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1mf8G6Z1YChtpJjD-2eiGJLELGnpo3ZbGEyc1&fid=0x0:0x91e30b5a8372ae47"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"YJ Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUf-IKSEtDyB9_CacExAL0Zh_kDpJkf1y7ohuhbEzyu4mi1Kcjd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an unforgettable experience at Woomi Sushi! This place is an absolute gem. Not only are the prices so reasonable, but the quality here far exceeds anything else I’ve tried in town.

Every piece of sushi is crafted with such care—the fish is incredibly fresh, and the rice is perfectly seasoned. Their rolls are exceptional, each bite bursting with layers of flavor, but the Avocado Oshi with a hint of truffle is truly on another level!

With generous portions, warm and attentive service, and an inviting atmosphere, Woomi Sushi has quickly become my new favorite spot. A must-visit for all sushi lovers!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1cPl5M1pfTyDrYsPjRebeT8T3epwIILrRPOb6&fid=0x0:0x91e30b5a8372ae47"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Anthony Plaxen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0TosyGAQWTqM_XvTHaXfq2jDGHv6ifKWBgTGcJKYnap3ceipL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Excellent quality and delicious tasting sushi rolls at Woomi in New Westminster. Located inside a mall, this place offers excellent high quality sushi rolls at very reasonable and affordable prices.

Ordered the Sunshine Roll and Red Dragon roll. The dragon roll was spot on, the sashimi was fresh and the sauce flavours were great. Everything tastes fresh. The sunshine roll was also very good. Big large pieces of salmon sashimi that was great.

I’ll definitely will be coming back to this spot, it’s certainly a hidden gem for a sushi spot. The place is takeout only but there are seats inside the mall.

4.5/5 stars","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBY6cVxuY9KnFqlK7EmMKB5M7Leg4X0oYmuHUp&fid=0x0:0x91e30b5a8372ae47"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Summer Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI0aGpnFXSQ6gH7mwJYTUZq5hNkCOynWn2tSmeYFOYAU4tN9g8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered chicken and beef bento box sets, and they were truly delicious with fresh ingredients!! 😋 The miso soup was good too, with just the right seasoning. Great quality for the price, and I think I'll be ordering from here often! Thank you for the great food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_RalYIEep6BDF3MTTmTtqgaJ12z7nVXFkYIDE&fid=0x0:0x91e30b5a8372ae47"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"hyunji kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYxvxT8oBRYjlqWW2cLJZxA5rIvMQ3gAF2V5YpLNuMTCcywG_j=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I thought it was a budget sushi place since it's take-out only, but to my surprise, it's an absolute gem! It's definitely not just a budget sushi place, but a true culinary delight! The chef used to work at Minami, and you can really taste the high quality.

Salmon Nigiri & Sashimi: The salmon is plump, and the portions are generous! The nigiri rice is incredibly tasty; it’s the best nigiri I've had recently.

Woomi Roll: It was my first time trying this combination, and it was delicious. It seems to be their signature roll.

Avocado Oshi : Typically, budget sushi places don’t offer oshi sushi, but this place has plenty of options, and they’re all delicious!

I would definately come back to try other menu!💜💜💜","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1g4wMdlKqvUEpGmytZNXAZBFmPlpd2zIZRFAu&fid=0x0:0x91e30b5a8372ae47"],"When":"2024-8-7"},{"Name":"Y Jennie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIM7WHAyn2cvREOJtbX2jNQuPyoIBgjtPWLjvsJO_3C7dpqVA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited a sushi restaurant that impressed me with its excellent food quality, reasonable prices, and convenient location.

The menu offered a wide variety of sushi and sashimi options, all incredibly fresh and skillfully prepared. Each dish highlighted the chef's expertise, from the precise cuts of fish to the perfectly seasoned rice.

Despite the high quality of the food, the prices were very reasonable, making it accessible to a wide range of customers.

Overall, I highly recommend the Woomi Roll, Sunshine Roll, and Avo Oshi that I had today :)

Please go and check out this place; it won't disappoint.

I will definitely visit Woomi again soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKXONrNOkIKuCsEVPMJdNU2XtzXqrm26eL9wkp&fid=0x0:0x91e30b5a8372ae47"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Fiona L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJoJISbnwMZeWkWADfrkXCzqTb02Zebd9qoOG5yLinVjumAgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious and fresh made sushi found in a small mall! All takeout, it’s just a sushi stand, but there are a few small tables nearby you can eat at in the mall. Portions and prices are great, everything tasted delicious and the slices of raw fish were nice and fresh!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDxy-kiOTM2AroNPnVCOyhWH-QJe_21ahyTU-k&fid=0x0:0x91e30b5a8372ae47"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"K K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLQsntpHDgzOc9qI_qNd438oblexnf5LUGqURIB40_XSlQFdw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had their salmon don, and it was stunning! The rice was well seasoned, and the fish was exceptionally fresh. I often visit here for takeout and I just noticed that the restaurant has changed ownership. BUT the excellent food and friendly service are still there!

What makes this place even more special is the value for money. They serves great quality of foods at very affordable costs. Highly recommended for anyone looking for delicious sushi :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNj0jnU19__fmkjY5qytMxdBkso_3y15pMyxvT_&fid=0x0:0x91e30b5a8372ae47"],"When":"2024-7-27"}]

Standard Vancouver pricing these days at $15.50-$16 a bowl.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNVds4yLV76B9Egpp-pDOZMGXsvc6mntjZN6Pr1&fid=0x0:0xf8174b009e5cfd14"],"When":"2022-9-21"},{"Name":"Arvin Tirk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYh2FT5cCPc0ARnWSgClckRe_ibZeJioJnK0VkkynD8VXZilEl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Honestly a good Vietnamese restaurant with good flavorful dishes and well spaced seating, but then why four stars?

Hot Vietnamese coffee was yummy but lukewarm. Hot means hot. Hot is not lukewarm.
Even the soup was lukewarm. Why?
It’s good but not good…. Okay but not okay…. Yummy food but stingy attitude with just warm food served. A lot of room for improvements and need a big heart to serve sides for free and not charge for them. Where did the asian manners, tradition and culture gone? [{"Name":"Ashley Melecio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVn7b3YsltOZczvp34LlGl71lMMhrOd9WThH168eGU8CC-Ly1O6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been waiting to introduce Dehls Gourmet to my family friends, and we finally came tonight :)! WORTH THE WAIT!! The portions are so good, and the puff puff was AMAZING. Definitely coming back with family. Also love how flaky the Jamaican patties were. Support your local businesses ✨","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDaG4QB7_KSO7t690D2nAkJEv9ZSKEFT9iuODv&fid=0x0:0x4d1bda7b762a79d2"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Kate MacMillan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIiOn4CRGx0W_zSOwBbarfyqFWSHlevsQZQeL5cK3AEIglcjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I called to see if they had anything that would be gluten free as I’ve been desperately looking to try west African cuisine! I’m so happy this restaurant has many options!

I ordered many things, some for me, some for my husband at home

For my meal I ordered:

Mushroom veg sauce with jollof rice: In the most complementary of ways, this was like a friend’s mother made you a home cooked meal that was meant to uplift you, and it did. The mushrooms were firm and flavourful and the mixed veg was firm but well cooked. The sauce was delicious! The jollof rice was fabulous.
Fried Plantain: SO GOOD. Crispy and sweet and dense.
Fresh pineapple and ginger juice: ginger really kicks in this drink and it was lovely.

To go:
Pistachio Croissant: my husband told me this was the best ever for him. The inside is filled with pistachio cream and the top is completely covered in pistachios. Well priced for the decadent nature.
Chicken Curry Patti: really good

Please note it does take time to get your order as it is made-to-order. This means it will be fresh and perfect textures, this is a win!

I can not WAIT! To come back and try more from this restaurant.

The people working on the day I came in were so friendly and were great about answering my questions. Thanks for serving up such great food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJo0xwLBRwEGLgwWOhM1C-7qLG_pHJKSQNylX0&fid=0x0:0x4d1bda7b762a79d2"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"K Joanne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZ0eLxgEfZYJMUxpADw8atKX1YqGlpQ6ymKdUBoNAcN4flUQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely West African restaurant located in the Quay. Tried the lovely honey jerk chicken wrap. They even sell  yummy pastries and gluten-free pastries.  We will come back for the weekend traditional African food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3-UFQPUCIBTtHi4mNg4gefsS-OWNeX6PlTFL9&fid=0x0:0x4d1bda7b762a79d2"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Meg *","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLXJmJLkThEQcQC8cX64Q6O9pAoiPm9DnCS9ndKFmg5JXNnPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went during the soft opening and got the tilapia and goat. We also got the grilled chicken jollof rice, which was definitely our favorite of the two! The meats were really tender, and the jollof rice itself was a comforting first experience with its subtle spices!

[{"Name":"Samrat Roy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-bYH4-yBOtNeXL4jqm3AOzFqHmewwl6Z80LgPdRXMd2gACbHH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"When we visited Jokim Kitchen in the evening, it wasn’t busy at all, which made for a relaxed dining experience. The Mẹt Bún Thập Cẩm Platter as well as lemongrass chicken rice was delicious, and the service was okay. It’s a cozy spot in New Westminster with great food and a calm atmosphere, perfect for an unhurried meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2SLK9mmOma9z99QERtaJdcVsQjBBai6Noa34M&fid=0x0:0x6631c1699c6230ad"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Michelle M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWeetN-W20mnzvtvgZG8vAeDlWwG6zd354oPCvc1I4B_3Cjy_PI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"There was plenty of seating when we arrived. We got lemongrass chicken and it was juicy and flavourful. The bbq platter was underwhelming as it came with Chinese chicken wings which I didn’t realize was extremely spicy. I never had Chinese chicken wings like this. The skewered prawns was also spicy but not as bad as the wings. Homemade sausage was delicious and I loved the large chunks of garlic in it. The beef ribs were a lower quality you will need teeth to eat it or scissors but flavour was delicious. We also for a papaya salad with beef jerky as I wasn’t full from the bbq platter. It paired well together with the beef jerky.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwaJwKBt_KnpAz94sWSekevdiDrGOBZD2qsfNf&fid=0x0:0x6631c1699c6230ad"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"Gina Grape","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjfpAS0e1J9DlXOCRvxRrfnAvo44TyYUw59aPp0ohD7GacQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good ambience inside.  A hole on the wall kinda of gem in Uptown New West. Great food and portion for your buck.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbKfhWZgiqe-B3nUCu02TypZb3vv8O3BZfBjFq&fid=0x0:0x6631c1699c6230ad"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Shulamie Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtB81aCg4AAdMLOwFvnHlpdLkbB43qZuPbkeepGzXQ192dANwppA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Our experience at Jokim was okay overall. About 3/4 of the tables were full during our visit on a Friday evening, but only one waitress working. The bun bo hue was good, the pho dac biet was okay, spring rolls were good but very thin, and the mango prawn salad was too sour (used too much filler marinated radish). Unfortunately won't be back as our experience, though not bad, wasn't great either.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOln2uOL1viXYxF1GvAAtqOPPL2BD02Plu5z5a2&fid=0x0:0x6631c1699c6230ad"],"When":"2023-12-9"},{"Name":"Alexander Thomas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLQHN0Aa0rJYdoqcfcagGbfOH-0cvC7psAXsBkP3P2cBz16RQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My wife and I went to Jokim for the first time and it was fantastic. The whole place was beautiful, clean, and had both a modern and relaxed vibe with low-fi music. We were greeted openly with a smile and sat down to see the menu. Our food came quickly, beautifully plated, and everything tasted amazing. The whole experience from start to finish was a delight. The portions were perfect, prices were more than reasonable. I really can't wait to go again and try something else on the menu.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marcus C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHlnwaovl3zd5Wc5SMTrMR58MAbhW47-67QJsaGLwyfRDvio4XoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time checking this place out and I was pleasantly surprised! Went here for a quick lunch and got the steak and the lady got vermicelli and both were so tasty! The sauce on the steak was next level and with an egg it made it that much better. The vermicelli was a perfect and filling dish for the lady as well. I'm looking forward to trying out the platter next time we come! Thanks for the great service, food and atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8_84XbjO5zxBoVrtaH5zOl2FqXLf8mBEVa010&fid=0x0:0x6631c1699c6230ad"],"When":"2023-2-12"},{"Name":"Lee Jay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzDtMsWCn-NlUmLWHN1-Vcx1s1iKHSJVkIwJ44E45omza3tzcN=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ate in many Vietnamese restaurants before, if you are looking for delicious Vietnamese food with affordable price, good customer service and generous food portion then this is the right place!

I ordered spicy noodle soup, they putted in real broth which they already cooked for 16 hours (not just water).

Jokim is the best and I will recommended to everyone!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHW2ImNbd78zO2Jt9fQ7IKVxFFs5L3dd3IlVqn&fid=0x0:0x6631c1699c6230ad"],"When":"2023-4-16"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, just wow! The Saigon platter was excellent! I didn't know grilled galangal pork can taste this good. The grilled beef in petel leaves was so juicy. I also love their mini pancakes, crispy bottom and rich coconut flavor inside. Fruit smoothies (avocado & mango) were okay, the flavor was not strong but the texture was creamy. Nice & attentive waitress.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNv2IksPCj6nJorm8StjZX4ISFAuOiHu4klHrrR&fid=0x0:0x6631c1699c6230ad"],"When":"2023-7-8"}]

Beds were comfy, pillows were a little too soft for my liking. The River Market, and the Boathouse Restaurant, are both just steps away, so your eating/dining options are voluminous.

The walk along the Quay is a nice way to spend some time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6uLnPHoYl_IaORISY4rMQmkzeUkgvxFqKsOMk&fid=0x0:0x7da59db8243cb015"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Brenda Duggan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX72ivqfktOPzKiV9Rp9tX0k5boQ36TuDWhPr5BSXJHNs0PzJ2J3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very comfortable room and bed. This recent room number was 516.  The beds are super comfortable pocket coil mattresses as you do not feel your partner move at all.  There is a fantastic collection of pillows for all sleeper types.  The view was great, service fantastic, and you are greeted with water and free chocolate bars or you can purchase specialized packages.  We purchased the craft beer, nuts and chips package for $30.  Well worth it. Rooms are very clean and despite being in the heart of New Westminster right on the water, it is not loud at all.  The AC provides white noise but bring ear plugs if you are a light sleeper.   There is 1 level 2 EV charger for those with electric vehicles.  Highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLw4llB2yv4HnhbOvAuoine2jZZZt5wMHehvK-&fid=0x0:0x7da59db8243cb015"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Jackie’s Law","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUszzOqI_r931gkNL0kGramN4TG_x4gsqPklTIBKTOEpgOmyBOj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Located by the riverside in New Westminster, an unique hotel on the out skirt of Vancouver, that takes about 30 mins to an hour subway ride to the city, the fun part is get to see the real lifestyle of the city. Rooms is in fair sized and clean, very quiet. There’s a market place by the water, and the subway station across the railway that has some retailers, offer guests convenience to get food and life supplies. Overall a pleasant experience as we stayed 2 nights before our cruise set sail from Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfCvxvDvKSehXnsWxavdYeJJANa_a7Bcu1Kdvr&fid=0x0:0x7da59db8243cb015"],"When":"2024-10-9"},{"Name":"Heather Haskett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIamAn44XQNFAxbHdibfDcIoHgoMYPDQLZQhVSlwUyivFQDAw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love my stays at the Inn on the Quay. The staff is exceptional and the rooms are magnificent. The front desk and housekeeping staff always ensure my week long stays are very enjoyable and the Boathouse is a great dining experience. You’re my favorite hotel!!","Images":null,"When":""}]
